{"target_data":{"ip_address":"10.8.200.69","role":"Workstation","fqdn":"MHL-PW06M2V2.maxhealth.com","mac_address":"F4:A8:0D:98:0A:4B","host_name":"MHL-PW06M2V2","target_type":"Computing"},"title":"SCC Generated CKLB at: 2026-03-05T07:54:57","cklb_version":"1.0","id":"A696242E-6D7C-1014-B621-8B243F66D9BB","stigs":[{"uuid":"2366E687-6D7C-1014-938D-B7BE63F2C882","stig_name":"Google Chrome Current Windows Security Technical Implementation Guide","version":"2","size":46,"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","reference_identifier":"4081","stig_id":"Google_Chrome_Current_Windows","rules":[{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-221558r960804","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:15\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Disable firewall traversal)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\RemoteAccessHostFirewallTraversal'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBC-0001","rule_title":"Firewall traversal from remote host must be disabled.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.chrome:def:240001"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-001414"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Universal method:        \n   1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy        \n   2. If RemoteAccessHostFirewallTraversal is not displayed under the Policy Name column or it is not set to false under the Policy Value column, then this is a finding.\n\nWindows registry:\n   1. Start regedit\n   2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n   3. If the RemoteAccessHostFirewallTraversal value name does not exist or its value data is not set to 0, then this is a finding.  \n","rule_id_src":"SV-221558r960804_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000039","false_positives":"","uuid":"2369288E-6D7C-1014-B091-9C76ADEF5328","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4081","stig_uuid":"2366E687-6D7C-1014-938D-B7BE63F2C882","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-57545","V-44711"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-221558","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000039","id":"V-221558"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n 1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc \n 2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative\\Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\Remote Access\n Policy Name: Enable firewall traversal from remote access host\n Policy State: Disabled\n Policy Value: N/A","discussion":"Remote connections should never be allowed that bypass the firewall, as there is no way to verify if they can be trusted. Enables usage of STUN and relay servers when remote clients are trying to establish a connection to this machine. If this setting is enabled, then remote clients can discover and connect to this machine even if they are separated by a firewall. If this setting is disabled and outgoing UDP connections are filtered by the firewall, then this machine will only allow connections from client machines within the local network. If this policy is left not set the setting will be enabled.\t","group_id_src":"V-221558"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-221559r961083","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:15\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Disable tracking user's location)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\DefaultGeolocationSetting'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBC-0002","rule_title":"Site tracking users location must be disabled.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.chrome:def:240002"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-001166"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Universal method:               \n   1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy             \n   2. If DefaultGeolocationSetting is not displayed under the Policy Name column or it is not set to 2, then this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n   1. Start regedit\n   2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n   3. If the DefaultGeolocationSetting value name does not exist or its value data is not set to 2, then this is a finding.\n","rule_id_src":"SV-221559r961083_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000206","false_positives":"","uuid":"236935D7-6D7C-1014-9B82-C692A2CADF4A","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4081","stig_uuid":"2366E687-6D7C-1014-938D-B7BE63F2C882","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-57557","V-44723"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-221559","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000206","id":"V-221559"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Windows group policy:    \n   1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc   \n   2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\Content Settings\\    \n   Policy Name: Default geolocation setting    \n   Policy State: Enabled    \n   Policy Value: Do not allow any site to track the users' physical location\n\n","discussion":"Website tracking is the practice of gathering information as to which websites were accesses by a browser. The common method of doing this is to have a website create a tracking cookie on the browser.   If the information of what sites are being accessed is made available to unauthorized persons, this violates confidentiality requirements, and over time poses a significant OPSEC issue. This policy setting allows you to set whether websites are allowed to track the userâs physical location. Tracking the userâs physical location can be allowed by default, denied by default or the user can be asked every time a website requests the physical location.\t\n   1 = Allow sites to track the userâs physical location\t\n   2 = Do not allow any site to track the userâs physical location\t\n   3 = Ask whenever a site wants to track the userâs physical location","group_id_src":"V-221559"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-221561r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:15\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Disable pop-ups)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\DefaultPopupsSetting'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBC-0004","rule_title":"Sites ability to show pop-ups must be disabled.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.chrome:def:240004"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Universal method: \n 1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy \n 2. If DefaultPopupsSetting is not displayed under the Policy Name column or it is not set to 2, then this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n 1. Start regedit\n 2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n 3. If the value name DefaultPopupsSetting does not exist or its value data is not set to 2, then this is a finding.\n\nNote:  If AO Approved exceptions to this rule have been enabled, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-221561r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"23693EF2-6D7C-1014-BFA3-C40ED599AFA4","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4081","stig_uuid":"2366E687-6D7C-1014-938D-B7BE63F2C882","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-57553","V-44719"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-221561","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-221561"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n   1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc   \n   2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\Content Settings\\\n    Policy Name: Default popups setting\n    Policy State: Enabled\n    Policy Value: Do not allow any site to show popups\n\n","discussion":"Chrome allows you to manage whether unwanted pop-up windows appear. Pop-up windows that are opened when the end user clicks a link are not blocked. If you enable this policy setting, most unwanted pop-up windows are prevented from appearing. If you disable this policy setting, pop-up windows are not prevented from appearing. If you disable this policy setting, scripts can continue to create pop-up windows, and pop-ups that hide other windows. Recommend configuring this setting to â2â to help prevent malicious websites from controlling the pop-up windows or fooling users into clicking on the wrong window.  If you do not configure this policy setting, most unwanted pop-up windows are prevented from appearing.  If this policy is left not set, 'BlockPopups' will be used and the user will be able to change it.    \n   1 = Allow all sites to show pop-ups    \n   2 = Do not allow any site to show pop-ups","group_id_src":"V-221561"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-221562r960879","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:15\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Extensions installation are blocklisted by default)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\ExtensionInstallBlocklist\\1'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBC-0005","rule_title":"Extensions installation must be blocklisted by default.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.chrome:def:240005"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000169"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Universal method: \n 1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy \n 2. If ExtensionInstallBlocklist is not displayed under the Policy Name column or it is not set to * under the Policy Value column, then this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n 1. Start regedit\n 2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\ExtensionInstallBlocklist\n 3. If the a registry value name of 1 does not exist under that key or its value is not set to *, then this is a finding. ","rule_id_src":"SV-221562r960879_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000089","false_positives":"","uuid":"2369465A-6D7C-1014-A38F-B25DA4B91B43","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4081","stig_uuid":"2366E687-6D7C-1014-938D-B7BE63F2C882","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-57561","V-44727"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-221562","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000089","id":"V-221562"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n 1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc \n 2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\Extensions\\\n Policy Name: Configure extension installation blocklist\n Policy State: Enabled\n Policy Value: *","discussion":"Extensions are developed by third party sources and are designed to extend Google Chrome's functionality. An extension can be made by anyone, to do and access almost anything on a system; this means they pose a high risk to any system that would allow all extensions to be installed by default. Allows you to specify which extensions the users can NOT install. Extensions already installed will be removed if blocklisted. A blocklist value of '*' means all extensions are blocklisted unless they are explicitly listed in the allowlist. If this policy is left not set the user can install any extension in Google Chrome.","group_id_src":"V-221562"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-221563r1015468","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:15\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Extensions that are approved for use are allowlisted)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\ExtensionInstallAllowlist\\1'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBC-0006","rule_title":"Extensions that are approved for use must be allowlisted.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.chrome:def:240006"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Universal method: \n1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy \n2. If ExtensionInstallAllowlist is not displayed under the Policy Name column or it is not set to oiigbmnaadbkfbmpbfijlflahbdbdgdf or a list of administrator approved extension IDs, then this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n1. Start regedit\n2. Navigate to the key HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\ExtensionInstallAllowlist\n3. If the ExtensionInstallAllowlist key is not set to 1 and oiigbmnaadbkfbmpbfijlflahbdbdgdf or a list of administrator-approved extension IDs, then this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-221563r1015468_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","false_positives":"","uuid":"23694D1F-6D7C-1014-8952-BCCEF09BB55D","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4081","stig_uuid":"2366E687-6D7C-1014-938D-B7BE63F2C882","severity":"low","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-57563","V-44729"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-221563","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000210","id":"V-221563"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc \n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\Extensions\\\nPolicy Name: Configure extension installation allowlist\nPolicy State: Enabled\nPolicy Value: oiigbmnaadbkfbmpbfijlflahbdbdgdf\n\nNote: oiigbmnaadbkfbmpbfijlflahbdbdgdfis the extension ID for scriptno (a commonly used Chrome extension), other extension IDs may vary.","discussion":"The allowlist should only contain organizationally approved extensions. This is to prevent a user from accidently allowlisitng a malicious extension. This policy allows you to specify which extensions are not subject to the blacklist. A blacklist value of â*â means all extensions are blacklisted and users can only install extensions listed in the allowlist. By default, no extensions are allowlisted. If all extensions have been blacklisted by policy, then the allowlist policy can be used to allow specific extensions to be installed. Administrators should determine which extensions should be allowed to be installed by their users. If no extensions are allowlisted, then no extensions can be installed when combined with blacklisting all extensions.","group_id_src":"V-221563"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-221564r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:15\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Set default search provider name)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\DefaultSearchProviderName'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBC-0007","rule_title":"The default search providers name must be set.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.chrome:def:240007"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Universal method:        \n   1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy        \n   2. If DefaultSearchProviderName is displayed under the Policy Name column or it is not set to an organization approved encrypted search provider that corresponds to the encrypted search provider set in DTBC-0008(ex. Google Encrypted, Bing Encrypted) under the Policy Value column, then this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n   1. Start regedit\n   2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n   3. If the DefaultSearchProviderName value name does not exist or it is not set to an organization approved encrypted search provider that corresponds to the encrypted search provider set in DTBC-0008(ex. Google Encrypted, Bing Encrypted), then this is a finding.\n","rule_id_src":"SV-221564r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"23695446-6D7C-1014-9C27-9E05A21F6779","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4081","stig_uuid":"2366E687-6D7C-1014-938D-B7BE63F2C882","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-57567","V-44733"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-221564","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-221564"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n   1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc   \n   2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\Default search provider\\\n    Policy Name: Default search provider name\n    Policy State: Enabled\n    Policy Value: set to an organization approved encrypted search provider that corresponds to the encrypted search provider set in DTBC-0008(ex. Google Encrypted, Bing Encrypted)\n\n","discussion":"Specifies the name of the default search provider that is to be used, if left empty or not set, the host name specified by the search URL will be used. This policy is only considered if the 'DefaultSearchProviderEnabled' policy is enabled. When doing internet searches it is important to use an encrypted connection via https.","group_id_src":"V-221564"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-221565r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:15\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (The default search provider URL must be set to perform encrypted searches.)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\DefaultSearchProviderSearchURL'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBC-0008","rule_title":"The default search provider URL must be set to perform encrypted searches.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.chrome:def:221565"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"If the system is on the SIPRNet, this requirement is NA.\n\nUniversal method: \n1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy.\n2. If DefaultSearchProviderSearchURL is not displayed under the Policy Name column or it is not set to an organization-approved encrypted search string (ex. https://www.google.com/search?q={searchTerms} or https://www.bing.com/search?q={searchTerms} ) under the Policy Value column, this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n1. Start regedit.\n2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\.\n3. If the DefaultSearchProviderSearchURL value name does not exist or its value data is not set to an organization-approved encrypted search string (ex. https://www.google.com/search?q={searchTerms} or https://www.bing.com/search?q={searchTerms} ), this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-221565r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"23695BBD-6D7C-1014-AD41-9AF84137859B","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4081","stig_uuid":"2366E687-6D7C-1014-938D-B7BE63F2C882","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-57569","V-44735"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-221565","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-221565"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"If the system is on the SIPRNet, this requirement is NA.\n\nWindows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc.\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\Default search provider\\.\n- Policy Name: Default search provider search URL\n- Policy State: Enabled\n- Policy Value: Must be set to an organization-approved encrypted search string \n(ex. https://www.google.com/search?q={searchTerms} or https://www.bing.com/search?q={searchTerms} )","discussion":"Specifies the URL of the search engine used when doing a default search. The URL should contain the string '{searchTerms}', which will be replaced at query time by the terms the user is searching for. This option must be set when the 'DefaultSearchProviderEnabled' policy is enabled and will only be respected if this is the case.  When doing internet searches it is important to use an encrypted connection via https.","group_id_src":"V-221565"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-221566r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:15\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Enable default search provider)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\DefaultSearchProviderEnabled'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBC-0009","rule_title":"Default search provider must be enabled.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.chrome:def:240009"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Universal method: \n 1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy \n 2. If DefaultSearchProviderEnabled is not displayed under the Policy Name column or it is not set to true under the Policy Value column, then this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n 1. Start regedit\n 2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n 3. If the DefaultSearchProviderEnabled value name does not exist or its value data is not set to 1, then this is a finding.\n\nNote: This policy will only display in the chrome://policy tab on domain joined systems. On standalone systems, the policy will not display.","rule_id_src":"SV-221566r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"2369620D-6D7C-1014-9B55-D5FCB9ADC606","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4081","stig_uuid":"2366E687-6D7C-1014-938D-B7BE63F2C882","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-57571","V-44737"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-221566","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-221566"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n   1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc   \n   2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\Default search provider\\\n    Policy Name: Enable the default search provider\n    Policy State: Enabled\n    Policy Value: N/A\n\n","discussion":"Policy enables the use of a default search provider. If you enable this setting, a default search is performed when the user types text in the omnibox that is not a URL. You can specify the default search provider to be used by setting the rest of the default search policies. If these are left empty, the user can choose the default provider. If you disable this setting, no search is performed when the user enters non-URL text in the omnibox. If you enable or disable this setting, users cannot change or override this setting in Google Chrome. If this policy is left not set, the default search provider is enabled, and the user will be able to set the search provider list.","group_id_src":"V-221566"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-221567r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:15\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Disable Password Manager)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\PasswordManagerEnabled'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBC-0011","rule_title":"The Password Manager must be disabled.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.chrome:def:240011"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Universal method:           \n   1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy           \n   2. If PasswordManagerEnabled is not displayed under the Policy Name column or it is not set to false under the Policy Value column, then this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n   1. Start regedit\n   2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n   3. If the PasswordManagerEnabled value name does not exist or its value data is not set to 0, then this is a finding.\n","rule_id_src":"SV-221567r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"23696882-6D7C-1014-B262-ECE54688DE29","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4081","stig_uuid":"2366E687-6D7C-1014-938D-B7BE63F2C882","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-57575","V-44741"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-221567","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-221567"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc \n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\Password Manager\\\nPolicy Name: Enable Saving Passwords to the Password Manager\nPolicy State: Disabled\nPolicy Value: N/A","discussion":"Enables saving passwords and using saved passwords in Google Chrome. Malicious sites may take advantage of this feature by using hidden fields gain access to the stored information. If you enable this setting, users can have Google Chrome memorize passwords and provide them automatically the next time they log in to a site. If you disable this setting, users are not able to save passwords or use already saved passwords. If you enable or disable this setting, users cannot change or override this setting in Google Chrome. If this policy is left not set, this will be enabled but the user will be able to change it. ListPassword manager should not be used as it stores passwords locally.","group_id_src":"V-221567"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-221570r960921","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:15\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Disable background processing)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\BackgroundModeEnabled'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBC-0017","rule_title":"Background processing must be disabled.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.chrome:def:240017"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-001695"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Universal method:        \n   1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy        \n   2. If BackgroundModeEnabled is not displayed under the Policy Name column and it is not set to false under the Policy Value column, then this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n   1. Start regedit\n   2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n   3. If the BackgroundModeEnabled value name does not exist or its value data is not set to 0, then this is a finding.\n","rule_id_src":"SV-221570r960921_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000112","false_positives":"","uuid":"23696E9F-6D7C-1014-B911-D179D00EA565","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4081","stig_uuid":"2366E687-6D7C-1014-938D-B7BE63F2C882","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-57587","V-44753"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-221570","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000112","id":"V-221570"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n   1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc   \n   2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\\n    Policy Name: Continue running background apps when Google Chrome is closed\n    Policy State: Disabled\n    Policy Value: N/A","discussion":"Determines whether a Google Chrome process is started on OS login that keeps running when the last browser window is closed, allowing background apps to remain active. The background process displays an icon in the system tray and can always be closed from there. If this policy is set to True, background mode is enabled and cannot be controlled by the user in the browser settings. If this policy is set to False, background mode is disabled and cannot be controlled by the user in the browser settings. If this policy is left unset, background mode is initially disabled and can be controlled by the user in the browser settings.' - Google Chrome Administrators Policy ListThis setting, if enabled, allows Google Chrome to run at all times. There is two reasons that this is not wanted. First, it can tie up system resources that might otherwise be needed. Second, it does not make it obvious to the user that it is running and poorly written extensions could cause instability on the system.","group_id_src":"V-221570"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-221571r987620","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:15\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Disable Google data synchronization)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\SyncDisabled'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBC-0020","rule_title":"Google Data Synchronization must be disabled.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.chrome:def:240020"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-001374"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Universal method:        \n  1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy        \n  2. If SyncDisabled is not displayed under the Policy Name column or it is not set to true under the Policy Value column, then this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n   1. Start regedit\n   2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n   3. If the SyncDisabled value name does not exist or its value data is not set to 1, then this is a finding.\n","rule_id_src":"SV-221571r987620_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000047","false_positives":"","uuid":"236974B9-6D7C-1014-B26F-D24E583E92E8","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4081","stig_uuid":"2366E687-6D7C-1014-938D-B7BE63F2C882","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-57593","V-44759"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-221571","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000047","id":"V-221571"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n   1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc   \n   2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\\n    Policy Name: Disable synchronization of data with Google\n    Policy State: Enabled\n    Policy Value: N/A","discussion":"Disables data synchronization in Google Chrome using Google-hosted synchronization services and prevents users from changing this setting. If you enable this setting, users cannot change or override this setting in Google Chrome. If this policy is left not set the user will be able to enable Google Sync.  Google Sync is used to sync information between different user devices, this data is then stored on Google owned servers. The synced data may consist of information such as email, calendars, viewing history, etc. This feature must be disabled because the organization does not have control over the servers the data is stored on.","group_id_src":"V-221571"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-221572r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:15\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (The URL protocol schema javascript is disabled)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\URLBlocklist\\1'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBC-0021","rule_title":"The URL protocol schema javascript must be disabled.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.chrome:def:240021"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Universal method:\n1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy.\n2. If URLBlocklist is not displayed under the Policy Name column or it is not set to javascript://* under the Policy Value column, this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n1. Start regedit.\n2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\URLBlocklist.\n3. If the URLBlocklist key does not exist, or the does not contain entries 1 set to javascript://*, this is a finding.\n\n","rule_id_src":"SV-221572r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"23697AC8-6D7C-1014-8B47-F9458BF62824","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4081","stig_uuid":"2366E687-6D7C-1014-938D-B7BE63F2C882","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-57595","V-44761"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-221572","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-221572"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc. \n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\\nPolicy Name: Block access to a list of URLs.\n- Policy State: Enabled\n- Policy Value 1: javascript://*","discussion":"Each access to a URL is handled by the browser according to the URL's \"scheme\". The \"scheme\" of a URL is the section before the \":\". The term \"protocol\" is often mistakenly used for a \"scheme\". The difference is that the scheme is how the browser handles a URL and the protocol is how the browser communicates with a service.  If a scheme or its associated protocol used by a browser is insecure or obsolete, vulnerabilities can be exploited resulting in exposed data or unrestricted access to the browser's system.   The browser must be configured to disable the use of insecure and obsolete schemas (protocols).\nThis policy disables the listed protocol schemes in Google Chrome, URLs using a scheme from this list will not load and cannot be navigated to. If this policy is left not set or the list is empty all schemes will be accessible in Google Chrome.","group_id_src":"V-221572"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-221573r987620","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:15\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Disable cloud print sharing)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\\CloudPrintProxyEnabled'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBC-0023","rule_title":"Cloud print sharing must be disabled.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.chrome:def:240023"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-001374"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Universal method:        \n   1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy        \n   2. If CloudPrintProxyEnabled is not displayed under the Policy Name column or it is not set to false under the Policy Value column, then this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n   1. Start regedit\n   2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n   3. If the CloudPrintProxyEnabled value name does not exist or its value data is not set to 0, then this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-221573r987620_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000047","false_positives":"","uuid":"236980DC-6D7C-1014-AA56-AF0ED75601D9","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4081","stig_uuid":"2366E687-6D7C-1014-938D-B7BE63F2C882","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-57599","V-44765"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-221573","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000047","id":"V-221573"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n 1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc \n 2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\Printing\n Policy Name: Enable Google Cloud Print proxy\n Policy State: Disabled\n Policy Value: N/A","discussion":"Policy enables Google Chrome to act as a proxy between Google Cloud Print and legacy printers connected to the machine. If this setting is enabled or not configured, users can enable the cloud print proxy by authentication with their Google account. If this setting is disabled, users cannot enable the proxy, and the machine will not be allowed to share itâs printers with Google Cloud Print. If this policy is not set, this will be enabled but the user will be able to change it.","group_id_src":"V-221573"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-221574r961863","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:15\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Disable network prediction)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\NetworkPredictionOptions'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBC-0025","rule_title":"Network prediction must be disabled.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.chrome:def:240025"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Universal method:\n1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy\n2. If \"NetworkPredictionOptions\" is not displayed under the âPolicy Nameâ column or it is not set to \"2\" under the âPolicy Valueâ column, this is a finding.\nWindows method:\n1. Start regedit\n2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n3. If the \"NetworkPredictionOptions\" value name does not exist or its value data is not set to \"2,\" this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-221574r961863_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","false_positives":"","uuid":"236986D8-6D7C-1014-A717-82FDF8382A90","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4081","stig_uuid":"2366E687-6D7C-1014-938D-B7BE63F2C882","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-57603","V-44769"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-221574","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000516","id":"V-221574"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\\nPolicy Name: Enable network prediction\nPolicy State: Enabled\nPolicy Value: Do not predict network actions on any network connection","discussion":"Enables network prediction in Google Chrome and prevents users from changing this setting. If you enable or disable this setting, users cannot change or override this setting in Google Chrome. If this policy is left not set, this will be disabled but the user will be able to change it.","group_id_src":"V-221574"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-221575r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:15\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Disable Google metrics reporting)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\MetricsReportingEnabled'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBC-0026","rule_title":"Metrics reporting to Google must be disabled.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.chrome:def:240026"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Universal method: \n 1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy \n 2. If MetricsReportingEnabled is not displayed under the Policy Name column or it is not set to false under the Policy Value column, then this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n 1. Start regedit\n 2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n 3. If the MetricsReportingEnabled value name does not exist or its value data is not set to 0, then this is a finding.\n\nNote: This policy will only display in the chrome://policy tab on domain joined systems. On standalone systems, the policy will not display.","rule_id_src":"SV-221575r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"23698CEA-6D7C-1014-9EF7-928E4BFCD0B2","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4081","stig_uuid":"2366E687-6D7C-1014-938D-B7BE63F2C882","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-57605","V-44771"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-221575","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-221575"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n   1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc   \n   2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\\n    Policy Name: Enable reporting of usage and crash-related data\n    Policy State: Disabled\n    Policy Value: N/A","discussion":"Enables anonymous reporting of usage and crash-related data about Google Chrome to Google and prevents users from changing this setting. If you enable this setting, anonymous reporting of usage and crash-related data is sent to Google. A crash report could contain sensitive information from the computer's memory. If you disable this setting, anonymous reporting of usage and crash-related data is never sent to Google. If you enable or disable this setting, users cannot change or override this setting in Google Chrome. If this policy is left not set the setting will be what the user chose upon installation / first run.","group_id_src":"V-221575"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-221576r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:15\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Enable search suggestion)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\SearchSuggestEnabled'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBC-0027","rule_title":"Search suggestions must be disabled.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.chrome:def:240027"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Universal method:        \n   1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy        \n   2. If SearchSuggestEnabled is not displayed under the Policy Name column or it is not set to false under the Policy Value column, then this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n   1. Start regedit\n   2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n   3. If the SearchSuggestEnabled value name does not exist or its value data is not set to 0, then this is a finding.\n","rule_id_src":"SV-221576r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"236994A0-6D7C-1014-B918-A873AE1E6AC7","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4081","stig_uuid":"2366E687-6D7C-1014-938D-B7BE63F2C882","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-57607","V-44773"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-221576","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-221576"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n   1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc   \n   2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\\n    Policy Name: Enable search suggestions\n    Policy State: Disabled\n    Policy Value: N/A","discussion":"Search suggestion should be disabled as it could lead to searches being conducted that were never intended to be made. Enables search suggestions in Google Chrome's omnibox and prevents users from changing this setting. If you enable this setting, search suggestions are used. If you disable this setting, search suggestions are never used. If you enable or disable this setting, users cannot change or override this setting in Google Chrome. If this policy is left not set, this will be enabled but the user will be able to change it.","group_id_src":"V-221576"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-221577r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:15\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Password history=VAR)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\ImportSavedPasswords'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBC-0029","rule_title":"Importing of saved passwords must be disabled.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.chrome:def:240029"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Universal method:        \n   1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy        \n   2. If ImportSavedPasswords is not displayed under the Policy Name column or it is not set to false under the Policy Value column, then this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n   1. Start regedit\n   2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n   3. If the ImportSavedPasswords value name does not exist or its value data is not set to 0, then this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-221577r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"23699C58-6D7C-1014-80E6-9723DB99F828","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4081","stig_uuid":"2366E687-6D7C-1014-938D-B7BE63F2C882","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-57609","V-44775"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-221577","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-221577"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n   1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc   \n   2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\\n   Policy Name: Import saved passwords from default browser on first run\n   Policy State: Disabled\n   Policy Value: N/A","discussion":"Importing of saved passwords should be disabled as it could lead to unencrypted account passwords stored on the system from another browser to be viewed. This policy forces the saved passwords to be imported from the previous default browser if enabled. If enabled, this policy also affects the import dialog. If disabled, the saved passwords are not imported. If it is not set, the user may be asked whether to import, or importing may happen automatically.","group_id_src":"V-221577"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-221578r960864","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:15\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Disable incognito mode)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\IncognitoModeAvailability'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBC-0030","rule_title":"Incognito mode must be disabled.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.chrome:def:240030"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000166"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Universal method:        \n   1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy        \n   2. If IncognitoModeAvailability is not displayed under the Policy Name column or it is not set to 1 under the Policy Value column, then this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n   1. Start regedit\n   2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n   3. If the IncognitoModeAvailability value name does not exist or its value data is not set to 1, then this is a finding.\n","rule_id_src":"SV-221578r960864_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000080","false_positives":"","uuid":"2369A3D2-6D7C-1014-949D-A7CB399B8BC8","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4081","stig_uuid":"2366E687-6D7C-1014-938D-B7BE63F2C882","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-57611","V-44777"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-221578","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000080","id":"V-221578"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n   1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc   \n   2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\\n    Policy Name: Incognito mode availability\n    Policy State: Enabled\n    Policy Value: Incognito mode disabled","discussion":"Incognito mode allows the user to browse the Internet without recording their browsing history/activity.  From a forensics perspective, this is unacceptable.  Best practice requires that browser history is retained.  The \"IncognitoModeAvailability\" setting controls whether the user may utilize Incognito mode in Google Chrome. If 'Enabled' is selected or the policy is left unset, pages may be opened in Incognito mode. If 'Disabled' is selected, pages may not be opened in Incognito mode. If 'Forced' is selected, pages may be opened ONLY in Incognito mode.   \n   0 = Incognito mode available.    \n   1 = Incognito mode disabled.    \n   2 = Incognito mode forced.","group_id_src":"V-221578"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-221579r961893","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:15\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Perform online revocation checks)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\EnableOnlineRevocationChecks'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBC-0037","rule_title":"Online revocation checks must be performed.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.chrome:def:240037"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000185"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Universal method:        \n   1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy        \n   2. If EnableOnlineRevocationChecks is not displayed under the Policy Name column or it is not set to true under the Policy Value column, then this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n   1. Start regedit\n   2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n   3. If the EnableOnlineRevocationChecks value name does not exist or its value data is not set to 1, then this is a finding.\n","rule_id_src":"SV-221579r961893_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000605","false_positives":"","uuid":"2369ADCD-6D7C-1014-8F05-DEA963595ECD","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4081","stig_uuid":"2366E687-6D7C-1014-938D-B7BE63F2C882","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-57623","V-44789"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-221579","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000605","id":"V-221579"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n 1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc \n 2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\\n Policy Name: Enable online OCSP/CRL checks\n Policy State: Enabled\n Policy Value: N/A","discussion":"By setting this policy to true, the previous behavior is restored and online OCSP/CRL checks will be performed. If the policy is not set, or is set to false, then Chrome will not perform online revocation checks. Certificates are revoked when they have been compromised or are no longer valid, and this option protects users from submitting confidential data to a site that may be fraudulent or not secure.","group_id_src":"V-221579"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-221580r961083","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:15\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Safe Browsing is enabled)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\SafeBrowsingProtectionLevel'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBC-0038","rule_title":"Safe Browsing must be enabled.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.chrome:def:240038"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-001166"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Universal method: \n 1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy \n 2. If SafeBrowsingProtectionLevel is not displayed under the Policy Name column or it is not set to 1 or 2 under the Policy Value column, then this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n 1. Start regedit\n 2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n 3. If the SafeBrowsingProtectionLevel value name does not exist or its value data is not set to 1 or 2, then this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-221580r961083_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000206","false_positives":"","uuid":"2369B4D2-6D7C-1014-9A56-CFD57C1C586B","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4081","stig_uuid":"2366E687-6D7C-1014-938D-B7BE63F2C882","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-57625","V-44791"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-221580","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000206","id":"V-221580"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n 1. Open the âgroup policy editorâ tool with gpedit.msc\n 2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\Safe Browsing Settings\n Policy Name: Safe Browsing Protection Level\n Policy State: Enabled\n Policy Value: \"(1) Safe Browsing is active in the standard mode\", or \"(2) Safe Browsing is active in the enhanced mode. This mode provides better security, but requires sharing more browsing information with Google\".","discussion":"Allows you to control whether Google Chrome's Safe Browsing feature is enabled and the mode it operates in.\n\nIf this policy is set to 'NoProtection' (value 0), Safe Browsing is never active.\n\nIf this policy is set to 'StandardProtection' (value 1, which is the default), Safe Browsing is always active in the standard mode.\n\nIf this policy is set to 'EnhancedProtection' (value 2), Safe Browsing is always active in the enhanced mode, which provides better security, but requires sharing more browsing information with Google.","group_id_src":"V-221580"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-221581r961128","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:15\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Save browser history)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\SavingBrowserHistoryDisabled'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBC-0039","rule_title":"Browser history must be saved.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.chrome:def:240039"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-001199"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Universal method:        \n   1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy        \n   2. If the policy 'SavingBrowserHistoryDisabled' is not shown or is not set to false, then this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n   1. Start regedit\n   2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n   3. If the SavingBrowserHistoryDisabled value name does not exist or its value data is not set to 0, then this is a finding.\n","rule_id_src":"SV-221581r961128_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000231","false_positives":"","uuid":"2369BB25-6D7C-1014-B738-FB02E8BB01B8","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4081","stig_uuid":"2366E687-6D7C-1014-938D-B7BE63F2C882","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-57627","V-44793"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-221581","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000231","id":"V-221581"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n   1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc   \n   2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\\n    Policy Name: Disable saving browser history\n    Policy State: Disabled\n    Policy Value:  N/A","discussion":"This policy disables saving browser history in Google Chrome and prevents users from changing this setting. If this setting is enabled, browsing history is not saved. If this setting is disabled or not set, browsing history is saved.","group_id_src":"V-221581"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-221584r961683","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:15\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT II, V-221584, SV-221584r961683, SRG-APP-000456)\n","rule_version":"DTBC-0050","rule_title":"The version of Google Chrome running on the system must be a supported version.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-ocil.xml","name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.chrome:questionnaire:4301"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-002605"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Universal method: \n1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://settings/help\n2. Cross-reference the build information displayed with the Google Chrome site to identify, at minimum, the oldest supported build available.  As of July 2019, this is 74.x.x.\n3. If the installed version of Chrome is not supported by Google, this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-221584r961683_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000456","false_positives":"","uuid":"2369C14D-6D7C-1014-98C1-FFE4C288F608","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4081","stig_uuid":"2366E687-6D7C-1014-938D-B7BE63F2C882","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-57639","V-44805"],"status":"not_reviewed","group_id":"V-221584","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000456","id":"V-221584"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Install a supported version of Google Chrome.","discussion":"Google Chrome is being continually updated by the vendor in order to address identified security vulnerabilities. Running an older version of the browser can introduce security vulnerabilities to the system.","group_id_src":"V-221584"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-221586r960879","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:15\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :   false (Check to make sure that google chrome is set to not allow deletion of browser and download history.)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\AllowDeletingBrowserHistory'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBC-0052","rule_title":"Deletion of browser history must be disabled.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.chrome:def:240052"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000169"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Universal method: \n 1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy \n 2. If the policy \"AllowDeletingBrowserHistory\" is not shown or is not set to false, this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n 1. Start regedit\n 2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n 3. If the \"AllowDeletingBrowserHistory\" value name does not exist or its value data is not set to \"0\",  this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-221586r960879_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000089","false_positives":"","uuid":"2369C77E-6D7C-1014-AD88-8B7076822130","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4081","stig_uuid":"2366E687-6D7C-1014-938D-B7BE63F2C882","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-89845","V-75165"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-221586","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000089","id":"V-221586"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n 1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc \n 2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\\n Policy Name: Enable deleting browser and download history\n Policy State: Disabled\n Policy Value: N/A","discussion":"Disabling this function will prevent users from deleting their browsing history, which could be used to identify malicious websites and files that could later be used for anti-virus and Intrusion Detection System (IDS) signatures. Furthermore, preventing users from deleting browsing history could be used to identify abusive web surfing on government systems.","group_id_src":"V-221586"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-221587r960879","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:15\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Prompt for download location)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\PromptForDownloadLocation'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBC-0053","rule_title":"Prompt for download location must be enabled.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.chrome:def:640053"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000169"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Universal method:\n1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome:// policy\n2. If \"PromptForDownloadLocation\" is not displayed under the \"Policy Name\" column or it is not set to \"true\" under the \"Policy Value\" column, then this is a finding.\nWindows method:\n1. Start regedit\n2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n3. If the \"PromptForDownloadLocation\" value name does not exist or its value data is not set to \"1\", this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-221587r960879_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000089","false_positives":"","uuid":"2369CDEA-6D7C-1014-9D3F-C7F85F0EB569","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4081","stig_uuid":"2366E687-6D7C-1014-938D-B7BE63F2C882","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-94633","V-79929"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-221587","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000089","id":"V-221587"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc\n2. Navigate to Policy Path:  Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\\n Policy Name: Ask where to save each file before downloading\n Policy State:  Enabled\n Policy Value: N/A","discussion":"If the policy is enabled, the user will be asked where to save each file before downloading. If the policy is disabled, downloads will start immediately, and the user will not be asked where to save the file. If the policy is not configured, the user will be able to change this setting.","group_id_src":"V-221587"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-221588r1106670","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:15\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\DownloadRestrictions is set to 1, 2, 3, or 4)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\DownloadRestrictions'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBC-0055","rule_title":"Download restrictions must be configured.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.chrome:def:610055"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000169"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"If the system is on the SIPRNet, this requirement is Not Applicable.\n\nUniversal method:\n1. In the omnibox (address bar) type \"chrome:// policy\".\n2. If \"DownloadRestrictions\" is not displayed under the \"Policy Name\" column or it is set to \"0\", this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n1. Start \"regedit\".\n2. Navigate to \"HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\".\n3. If the \"DownloadRestrictions\" value name does not exist or its value data is set to \"0\", this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-221588r1106670_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000089","false_positives":"","uuid":"2369D495-6D7C-1014-B562-C7424F73F8DF","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4081","stig_uuid":"2366E687-6D7C-1014-938D-B7BE63F2C882","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-94635","V-79931"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-221588","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000089","id":"V-221588"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"If the system is on the SIPRNet, this requirement is Not Applicable.\n\nWindows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc.\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\\nPolicy Name: Allow download restrictions\nPolicy State: 1, 2, or 4\nPolicy Value: N/A","discussion":"Setting the policy means users cannot bypass download security decisions. There are many types of download warnings within Chrome, which roughly break down into these categories:\n- Malicious, as flagged by the Safe Browsing server.\n- Uncommon or unwanted, as flagged by the Safe Browsing server.\n- A dangerous file type (e.g., all SWF downloads and many EXE downloads).\n\nSetting the policy blocks different subsets of these, depending on its value:\n\n0 = No special restrictions. Default.\n1 = Block malicious downloads and dangerous file types.\n2 = Block malicious downloads, uncommon or unwanted downloads, and dangerous file types.\n3 = Block all downloads.\n4 = Block malicious downloads. Recommended.","group_id_src":"V-221588"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-221590r961083","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:15\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Check SafeBrowsingExtendedReportingEnabled value.)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\SafeBrowsingExtendedReportingEnabled'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBC-0057","rule_title":"Safe Browsing Extended Reporting must be disabled.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.chrome:def:660057"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-001166"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Universal method:\n 1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy\n 2. If \"SafeBrowsingExtendedReportingEnabled\" is not displayed under the \"Policy Name\" column or it is not set to \"False\", this is a finding.\nWindows method:\n 1. Start regedit\n 2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n 3. If the \"SafeBrowsingExtendedReportingEnabled\" value name does not exist or its value data is not set to \"0\", this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-221590r961083_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000206","false_positives":"","uuid":"2369DB11-6D7C-1014-A2D5-DA307868CB73","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4081","stig_uuid":"2366E687-6D7C-1014-938D-B7BE63F2C882","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-96299","V-81585"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-221590","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000206","id":"V-221590"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the âgroup policy editorâ tool with gpedit.msc\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\Safe Browsing settings\\\nPolicy Name: Enable Safe Browsing Extended Reporting\nPolicy State: Disabled\nPolicy Value: N/A","discussion":"Enables Google Chrome's Safe Browsing Extended Reporting and prevents users from changing this setting. Extended Reporting sends some system information and page content to Google servers to help detect dangerous apps and sites.\nIf the setting is set to \"True\", then reports will be created and sent whenever necessary (such as when a security interstitial is shown).\nIf the setting is set to \"False\", reports will never be sent.\nIf this policy is set to \"True\" or \"False\", the user will not be able to modify the setting.\nIf this policy is left unset, the user will be able to change the setting and decide whether to send reports or not.","group_id_src":"V-221590"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-221591r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:15\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (WebUSB must be disabled.)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\DefaultWebUsbGuardSetting'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBC-0058","rule_title":"WebUSB must be disabled.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.chrome:def:670058"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Universal method: \n 1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy\n 2. If \"DefaultWebUsbGuardSetting\" is not displayed under the \"Policy Name\" column or it is not set to \"2\", this is a finding.\nWindows method:\n 1. Start regedit\n 2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n 3. If the \"DefaultWebUsbGuardSetting\" value name does not exist or its value data is not set to \"2\", this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-221591r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"2369E2FD-6D7C-1014-B5DB-CEEF9394148C","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4081","stig_uuid":"2366E687-6D7C-1014-938D-B7BE63F2C882","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-96301","V-81587"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-221591","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-221591"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n 1. Open the âgroup policy editorâ tool with gpedit.msc\n 2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\Content Settings\n Policy Name: Control use of the WebUSB API\n Policy State: Enabled\n Policy Value: 2\n","discussion":"Allows you to set whether websites are allowed to get access to connected USB devices. Access can be completely blocked, or the user can be asked every time a website wants to get access to connected USB devices.\nIf this policy is left not set, â3â will be used, and the user will be able to change it.\n2 = Do not allow any site to request access to USB devices via the WebUSB API\n3 = Allow sites to ask the user to grant access to a connected USB device","group_id_src":"V-221591"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-221594r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:15\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Google Cast must be disabled.)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\EnableMediaRouter'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBC-0063","rule_title":"Google Cast must be disabled.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.chrome:def:520063"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Universal method: \n 1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy\n 2. If \"EnableMediaRouter\" is not displayed under the \"Policy Name\" column or it is not set to \"False\", this is a finding.\nWindows method:\n 1. Start regedit\n 2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n 3. If the \"EnableMediaRouter\" value name does not exist or its value data is not set to \"0\", this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-221594r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"2369EEE3-6D7C-1014-B3D7-A67DAF367D9A","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4081","stig_uuid":"2366E687-6D7C-1014-938D-B7BE63F2C882","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-96311","V-81597"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-221594","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-221594"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the âgroup policy editorâ tool with gpedit.msc\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\Google Cast\nPolicy Name: Enable Google Cast\nPolicy State: Disabled\nPolicy Value: N/A","discussion":"If this policy is set to âTrueâ or is not set, Google Cast will be enabled, and users will be able to launch it from the app menu, page context menus, media controls on Cast-enabled websites, and (if shown) the âCast toolbarâ icon.\nIf this policy set to âFalseâ, Google Cast will be disabled.","group_id_src":"V-221594"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-221595r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:15\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Autoplay is disabled)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\AutoplayAllowed'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBC-0064","rule_title":"Autoplay must be disabled.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.chrome:def:660055"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Universal method: \n 1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy\n 2. If \"AutoplayAllowed\" is not displayed under the \"Policy Name\" column or it is not set to \"False\", this is a finding.\nWindows method:\n 1. Start regedit\n 2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n 3. If the \"AutoplayAllowed\" value name does not exist or its value data is not set to \"0\", this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-221595r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"2369F83A-6D7C-1014-B92A-A2B9ACAB4020","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4081","stig_uuid":"2366E687-6D7C-1014-938D-B7BE63F2C882","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-96295","V-81581"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-221595","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-221595"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the âgroup policy editorâ tool with gpedit.msc\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\\nPolicy Name: Allow media autoplay\nPolicy State: Disabled\nPolicy Value: N/A","discussion":"This allows a user to control if videos can play automatically with audio content (without user consent) in Google Chrome.\n\nIf the policy is set to \"True\", Google Chrome is allowed to autoplay media. If the policy is set to \"False\", Google Chrome is not allowed to autoplay media. The \"AutoplayAllowlist\" policy can be used to override this for certain URL patterns. By default, Google Chrome is not allowed to autoplay media. The \"AutoplayAllowlist\" policy can be used to override this for certain URL patterns.","group_id_src":"V-221595"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-221596r961092","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:15\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT II, V-221596, SV-221596r961092, SRG-APP-000210)\n","rule_version":"DTBC-0065","rule_title":"URLs must be allowlisted for Autoplay use.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-ocil.xml","name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.chrome:questionnaire:5901"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Universal method:\n1. In the omnibox (address bar), type chrome://policy.\n2. If âAutoplayAllowlistâ under the âPolicy Nameâ column may be set to a list of administrator-approved URLs under the âPolicy Valueâ column. This requirement is optional.\n\nWindows method:\n1. Start regedit.\n2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n3. If the âAutoplayAllowlistâ key may contain a list of administrator-approved URLs. This requirement is optional.","rule_id_src":"SV-221596r961092_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","false_positives":"","uuid":"2369FED5-6D7C-1014-BE12-FF97A9F55421","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4081","stig_uuid":"2366E687-6D7C-1014-938D-B7BE63F2C882","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-96303","V-81589"],"status":"not_reviewed","group_id":"V-221596","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000210","id":"V-221596"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the âgroup policy editorâ tool with gpedit.msc.\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\n- Policy Name: Allow media autoplay on a allowlist of URL patterns.\n- Policy State: Enabled\n- Policy Value 1: [*.]mil\n- Policy Value 2: [*.]gov\n\nNote: Policy values are examples.","discussion":"Controls the allowlist of URL patterns that autoplay will always be enabled on. If the \"AutoplayAllowed\" policy is set to \"True\" then this policy will have no effect. If the \"AutoplayAllowed\" policy is set to \"False\", then any URL patterns set in this policy will still be allowed to play.","group_id_src":"V-221596"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-221597r961083","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:15\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Disable URL-keyed anonymized data collection)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\UrlKeyedAnonymizedDataCollectionEnabled'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBC-0066","rule_title":"Anonymized data collection must be disabled.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.chrome:def:690066"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-001166"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Universal method: \n1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy\n2. If \"UrlKeyedAnonymizedDataCollectionEnabled\" is not displayed under the âPolicy Nameâ column or it is not set to \"0\" under the âPolicy Valueâ column, this is a finding.\nWindows method:\n1. Start regedit\n2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n3. If the âUrlKeyedAnonymizedDataCollectionEnabled\" value name does not exist or its value data is not set to \"0,\" this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-221597r961083_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000206","false_positives":"","uuid":"236A04EE-6D7C-1014-B8A5-800F96D4EE1F","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4081","stig_uuid":"2366E687-6D7C-1014-938D-B7BE63F2C882","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-101303","V-91203"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-221597","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000206","id":"V-221597"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\\nPolicy Name: Enable URL-keyed anonymized data collection\nPolicy State: Disabled\nPolicy Value: NA","discussion":"Enable URL-keyed anonymized data collection in Google Chrome and prevent users from changing this setting.\nURL-keyed anonymized data collection sends URLs of pages the user visits to Google to make searches and browsing better.\nIf you enable this policy, URL-keyed anonymized data collection is always active.\nIf you disable this policy, URL-keyed anonymized data collection is never active.\nIf this policy is left not set, URL-keyed anonymized data collection will be enabled but the user will be able to change it.","group_id_src":"V-221597"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-221598r961083","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:15\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Disable WebRTC event log collection)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\WebRtcEventLogCollectionAllowed'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBC-0067","rule_title":"Collection of WebRTC event logs must be disabled.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.chrome:def:700067"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-001166"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Universal method:\n1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy\n2. If \"WebRtcEventLogCollectionAllowed\" is not displayed under the âPolicy Nameâ column or it is not set to \"0\" under the âPolicy Valueâ column, this is a finding.\nWindows method:\n1. Start regedit\n2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n3. If the \"WebRtcEventLogCollectionAllowed\" value name does not exist or its value data is not set to \"0,\" this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-221598r961083_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000206","false_positives":"","uuid":"236A0B28-6D7C-1014-9537-E85CBE9B5EE2","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4081","stig_uuid":"2366E687-6D7C-1014-938D-B7BE63F2C882","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-101305","V-91205"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-221598","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000206","id":"V-221598"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\\nPolicy Name: Allow collection of WebRTC event logs from Google services\nPolicy State: Disabled\nPolicy Value: NA","discussion":"If the policy is set to âtrueâ, Google Chrome is allowed to collect WebRTC event logs from Google services (e.g., Google Meet), and upload those logs to Google.\nIf the policy is set to âfalseâ, or is unset, Google Chrome may not collect nor upload such logs.\nThese logs contain diagnostic information helpful when debugging issues with audio or video calls in Chrome, such as the time and size of sent and received RTP packets, feedback about congestion on the network, and metadata about time and quality of audio and video frames. These logs do not contain audio or video contents from the call.\nThis data collection by Chrome can only be triggered by Google's web services, such as Google Hangouts or Google Meet.","group_id_src":"V-221598"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-221599r961167","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:15\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Chrome Developer Tools Availability must be disallowed.)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\DeveloperToolsAvailability'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBC-0068","rule_title":"Chrome development tools must be disabled.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.chrome:def:680062"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-001312"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Universal method: \n1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy \n2. If the policy \"DeveloperToolsAvailability\" is not shown or is not set to \"2\", this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n1. Start regedit\n2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n3. If the key \"DeveloperToolsAvailability\" does not exist or is not set to \"2\", this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-221599r961167_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000266","false_positives":"","uuid":"236A1155-6D7C-1014-A20F-D1B119050DB4","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4081","stig_uuid":"2366E687-6D7C-1014-938D-B7BE63F2C882","severity":"low","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-106629","V-97525"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-221599","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000266","id":"V-221599"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the \"group policy editor\" tool with gpedit.msc \n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\nPolicy Name: Control where Developer Tools can be used\nPolicy State: Enabled\nPolicy Value: Disallow usage of the Developer Tools","discussion":"While the risk associated with browser development tools is more related to the proper design of a web application, a risk vector remains within the browser. The developer tools allow end users and application developers to view and edit all types of web application related data via the browser. Page elements, source code, javascript, API calls, application data, etc. may all be viewed and potentially manipulated. Manipulation could be useful for troubleshooting legitimate issues, and this may be performed in a development environment. Manipulation could also be malicious and must be addressed.","group_id_src":"V-221599"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-226401r961083","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:15\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Disable Browser Guest Mode)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\BrowserGuestModeEnabled'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBC-0069","rule_title":"Guest Mode must be disabled.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.chrome:def:240069"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-001166"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Universal method: \n1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy \n2. If BrowserGuestModeEnabled is not displayed under the Policy Name column or it is not set to 0 under the Policy Value column, this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n1. Start regedit\n2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n3. If the BrowserGuestModeEnabled value name does not exist or its value data is not set to 0, this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-226401r961083_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000206","false_positives":"","uuid":"236A1A98-6D7C-1014-BD8A-907382941FE6","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4081","stig_uuid":"2366E687-6D7C-1014-938D-B7BE63F2C882","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-111829","V-102867"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-226401","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000206","id":"V-226401"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the \"group policy editor\" tool with gpedit.msc \n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\\nPolicy Name: Enable guest mode in browser\nPolicy State: Disabled","discussion":"If this policy is set to true or not configured, Google Chrome will enable guest logins. Guest logins are Google Chrome profiles where all windows are in incognito mode.\n\nIf this policy is set to false, Google Chrome will not allow guest profiles to be started.","group_id_src":"V-226401"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-226402r961083","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:15\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Disable auto filling of credit card information)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\AutofillCreditCardEnabled'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBC-0070","rule_title":"AutoFill for credit cards must be disabled.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.chrome:def:240070"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-001166"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Universal method: \n1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy \n2. If AutofillCreditCardEnabled is not displayed under the Policy Name column or it is not set to 0 under the Policy Value column, this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n1. Start regedit\n2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n3. If the AutofillCreditCardEnabled value name does not exist or its value data is not set to 0, this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-226402r961083_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000206","false_positives":"","uuid":"236A208D-6D7C-1014-A7FE-FBED3A80B054","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4081","stig_uuid":"2366E687-6D7C-1014-938D-B7BE63F2C882","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-111831","V-102869"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-226402","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000206","id":"V-226402"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the \"group policy editor\" tool with gpedit.msc \n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\\nPolicy Name: Enable AutoFill for credit cards\nPolicy State: Disabled","discussion":"Enabling Google Chrome's AutoFill feature allows users to auto complete credit card information in web forms using previously stored information.\nIf this setting is disabled, Autofill will never suggest or fill credit card information, nor will it save additional credit card information that the user might submit while browsing the web.\n\nIf this setting is enabled or has no value, the user will be able to control Autofill for credit cards in the UI.","group_id_src":"V-226402"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-226403r961083","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:15\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Disable AutoFill for addresses)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\AutofillAddressEnabled'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBC-0071","rule_title":"AutoFill for addresses must be disabled.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.chrome:def:240071"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-001166"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Universal method: \n1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy \n2. If AutofillAddressEnabled is not displayed under the Policy Name column or it is not set to 0 under the Policy Value column, this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n1. Start regedit\n2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n3. If the AutofillAddressEnabled value name does not exist or its value data is not set to 0, this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-226403r961083_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000206","false_positives":"","uuid":"236A265B-6D7C-1014-A928-C68823FBD0A5","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4081","stig_uuid":"2366E687-6D7C-1014-938D-B7BE63F2C882","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-111833","V-102871"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-226403","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000206","id":"V-226403"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the \"group policy editor\" tool with gpedit.msc \n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\\nPolicy Name: Enable AutoFill for addresses\nPolicy State: Disabled","discussion":"Enabling Google Chrome's AutoFill feature allows users to auto complete address information in web forms using previously stored information.\nIf this setting is disabled, Autofill will never suggest or fill address information, nor will it save additional address information that the user might submit while browsing the web.\n\nIf this setting is enabled or has no value, the user will be able to control Autofill for addresses in the UI.","group_id_src":"V-226403"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-226404r961083","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:15\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Disable Browser Guest Mode)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\ImportAutofillFormData'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBC-0072","rule_title":"Import AutoFill form data must be disabled.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.chrome:def:240072"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-001166"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Universal method: \n1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy \n2. If ImportAutofillFormData is not displayed under the Policy Name column or it is not set to 0 under the Policy Value column, this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n1. Start regedit\n2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n3. If the ImportAutofillFormData value name does not exist or its value data is not set to 0, this is a finding.\n","rule_id_src":"SV-226404r961083_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000206","false_positives":"","uuid":"236A2C27-6D7C-1014-BE8E-F70FEF23F0BF","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4081","stig_uuid":"2366E687-6D7C-1014-938D-B7BE63F2C882","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-111835","V-102873"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-226404","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000206","id":"V-226404"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the \"group policy editor\" tool with gpedit.msc \n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\\nPolicy Name: Import autofill form data from default browser on first run\nPolicy State: Disabled","discussion":"This policy forces the autofill form data to be imported from the previous default browser if enabled. If enabled, this policy also affects the import dialog.\nIf disabled, the autofill form data is not imported.\n\nIf it is not set, the user may be asked whether to import, or importing may happen automatically.","group_id_src":"V-226404"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-241787r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:15\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Web Bluetooth API must be disabled.)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\DefaultWebBluetoothGuardSetting'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBC-0073","rule_title":"Web Bluetooth API must be disabled.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.chrome:def:241787"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Universal method: \n1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy \n2. If DefaultWebBluetoothGuardSetting is not displayed under the Policy Name column or it is not set to 2 under the Policy Value column, then this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n 1. Start regedit\n 2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n 3. If the DefaultWebBluetoothGuardSetting value name does not exist or its value data is not set to 2, then this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-241787r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"236A3215-6D7C-1014-A45F-A9E58CF43C91","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4081","stig_uuid":"2366E687-6D7C-1014-938D-B7BE63F2C882","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-34246","V-26961"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-241787","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-241787"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the âgroup policy editorâ tool with gpedit.msc\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\Content Settings\n Policy Name: Control use of the Web Bluetooth API\n Policy State: Enabled\n Policy Value: Do not allow any site to request access to Bluetooth devices via the Web Bluetooth API","discussion":"Setting the policy to 3 lets websites ask for access to nearby Bluetooth devices. Setting the policy to 2 denies access to nearby Bluetooth devices.\n\nLeaving the policy unset lets sites ask for access, but users can change this setting.\n\n2 = Do not allow any site to request access to Bluetooth devices via the Web Bluetooth API\n3 = Allow sites to ask the user to grant access to a nearby Bluetooth device","group_id_src":"V-241787"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-245538r961470","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:15\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Use of the QUIC protocol is disabled)\n","rule_version":"DTBC-0074","rule_title":"Use of the QUIC protocol must be disabled.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.chrome:def:138"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-001762"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Universal method: \n1. In the omnibox (address bar), type chrome://policy.\n2. If QuicAllowed is not displayed under the Policy Name column or it is not set to False under the Policy Value column, this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n1. Start regedit.\n2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\.\n3. If the QuicAllowed value name does not exist or its value data is not set to 0, this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-245538r961470_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000383","false_positives":"","uuid":"236A37C0-6D7C-1014-AED3-E82DADE1453F","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4081","stig_uuid":"2366E687-6D7C-1014-938D-B7BE63F2C882","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_id":"V-245538","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000383","id":"V-245538"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the âgroup policy editorâ tool with gpedit.msc.\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google Chrome.\n- Policy Name: Allow QUIC protocol\n- Policy State: Disabled\n- Policy Value: N/A","discussion":"QUIC is used by more than half of all connections from the Chrome web browser to Google's servers, and this activity is undesirable in the DoD.\n\nSetting the policy to Enabled or leaving it unset allows the use of QUIC protocol in Google Chrome.\n\nSetting the policy to Disabled disallows the use of QUIC protocol.","group_id_src":"V-245538"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-245539r960864","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:15\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Session only based cookies are enabled)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\DefaultCookiesSetting'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBC-0045","rule_title":"Session only based cookies must be enabled.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.chrome:def:240045"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000166"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Universal method: \n1. In the omnibox (address bar), type chrome://policy\n2. If the policy \"DefaultCookiesSetting\" is not shown or is not set to \"4\", this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n1. Start regedit.\n2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\DefaultCookiesSetting.\n3. If this key does not exist, or is not set to \"4\", this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-245539r960864_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000080","false_positives":"","uuid":"236A3D39-6D7C-1014-91F0-B8164FCB6A68","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4081","stig_uuid":"2366E687-6D7C-1014-938D-B7BE63F2C882","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_id":"V-245539","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000080","id":"V-245539"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc \n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\Content Settings.\n- Policy Name: Default cookies setting\n- Policy State: Enabled\n- Policy Value: Keep cookies for the duration of the session","discussion":"Cookies must only be allowed per session and only for approved URLs as permanently stored cookies can be used for malicious intent. \n\nApproved URLs may be allowlisted via the CookiesAllowedForUrls policy setting, but is not a requirement.","group_id_src":"V-245539"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-275780r1106603","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:15\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Create Themes with AI must be disabled.)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\CreateThemesSettings'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBC-0075","rule_title":"Create Themes with AI must be disabled.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.chrome:def:275780"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000169"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Universal method:\n1. In the omnibox (address bar) type \"chrome:// policy\".\n2. If \"CreateThemesSettings\" is not displayed under the \"Policy Name\" column or it is not set to \"2\" under the \"Policy Value\" column, this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n1. Start \"regedit\".\n2. Navigate to \"HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\".\n3. If the \"CreateThemesSettings\" value name does not exist or its value data is not set to \"2\", this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-275780r1106603_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000089","false_positives":"","uuid":"236A4378-6D7C-1014-BE9E-F25A95C8DB4D","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4081","stig_uuid":"2366E687-6D7C-1014-938D-B7BE63F2C882","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_id":"V-275780","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000089","id":"V-275780"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc.\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\Generative AI\nPolicy Name: Settings for Create Themes with AI\nPolicy State: Enabled\nPolicy Value: Do not allow Create Themes","discussion":"Create Themes with AI lets users create custom themes/wallpapers by preselecting from a list of options.\n\n0 = Allow the feature to be used, while allowing Google to use relevant data to improve its AI models. Relevant data may include prompts, inputs, outputs, source materials, and written feedback, depending on the feature. It may also be reviewed by humans to improve AI models. 0 is the default value, except when noted below.\n\n1 = Allow the feature to be used, but does not allow Google to improve models using users' content (including prompts, inputs, outputs, source materials, and written feedback). 1 is the default value for Enterprise users managed by Google Admin console and for Education accounts managed by Google Workspace.\n\n2 = Do not allow the feature.","group_id_src":"V-275780"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-275781r1106671","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:15\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (DevTools Generative AI features must be disabled.)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\DevToolsGenAiSettings'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBC-0076","rule_title":"DevTools Generative AI features must be disabled.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.chrome:def:275781"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000169"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Universal method:\n1. In the omnibox (address bar) type \"chrome:// policy\".\n2. If \"DevToolsGenAiSettings\" is not displayed under the \"Policy Name\" column or it is not set to \"2\" under the \"Policy Value\" column, this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n1. Start \"regedit\".\n2. Navigate to \"HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\".\n3. If the \"DevToolsGenAiSettings\" value name does not exist or its value data is not set to \"2\", this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-275781r1106671_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000089","false_positives":"","uuid":"236A497F-6D7C-1014-9E33-AFFC2017D73E","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4081","stig_uuid":"2366E687-6D7C-1014-938D-B7BE63F2C882","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_id":"V-275781","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000089","id":"V-275781"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc.\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\Generative AI\nPolicy Name: Settings for DevTools Generative AI Features\nPolicy State: Enabled\nPolicy Value: Do not allow DevTools Generative AI Features","discussion":"These features in Google Chrome's DevTools employ generative AI models to provide additional debugging information. To use these features, Google Chrome collects data such as error messages, stack traces, code snippets, and network requests and sends them to a server owned by Google, which runs a generative AI model. Response body or authentication and cookie headers in network requests are not included in the data sent to the server.\n\n0 = Allow the feature to be used, while allowing Google to use relevant data to improve its AI models. Relevant data may include prompts, inputs, outputs, source materials, and written feedback, depending on the feature. It may also be reviewed by humans to improve AI models. 0 is the default value, except when noted below.\n\n1 = Allow the feature to be used, but does not allow Google to improve models using users' content (including prompts, inputs, outputs, source materials, and written feedback). 1 is the default value for Enterprise users managed by Google Admin console and for Education accounts managed by Google Workspace.\n\n2 = Do not allow the feature.","group_id_src":"V-275781"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-275782r1106672","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:15\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (GenAI local foundational model must be disabled.)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\GenAILocalFoundationalModelSettings'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBC-0077","rule_title":"GenAI local foundational model must be disabled.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.chrome:def:275782"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000169"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Universal method:\n1. In the omnibox (address bar) type \"chrome:// policy\".\n2. If \"GenAILocalFoundationalModelSettings\" is not displayed under the \"Policy Name\" column or it is not set to \"1\" under the \"Policy Value\" column, this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n1. Start \"regedit\".\n2. Navigate to \"HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\".\n3. If the \"GenAILocalFoundationalModelSettings\" value name does not exist or its value data is not set to \"1\", this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-275782r1106672_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000089","false_positives":"","uuid":"236A5045-6D7C-1014-978B-9E4FE2B846C3","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4081","stig_uuid":"2366E687-6D7C-1014-938D-B7BE63F2C882","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_id":"V-275782","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000089","id":"V-275782"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc.\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\Generative AI\nPolicy Name: Settings for GenAI local foundational model\nPolicy State: Enabled\nPolicy Value: Do not download model","discussion":"Configure how Google Chrome downloads the foundational GenAI model and uses it for inference locally.\n\nWhen the policy is set to Allowed (0) or not set, the model is downloaded automatically, and used for inference.\n\nWhen the policy is set to Disabled (1), the model will not be downloaded.\n\nModel downloading can also be disabled by ComponentUpdatesEnabled.\n\n0 = Downloads model automatically\n1 = Do not download model","group_id_src":"V-275782"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-275783r1106612","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:15\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Help Me Write must be disabled.)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\HelpMeWriteSettings'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBC-0078","rule_title":"Help Me Write must be disabled.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.chrome:def:275783"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000169"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Universal method:\n1. In the omnibox (address bar) type \"chrome:// policy\".\n2. If \"HelpMeWriteSettings\" is not displayed under the \"Policy Name\" column or it is not set to \"2\" under the \"Policy Value\" column, this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n1. Start \"regedit\".\n2. Navigate to \"HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\".\n3. If the \"HelpMeWriteSettings\" value name does not exist or its value data is not set to \"2\", this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-275783r1106612_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000089","false_positives":"","uuid":"236A55C1-6D7C-1014-886C-E25CCF6000B0","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4081","stig_uuid":"2366E687-6D7C-1014-938D-B7BE63F2C882","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_id":"V-275783","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000089","id":"V-275783"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc.\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\Generative AI\nPolicy Name: Settings forSettings for Help Me Write\nPolicy State: Enabled\nPolicy Value: Do not allow Help Me Write","discussion":"Help Me Write is an AI-based writing assistant for short-form content on the web. Suggested content is based on prompts entered by the user and the content of the web page.\n\n0 = Allow the feature to be used, while allowing Google to use relevant data to improve its AI models. Relevant data may include prompts, inputs, outputs, source materials, and written feedback, depending on the feature. It may also be reviewed by humans to improve AI models. 0 is the default value, except when noted below.\n\n1 = Allow the feature to be used, but does not allow Google to improve models using users' content (including prompts, inputs, outputs, source materials, and written feedback). 1 is the default value for Enterprise users managed by Google Admin console and for Education accounts managed by Google Workspace.\n\n2 = Do not allow the feature.","group_id_src":"V-275783"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-275784r1106615","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:15\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (AI-powered History Search must be disabled)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\HistorySearchSettings'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBC-0079","rule_title":"AI-powered History Search must be disabled.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.chrome:def:275784"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000169"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Universal method:\n1. In the omnibox (address bar) type \"chrome:// policy\".\n2. If \"HistorySearchSettings\" is not displayed under the \"Policy Name\" column or it is not set to \"2\" under the \"Policy Value\" column, this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n1. Start \"regedit\".\n2. Navigate to \"HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\".\n3. If the \"HistorySearchSettings\" value name does not exist or its value data is not set to \"2\", this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-275784r1106615_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000089","false_positives":"","uuid":"236A5B4B-6D7C-1014-AF7D-F526CAF3AC09","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4081","stig_uuid":"2366E687-6D7C-1014-938D-B7BE63F2C882","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_id":"V-275784","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000089","id":"V-275784"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc.\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\Generative AI\nPolicy Name: Settings for AI-powered History Search\nPolicy State: Enabled\nPolicy Value: Do not allow AI History Search","discussion":"AI History Search is a feature that allows users to search their browsing history and receive generated answers based on page contents and not just the page title and URL.\n\n0 = Allow the feature to be used, while allowing Google to use relevant data to improve its AI models. Relevant data may include prompts, inputs, outputs, source materials, and written feedback, depending on the feature. It may also be reviewed by humans to improve AI models. 0 is the default value, except when noted below.\n\n1 = Allow the feature to be used, but does not allow Google to improve models using users' content (including prompts, inputs, outputs, source materials, and written feedback). 1 is the default value for Enterprise users managed by Google Admin console and for Education accounts managed by Google Workspace.\n\n2 = Do not allow the feature.","group_id_src":"V-275784"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-275785r1106673","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:15\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Tab Compare Settings must be disabled.)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\TabCompareSettings'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBC-0080","rule_title":"Tab Compare Settings must be disabled.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.chrome:def:275785"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000169"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Universal method:\n1. In the omnibox (address bar) type \"chrome:// policy\".\n2. If \"TabCompareSettings\" is not displayed under the \"Policy Name\" column or it is not set to \"2\" under the \"Policy Value\" column, this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n1. Start \"regedit\".\n2. Navigate to \"HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\".\n3. If the \"TabCompareSettings\" value name does not exist or its value data is not set to \"2\", this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-275785r1106673_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000089","false_positives":"","uuid":"236A60C2-6D7C-1014-9BDF-8EFD027C8E2A","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4081","stig_uuid":"2366E687-6D7C-1014-938D-B7BE63F2C882","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_id":"V-275785","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000089","id":"V-275785"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc.\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\Generative AI\nPolicy Name: Tab Compare settings\nPolicy State: Enabled\nPolicy Value: Do not allow Tab Compare","discussion":"Tab Compare is an AI-powered tool for comparing information across a user's tabs. For example, the feature can be offered to the user when multiple tabs with products in a similar category are open.\n\n0 = Allow the feature to be used, while allowing Google to use relevant data to improve its AI models. Relevant data may include prompts, inputs, outputs, source materials, and written feedback, depending on the feature. It may also be reviewed by humans to improve AI models. 0 is the default value, except when noted below.\n\n1 = Allow the feature to be used, but does not allow Google to improve models using users' content (including prompts, inputs, outputs, source materials, and written feedback). 1 is the default value for Enterprise users managed by Google Admin console and for Education accounts managed by Google Workspace.\n\n2 = Do not allow the feature.","group_id_src":"V-275785"}],"display_name":"Google Chrome Current Windows","release_info":"Release: 11 Benchmark Date: 02 Jul 2025"},{"uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","stig_name":"Microsoft Internet Explorer 11 Security Technical Implementation Guide","version":"2","size":137,"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_id":"IE_11_STIG","rules":[{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223015r961863","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Windows Components/Internet Explorer/Internet Control Panel/Security Page/Turn on certificate address mismatch warning)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\WarnOnBadCertRecving'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI015-IE11","rule_title":"The Internet Explorer warning about certificate address mismatch must be enforced.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:421"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page 'Turn on certificate address mismatch warning' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings Criteria: If the value \"WarnOnBadCertRecving\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223015r961863_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B381082-6D7C-1014-A4AE-AC06E694C3F0","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59339","V-46475"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223015","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000516","id":"V-223015"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page 'Turn on certificate address mismatch warning' to 'Enabled'.  ","discussion":"This parameter warns users if the certificate being presented by the website is invalid. Since server certificates are used to validate the identity of the web server it is critical to warn the user of a potential issue with the certificate being presented by the web server. This setting aids to prevent spoofing attacks.","group_id_src":"V-223015"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223016r961038","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Check for publishers certificate revocation must be enforced.)\n","rule_version":"DTBI018-IE11","rule_title":"Check for publishers certificate revocation must be enforced.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.ie:def:223016"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000185"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"If the system is on the SIPRNet, this requirement is NA.\n\nOpen Internet Explorer.\nFrom the menu bar, select \"Tools\".\nFrom the \"Tools\" drop-down menu, select \"Internet Options\". From the \"Internet Options\" window, select the \"Advanced\" tab, from the \"Advanced\" tab window, scroll down to the \"Security\" category, and verify the \"Check for publisher's certificate revocation\" box is selected.\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n HKCU\\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\WinTrust\\Trust Providers\\Software Publishing Criteria\n\nIf the value \"State\" is \"REG_DWORD = 23C00\", this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223016r961038_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000175","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B381965-6D7C-1014-A868-B50E87B4797F","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"low","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59341","V-46477"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_id":"V-223016","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000175","id":"V-223016"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"If the system is on the SIPRNet, this requirement is NA.\n\nOpen Internet Explorer.\nFrom the menu bar, select \"Tools\".\nFrom the \"Tools\" drop-down menu, select \"Internet Options\". From the \"Internet Options\" window, select the \"Advanced\" tab from the \"Advanced\" tab window, scroll down to the \"Security\" category, and select the \"Check for publisher's certificate revocation\" box.\n\nNote: Manual entry in the registry key:\n\nHKCU\\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Current Version\\WinTrust\\Trust Providers\\Software Publishing for the value \"State\", set to \"REG_DWORD = 23C00\", may first be required.","discussion":"Check for publisher's certificate revocation options should be enforced to ensure all PKI signed objects are validated.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-APP-000605","group_id_src":"V-223016"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223017r961089","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Download signed ActiveX controls)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3\\1001'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI022-IE11","rule_title":"The Download signed ActiveX controls property must be disallowed (Internet zone).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:422"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-001169"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Download signed ActiveX controls' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box.  Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"1001\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223017r961089_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000209","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B381FE3-6D7C-1014-8836-FB8DDCACAC69","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59345","V-46481"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223017","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000209","id":"V-223017"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Download signed ActiveX controls' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","discussion":"Active X controls can contain potentially malicious code and must only be allowed to be downloaded from trusted sites. Signed code is better than unsigned code in that it may be easier to determine its author, but it is still potentially harmful, especially when coming from an untrusted zone. This policy setting allows you to manage whether users may download signed ActiveX controls from a page in the zone. If you enable this policy, users can download signed controls without user intervention. If you select Prompt in the drop-down box, users are queried whether to download controls signed by untrusted publishers. Code signed by trusted publishers is silently downloaded. If you disable the policy setting, signed controls cannot be downloaded.","group_id_src":"V-223017"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223018r961089","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Download unsigned ActiveX controls)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3\\1004'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI023-IE11","rule_title":"The Download unsigned ActiveX controls property must be disallowed (Internet zone).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:423"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-001169"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Download unsigned ActiveX controls' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"1004\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223018r961089_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000209","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B382638-6D7C-1014-BB0A-BC727D1A30EE","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59347","V-46483"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223018","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000209","id":"V-223018"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Download unsigned ActiveX controls' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box. ","discussion":"Unsigned code is potentially harmful, especially when coming from an untrusted zone. This policy setting allows you to manage whether users may download unsigned ActiveX controls from the zone. If you enable this policy setting, users can run unsigned controls without user intervention. If you select \"Prompt\" in the drop-down box, users are queried to choose whether to allow the unsigned control to run. If you disable this policy setting, users cannot run unsigned controls. If you do not configure this policy setting, users cannot run unsigned controls.","group_id_src":"V-223018"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223019r961092","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Initialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safe)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3\\1201'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI024-IE11","rule_title":"The Initialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safe property must be disallowed (Internet zone).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:424"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Initialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safe' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"1201\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223019r961092_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B382D7A-6D7C-1014-B243-D1F5E716F018","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59365","V-46501"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223019","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000210","id":"V-223019"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Initialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safe' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","discussion":"ActiveX controls that are not marked safe for scripting should not be executed. Although this is not a complete security measure for a control to be marked safe for scripting, if a control is not marked safe, it should not be initialized and executed. This setting causes both unsafe and safe controls to be initialized and scripted, ignoring the Script ActiveX controls marked safe for scripting option. This increases the risk of malicious code being loaded and executed by the browser. If you enable this policy setting, ActiveX controls are run, loaded with parameters and scripted without setting object safety for untrusted data or scripts. If you disable this policy setting, ActiveX controls that cannot be made safe are not loaded with parameters or scripted. This setting is not recommended, except for secure and administered zones.","group_id_src":"V-223019"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223020r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Java permissions)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3\\1C00'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI031-IE11","rule_title":"The Java permissions must be disallowed (Internet zone).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:426"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Java permissions' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable Java' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"1C00\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223020r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B3832D8-6D7C-1014-8A2F-EE62F91E2B78","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59371","V-46507"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223020","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223020"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Java permissions' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable Java' from the drop-down box.  ","discussion":"Java applications could contain malicious code; sites located in this security zone are more likely to be hosted by malicious individuals. This policy setting allows you to manage permissions for Java applets. If you enable this policy setting, options can be chosen from the drop-down box. Use of the Custom permission will control permissions settings individually. Use of the Low Safety permission enables applets to perform all operations. Use of the Medium Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox (an area in memory outside of which the program cannot make calls), plus adds capabilities like scratch space (a safe and secure storage area on the client computer) and a user-controlled file I/O. Use of the High Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox. If you disable this policy setting, Java applets cannot run. If you do not configure this policy setting, the permission is set to High Safety.","group_id_src":"V-223020"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223021r1117169","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Access data sources across domains)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3\\1406'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI032-IE11","rule_title":"Accessing data sources across domains must be disallowed (Internet zone).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:427"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-001414"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Access data sources across domains' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"1406\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223021r1117169_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000039","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B383880-6D7C-1014-8399-D317A09CAECC","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59373","V-46509"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223021","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000039","id":"V-223021"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Access data sources across domains' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","discussion":"The ability to access data zones across domains could cause the user to unknowingly access content hosted on an unauthorized server. Access to data sources across multiple domains must be controlled based upon the site being browsed. This policy setting allows you to manage whether Internet Explorer can access data from another security zone using the Microsoft XML Parser (MSXML) or ActiveX Data Objects (ADO).","group_id_src":"V-223021"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223022r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Allow drag and drop or copy and paste files)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3\\1802'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI036-IE11","rule_title":"Functionality to drag and drop or copy and paste files must be disallowed (Internet zone).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:428"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Allow drag and drop or copy and paste files' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value for \"1802\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223022r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B383EA0-6D7C-1014-A5FD-A63DD60048C0","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59375","V-46511"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223022","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223022"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Allow drag and drop or copy and paste files' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","discussion":"Content hosted on sites located in the Internet zone are likely to contain malicious payloads and therefore this feature should be blocked for this zone. Drag and drop or copy and paste files must have a level of protection based upon the site being accessed.","group_id_src":"V-223022"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223023r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Launching applications and files in an IFRAME)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3\\1804'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI038-IE11","rule_title":"Launching programs and files in IFRAME must be disallowed (Internet zone).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:429"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Launching applications and files in an IFRAME' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"1804\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223023r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B38446C-6D7C-1014-9C58-DDBC7128BB9C","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59377","V-46513"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223023","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223023"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Launching applications and files in an IFRAME' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.  ","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether applications may be run and files may be downloaded from an IFRAME reference in the HTML of the pages in this zone. Launching of programs in IFRAME must have a level of protection based upon the site being accessed. If you enable this policy setting, applications can run and files can be downloaded from IFRAMEs on the pages in this zone without user intervention. If you disable this setting, users are prevented from running applications and downloading files from IFRAMEs on the pages in this zone.","group_id_src":"V-223023"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223024r1117169","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Navigate windows and frames across different domains)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3\\1607'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI039-IE11","rule_title":"Navigating windows and frames across different domains must be disallowed (Internet zone).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:430"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-001414"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Navigate windows and frames across different domains' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\InternetSettings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"1607\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223024r1117169_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000039","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B3849CC-6D7C-1014-8467-D56BB24035B1","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59379","V-46515"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223024","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000039","id":"V-223024"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Navigate windows and frames across different domains' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","discussion":"Frames that navigate across different domains are a security concern, because the user may think they are accessing pages on one site while they are actually accessing pages on another site. It is possible that a website hosting malicious content could use this feature in a manner similar to cross-site scripting (XSS). This policy setting allows you to manage the opening of sub-frames and access of applications across different domains.","group_id_src":"V-223024"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223025r961128","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Userdata persistence)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3\\1606'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI042-IE11","rule_title":"Userdata persistence must be disallowed (Internet zone).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:431"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-001199"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Userdata persistence' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"1606\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223025r961128_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000231","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B384F57-6D7C-1014-BFC7-91CE9D86C81E","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59381","V-46517"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223025","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000231","id":"V-223025"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Userdata persistence' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","discussion":"Userdata persistence must have a level of protection based upon the site being accessed. It is possible for sites hosting malicious content to exploit this feature as part of an attack against visitors browsing the site. This policy setting allows you to manage the preservation of information in the browser's history, in Favorites, in an XML store, or directly within a web page saved to disk. When a user returns to a persisted page, the state of the page can be restored if this policy setting is not appropriately configured. ","group_id_src":"V-223025"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223026r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Allow cut, copy, or paste operations from the clipboard via script)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3\\1407'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI044-IE11","rule_title":"Clipboard operations via script must be disallowed (Internet zone).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:432"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Allow cut, copy or paste operations from the clipboard via script' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"1407\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223026r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B385482-6D7C-1014-B42C-931FB740FD80","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59385","V-46521"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223026","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223026"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Allow cut, copy or paste operations from the clipboard via script' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","discussion":"A malicious script could use the clipboard in an undesirable manner, for example, if the user had recently copied confidential information to the clipboard while editing a document, a malicious script could harvest that information. It might be possible to exploit other vulnerabilities in order to send the harvested data to the attacker. Allow paste operations via script must have a level of protection based upon the site being accessed.","group_id_src":"V-223026"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223027r1043178","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Logon options)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3\\1A00'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI046-IE11","rule_title":"Logon options must be configured to prompt (Internet zone).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:433"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-001184"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Logon options' must be 'Enabled', and 'Prompt for user name and password' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"1A00\" is REG_DWORD = 65536 (decimal), this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223027r1043178_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000219","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B385A1B-6D7C-1014-9FE0-F56D3408B0BC","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59387","V-46523"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223027","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000219","id":"V-223027"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Logon options' to 'Enabled', and select 'Prompt for user name and password' from the drop-down box.  ","discussion":"Users could submit credentials to servers operated by malicious individuals who could then attempt to connect to legitimate servers with those captured credentials. Care must be taken with user credentials, automatic logon performance, and how default Windows credentials are passed to the websites. This policy setting allows management of settings for logon options. If you enable this policy setting, you can choose from varying logon options. âAnonymous logonâ disables HTTP authentication and uses the guest account only for the Common Internet File System (CIFS) protocol. âPrompt for user name and passwordâ queries users for user IDs and passwords. After a user is queried, these values can be used silently for the remainder of the session. âAutomatic logon only in Intranet zoneâ queries users for user IDs and passwords in other zones. After a user is queried, these values can be used silently for the remainder of the session. âAutomatic logon with current user name and passwordâ attempts logon using Windows NT Challenge Response. If Windows NT Challenge Response is supported by the server, the logon uses the user's network user name and password for login. If Windows NT Challenge Response is not supported by the server, the user is queried to provide the user name and password. If you disable this policy setting, logon is set to âAutomatic logon only in Intranet zoneâ. If you do not configure this policy setting, logon is set to âAutomatic logon only in Intranet zoneâ. The most secure option is to configure this setting to âEnabledâ; âAnonymous logonâ, but configuring this setting to âEnabledâ; âPrompt for user name and passwordâ, provides a reasonable balance between security and usability.","group_id_src":"V-223027"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223028r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Intranet Zone\\Java permissions)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\1\\1C00'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI061-IE11","rule_title":"Java permissions must be configured with High Safety (Intranet zone).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:434"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Intranet Zone -&gt; 'Java permissions' must be 'Enabled', and 'High Safety' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\1 Criteria: If the value \"1C00\" is REG_DWORD = 65536, (Decimal), this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223028r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B385F5F-6D7C-1014-8CCC-B0F5A0018F0C","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59389","V-46525"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223028","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223028"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Intranet Zone -&gt; 'Java permissions' to 'Enabled', and select 'High Safety' from the drop-down box.   ","discussion":"Java applications could contain malicious code. This policy setting allows you to manage permissions for Java applets. If you enable this policy setting, options can be chosen from the drop-down box. Use of the Custom permission will control permissions settings individually. Use of the Low Safety permission enables applets to perform all operations. Use of the Medium Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox (an area in memory outside of which the program cannot make calls), plus adds capabilities like scratch space (a safe and secure storage area on the client computer) and a user-controlled file I/O. Use of the High Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox. If you disable this policy setting, Java applets cannot run. If you do not configure this policy setting, the permission is set to High Safety.","group_id_src":"V-223028"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223029r961086","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Intranet Zone Don't run antimalware programs against ActiveX controls)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\1\\270C'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI062-IE11","rule_title":"Anti-Malware programs against ActiveX controls must be run for the Intranet zone.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:566"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-001662"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer-&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Intranet Zone 'Don't run antimalware programs against ActiveX controls' must be 'Enabled' and 'Disable' selected in the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\1  Criteria: If the value \"270C\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223029r961086_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000207","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B386488-6D7C-1014-95E0-B22A4741FFD2","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59865","V-46999"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223029","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000207","id":"V-223029"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer-&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Intranet Zone 'Don't run antimalware programs against ActiveX controls' to 'Enabled' and select 'Disable' in the drop-down box.   ","discussion":"This policy setting determines whether Internet Explorer runs Anti-Malware programs against ActiveX controls, to check if they're safe to load on pages.      If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer won't check with your Anti-Malware program to see if it's safe to create an instance of the ActiveX control. If you disable this policy setting, Internet Explorer always checks with your Anti-Malware program to see if it's safe to create an instance of the ActiveX control. If you don't configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer won't check with your Anti-Malware program to see if it's safe to create an instance of the ActiveX control. Users can turn this behavior on or off, using Internet Explorer Security settings.","group_id_src":"V-223029"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223030r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Trusted Sites Zone\\Java permissions)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\2\\1C00'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI091-IE11","rule_title":"Java permissions must be configured with High Safety (Trusted Sites zone).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:435"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Trusted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Java permissions' must be 'Enabled', and 'High Safety' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\2 Criteria: If the value \"1C00\" is REG_DWORD = 65536, (Decimal), this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223030r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B3869D5-6D7C-1014-AB45-C2A5BD030225","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59407","V-46543"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223030","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223030"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Trusted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Java permissions' to 'Enabled', and select 'High Safety' from the drop-down box.","discussion":"Java applications could contain malicious code. This policy setting allows you to manage permissions for Java applets. If you enable this policy setting, options can be chosen from the drop-down box. Use of the Custom permission will control permissions settings individually. Use of the Low Safety permission enables applets to perform all operations. Use of the Medium Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox (an area in memory outside of which the program cannot make calls), plus adds capabilities like scratch space (a safe and secure storage area on the client computer) and a user-controlled file I/O. Use of the High Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox. If you disable this policy setting, Java applets cannot run. If you do not configure this policy setting, the permission is set to High Safety","group_id_src":"V-223030"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223031r961086","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Trusted Sites Zone Don't run antimalware programs against ActiveX controls)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\2\\270C'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI092-IE11","rule_title":"Anti-Malware programs against ActiveX controls must be run for the Trusted Sites zone.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:569"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-001662"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer-&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Trusted Sites Zone 'Don't run antimalware programs against ActiveX controls' must be 'Enabled' and 'Disable' selected in the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\2  Criteria: If the value \"270C\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223031r961086_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000207","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B386EE9-6D7C-1014-B8A4-AAD6350C6B10","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59875","V-47009"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223031","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000207","id":"V-223031"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer-&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Trusted Sites Zone 'Don't run antimalware programs against ActiveX controls' to 'Enabled' and select 'Disable' in the drop-down box.   ","discussion":"This policy setting determines whether Internet Explorer runs Anti-Malware programs against ActiveX controls, to check if they're safe to load on pages.      If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer won't check with your Anti-Malware program to see if it's safe to create an instance of the ActiveX control. If you disable this policy setting, Internet Explorer always checks with your Anti-Malware program to see if it's safe to create an instance of the ActiveX control. If you don't configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer won't check with your Anti-Malware program to see if it's safe to create an instance of the ActiveX control. Users can turn this behavior on or off, using Internet Explorer Security settings.","group_id_src":"V-223031"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223032r1117169","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Enable dragging of content from different domains within a window)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3\\2708'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI1000-IE11","rule_title":"Dragging of content from different domains within a window must be disallowed (Internet zone).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:549"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-001414"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer-&gt; Internet Control Panel-&gt; Security Page-&gt; Internet Zone 'Enable dragging of content from different domains within a window' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disabled' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"2708\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223032r1117169_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000039","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B387511-6D7C-1014-8992-826AECF33288","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59409","V-46545"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223032","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000039","id":"V-223032"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer-&gt; Internet Control Panel-&gt; Security Page-&gt; Internet Zone 'Enable dragging of content from different domains within a window' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disabled' from the drop-down box.   ","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to set options for dragging content from one domain to a different domain when the source and destination are in the same window. If you enable this policy setting, users can drag content from one domain to a different domain when the source and destination are in the same window. Users cannot change this setting. If you disable this policy setting, users cannot drag content from one domain to a different domain when the source and destination are in the same window. Users cannot change this setting in the Internet Options dialog box. If you do not configure this policy setting, users cannot drag content from one domain to a different domain when the source and destination are in the same window. Users can change this setting in the Internet Options dialog box.","group_id_src":"V-223032"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223033r1117169","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer-&gt; Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Enable dragging of content from different domains across windows)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\\2709'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI1005-IE11","rule_title":"Dragging of content from different domains across windows must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:548"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-001414"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer-&gt; Internet Control Panel-&gt; Security Page-&gt; Restricted Sites Zone 'Enable dragging of content from different domains across windows' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disabled' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"2709\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223033r1117169_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000039","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B387A5A-6D7C-1014-8698-FE0E3FD08A82","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59411","V-46547"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223033","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000039","id":"V-223033"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer-&gt; Internet Control Panel-&gt; Security Page-&gt; Restricted Sites Zone 'Enable dragging of content from different domains across windows' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disabled' from the drop-down box.   ","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to set options for dragging content from one domain to a different domain when the source and destination are in different windows. If you enable this policy setting, users can drag content from one domain to a different domain when the source and destination are in different windows. Users cannot change this setting. If you enable this policy setting, users cannot drag content from one domain to a different domain when both the source and destination are in different windows. Users cannot change this setting. If you do not configure this policy setting, users cannot drag content from one domain to a different domain when the source and destination are in different windows. Users can change this setting in the Internet Options dialog box.","group_id_src":"V-223033"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223034r960921","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Restrict ActiveX Install\\Internet Explorer Processes must be Enabled)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_RESTRICT_ACTIVEXINSTALL\\explorer.exe'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI1010-IE11","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes Restrict ActiveX Install must be enforced (Explorer).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:535"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-001695"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Restrict ActiveX Install -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_RESTRICT_ACTIVEXINSTALL   Criteria: If the value \"explorer.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223034r960921_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000112","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B387F8F-6D7C-1014-AF41-D8057844F5C0","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59413","V-46549"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223034","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000112","id":"V-223034"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Restrict ActiveX Install -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   ","discussion":"Users often choose to install software such as ActiveX controls that are not permitted by their organization's security policy. Such software can pose significant security and privacy risks to networks. This policy setting enables blocking of ActiveX control installation prompts for Internet Explorer processes. If you enable this policy setting, prompts for ActiveX control installations will be blocked for Internet Explorer processes. If you disable this policy setting, prompts for ActiveX control installations will not be blocked and these prompts will be displayed to users. If you do not configure this policy setting, the user's preference will be used to determine whether to block ActiveX control installations for Internet Explorer processes.","group_id_src":"V-223034"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223035r960921","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Restrict ActiveX Install\\Internet Explorer Processes must be Enabled)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_RESTRICT_ACTIVEXINSTALL\\iexplore.exe'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI1020-IE11","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes Restrict ActiveX Install must be enforced (iexplore).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:536"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-001695"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Restrict ActiveX Install -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_RESTRICT_ACTIVEXINSTALL   Criteria: If the value \"iexplore.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223035r960921_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000112","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B3884B2-6D7C-1014-8888-9186914C32BA","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59417","V-46553"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223035","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000112","id":"V-223035"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Restrict ActiveX Install -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   ","discussion":"Users often choose to install software such as ActiveX controls that are not permitted by their organization's security policy. Such software can pose significant security and privacy risks to networks. This policy setting enables blocking of ActiveX control installation prompts for Internet Explorer processes. If you enable this policy setting, prompts for ActiveX control installations will be blocked for Internet Explorer processes. If you disable this policy setting, prompts for ActiveX control installations will not be blocked and these prompts will be displayed to users. If you do not configure this policy setting, the user's preference will be used to determine whether to block ActiveX control installations for Internet Explorer processes.","group_id_src":"V-223035"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223036r1117169","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Windows Components/Internet Explorer/Internet Control Panel/Security Page/Restricted Sites Zone/Enable dragging of content from different domains within a window)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\\2708'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI1025-IE11","