can drag content from one domain to a different domain when the source and destination are in the same window. Users cannot change this setting. If you disable this policy setting, users cannot drag content from one domain to a different domain when the source and destination are in the same window. Users cannot change this setting in the Internet Options dialog box. If you do not configure this policy setting, users cannot drag content from one domain to a different domain when the source and destination are in the same window. Users can change this setting in the Internet Options dialog box.","group_id_src":"V-223036"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223037r961086","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone Don't run antimalware programs against ActiveX controls)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3\\270C'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI1046-IE11","rule_title":"Anti-Malware programs against ActiveX controls must be run for the Internet zone.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:565"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-001662"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer-&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone 'Don't run antimalware programs against ActiveX controls' must be 'Enabled' and 'Disable' selected in the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3  Criteria: If the value \"270C\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223037r961086_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000207","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B388EB7-6D7C-1014-BB95-F0DAC4E63B9D","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59863","V-46997"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223037","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000207","id":"V-223037"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer-&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone 'Don't run antimalware programs against ActiveX controls' to 'Enabled' and select 'Disable' in the drop-down box.   ","discussion":"This policy setting determines whether Internet Explorer runs Anti-Malware programs against ActiveX controls, to check if they're safe to load on pages.      If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer won't check with your Anti-Malware program to see if it's safe to create an instance of the ActiveX control. If you disable this policy setting, Internet Explorer always checks with your Anti-Malware program to see if it's safe to create an instance of the ActiveX control. If you don't configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer always checks with your Anti-Malware program to see if it's safe to create an instance of the ActiveX control. Users can turn this behavior on or off, using Internet Explorer Security settings.","group_id_src":"V-223037"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223038r961086","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone Don't run antimalware programs against ActiveX controls)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\\270C'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI1051-IE11","rule_title":"Anti-Malware programs against ActiveX controls must be run for the Restricted Sites zone.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:568"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-001662"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer-&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone 'Don't run antimalware programs against ActiveX controls' must be 'Enabled' and 'Disable' selected in the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4  Criteria: If the value \"270C\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223038r961086_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000207","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B3893C7-6D7C-1014-8E3A-F210D453E663","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59871","V-47005"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223038","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000207","id":"V-223038"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer-&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone 'Don't run antimalware programs against ActiveX controls' to 'Enabled' and select 'Disable' in the drop-down box.   ","discussion":"This policy setting determines whether Internet Explorer runs Anti-Malware programs against ActiveX controls, to check if they're safe to load on pages.      If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer won't check with your Anti-Malware program to see if it's safe to create an instance of the ActiveX control. If you disable this policy setting, Internet Explorer always checks with your Anti-Malware program to see if it's safe to create an instance of the ActiveX control. If you don't configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer always checks with your Anti-Malware program to see if it's safe to create an instance of the ActiveX control. Users can turn this behavior on or off, using Internet Explorer Security settings.","group_id_src":"V-223038"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223039r961194","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\PhishingFilter\\PreventOverride is a REG_DWORD equal to 1)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\PhishingFilter\\PreventOverride'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI1060-IE11","rule_title":"Prevent bypassing SmartScreen Filter warnings must be enabled.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:578"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-001242"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"If the system is on the SIPRNet, this requirement is NA.\n\nThe policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; âPrevent bypassing SmartScreen Filter warningsâ must be âEnabledâ. \n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\PhishingFilter. \n\nCriteria: If the value \"PreventOverride\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.\n","rule_id_src":"SV-223039r961194_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000278","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B3898EF-6D7C-1014-8410-884E6BC6F602","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-79201","V-64711"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223039","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000278","id":"V-223039"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"If the system is on the SIPRNet, this requirement is NA.\n\nSet the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; âPrevent bypassing SmartScreen Filter warningsâ to âEnabledâ.   ","discussion":"This policy setting determines whether the user can bypass warnings from SmartScreen Filter. SmartScreen Filter prevents the user from browsing to or downloading from sites that are known to host malicious content. SmartScreen Filter also prevents the execution of files that are known to be malicious. If you enable this policy setting, SmartScreen Filter warnings block the user. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, the user can bypass SmartScreen Filter warnings.","group_id_src":"V-223039"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223040r961089","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\PhishingFilter\\PreventOverrideAppRepUnknown is a REG_DWORD equal to 1)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\PhishingFilter\\PreventOverrideAppRepUnknown'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI1065-IE11","rule_title":"Prevent bypassing SmartScreen Filter warnings about files that are not commonly downloaded from the internet must be enabled.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:572"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-001169"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"If the system is on the SIPRNet, this requirement is NA.\n\nThe policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; âPrevent bypassing SmartScreen Filter warnings about files that are not commonly downloaded from the internetâ must be âEnabledâ. \n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\PhishingFilter.\n\nCriteria: If the value \"PreventOverrideAppRepUnknown\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.\n","rule_id_src":"SV-223040r961089_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000209","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B389E33-6D7C-1014-B8EF-C4098E520DAF","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-79203","V-64713"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223040","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000209","id":"V-223040"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"If the system is on the SIPRNet, this requirement is NA.\n\nSet the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; âPrevent bypassing SmartScreen Filter warnings about files that are not commonly downloaded from the internetâ to âEnabledâ.   ","discussion":"This policy setting determines whether the user can bypass warnings from SmartScreen Filter. SmartScreen Filter warns the user about executable files that Internet Explorer users do not commonly download from the internet. If you enable this policy setting, SmartScreen Filter warnings block the user. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, the user can bypass SmartScreen Filter warnings.","group_id_src":"V-223040"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223041r961092","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Security\\ActiveX\\BlockNonAdminActiveXInstall is a REG_DWORD equal to 1)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Security\\ActiveX\\BlockNonAdminActiveXInstall'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI1070-IE11","rule_title":"Prevent per-user installation of ActiveX controls must be enabled.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:574"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; âPrevent per-user installation of ActiveX controlsâ must be âEnabledâ. \n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Security\\ActiveX. \n\nCriteria: If the value \"BlockNonAdminActiveXInstall\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.\n","rule_id_src":"SV-223041r961092_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B38A36B-6D7C-1014-B819-8F840ED04924","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-79205","V-64715"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223041","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000210","id":"V-223041"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; âPrevent per-user installation of ActiveX controlsâ to âEnabledâ.   ","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to prevent the installation of ActiveX controls on a per-user basis. If you enable this policy setting, ActiveX controls cannot be installed on a per-user basis. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, ActiveX controls can be installed on a per-user basis.","group_id_src":"V-223041"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223042r961596","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\PreventIgnoreCertErrors is a REG_DWORD equal to 1)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\PreventIgnoreCertErrors'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI1075-IE11","rule_title":"Prevent ignoring certificate errors option must be enabled.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:575"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-001954"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; âPrevent ignoring certificate errorsâ must be âEnabledâ. \n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings. \n\nCriteria: If the value \"PreventIgnoreCertErrors\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.\n","rule_id_src":"SV-223042r961596_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000427","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B38A87E-6D7C-1014-BE7C-9F71EA5C2222","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-79207","V-64717"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223042","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000427","id":"V-223042"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; âPrevent ignoring certificate errorsâ to âEnabledâ.   ","discussion":"This policy setting prevents the user from ignoring Secure Sockets Layer/Transport Layer Security (SSL/TLS) certificate errors that interrupt browsing (such as âexpiredâ, ârevokedâ, or âname mismatchâ errors) in Internet Explorer. If you enable this policy setting, the user cannot continue browsing. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, the user can choose to ignore certificate errors and continue browsing.","group_id_src":"V-223042"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223043r961194","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3\\2301 is a REG_DWORD equal to 0)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3\\2301'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI1080-IE11","rule_title":"Turn on SmartScreen Filter scan option for the Internet Zone must be enabled.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:577"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-001242"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; Security Page &gt;&gt; Internet Zone &gt;&gt; âTurn on SmartScreen Filter scanâ must be âEnabledâ and âEnableâ selected from the drop-down box. \n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3. \n\nCriteria: If the value \"2301\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.\n","rule_id_src":"SV-223043r961194_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000278","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B38AEEB-6D7C-1014-8824-B4033097EFA2","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-79209","V-64719"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223043","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000278","id":"V-223043"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; Security Page &gt;&gt; Internet Zone &gt;&gt; âTurn on SmartScreen Filter scanâ to âEnabledâ, and select âEnableâ from the drop-down box.   ","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether SmartScreen Filter scans pages in this zone for malicious content. If you enable this policy setting, SmartScreen Filter scans pages in this zone for malicious content. If you disable this policy setting, SmartScreen Filter does not scan pages in this zone for malicious content. If you do not configure this policy setting, the user can choose whether SmartScreen Filter scans pages in this zone for malicious content.","group_id_src":"V-223043"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223044r961194","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\\2301 is a REG_DWORD equal to 0)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\\2301'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI1085-IE11","rule_title":"Turn on SmartScreen Filter scan option for the Restricted Sites Zone must be enabled.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:576"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-001242"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; Security Page &gt;&gt; Restricted Sites Zone &gt;&gt; âTurn on SmartScreen Filter scanâ must be âEnabledâ and âEnableâ selected from the drop-down box. \n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4. \n\nCriteria: If the value \"2301\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.\n","rule_id_src":"SV-223044r961194_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000278","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B38B4B9-6D7C-1014-9B66-85565C7679AC","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-79211","V-64721"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223044","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000278","id":"V-223044"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; Security Page &gt;&gt; Restricted Sites Zone &gt;&gt; âTurn on SmartScreen Filter scanâ to âEnabledâ, and select âEnableâ from the drop-down box.   ","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether SmartScreen Filter scans pages in this zone for malicious content. If you enable this policy setting, SmartScreen Filter scans pages in this zone for malicious content. If you disable this policy setting, SmartScreen Filter does not scan pages in this zone for malicious content. If you do not configure this policy setting, the user can choose whether SmartScreen Filter scans pages in this zone for malicious content.","group_id_src":"V-223044"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223045r961092","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\1\\1201 is a REG_DWORD equal to 3)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\1\\1201'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI1090-IE11","rule_title":"The Initialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safe must be disallowed (Intranet Zone).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:579"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; Security Page &gt;&gt; Intranet Zone &gt;&gt; âInitialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safeâ must be âEnabledâ and âDisableâ selected from the drop-down box. \n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\1. \n\nCriteria: If the value \"1201\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.\n","rule_id_src":"SV-223045r961092_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B38BB8C-6D7C-1014-BCE0-AAB2EAD0819C","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-79213","V-64723"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223045","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000210","id":"V-223045"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; Security Page &gt;&gt; Intranet Zone &gt;&gt; âInitialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safeâ to âEnabledâ, and select âDisableâ from the drop-down box.   ","discussion":"ActiveX controls that are not marked safe for scripting should not be executed. Although this is not a complete security measure for a control to be marked safe for scripting, if a control is not marked safe, it should not be initialized and executed. This setting causes both unsafe and safe controls to be initialized and scripted, ignoring the Script ActiveX controls marked safe for scripting option. This increases the risk of malicious code being loaded and executed by the browser. If you enable this policy setting, ActiveX controls are run, loaded with parameters and scripted without setting object safety for untrusted data or scripts. If you disable this policy setting, ActiveX controls that cannot be made safe are not loaded with parameters or scripted. This setting is not recommended, except for secure and administered zones.","group_id_src":"V-223045"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223046r961092","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\2\\1201 is a REG_DWORD equal to 3)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\2\\1201'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI1095-IE11","rule_title":"The Initialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safe must be disallowed (Trusted Sites Zone).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:573"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; Security Page &gt;&gt; Trusted Sites Zone &gt;&gt; âInitialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safeâ must be âEnabledâ and âDisableâ selected from the drop-down box. \n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\2. \n\nCriteria: If the value \"1201\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.\n","rule_id_src":"SV-223046r961092_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B38C1C6-6D7C-1014-82DE-B5D40C05CF92","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-79215","V-64725"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223046","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000210","id":"V-223046"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; Security Page &gt;&gt; Trusted Sites Zone &gt;&gt; âInitialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safeâ to âEnabledâ, and select âDisableâ from the drop-down box.   ","discussion":"ActiveX controls that are not marked safe for scripting should not be executed. Although this is not a complete security measure for a control to be marked safe for scripting, if a control is not marked safe, it should not be initialized and executed. This setting causes both unsafe and safe controls to be initialized and scripted, ignoring the Script ActiveX controls marked safe for scripting option. This increases the risk of malicious code being loaded and executed by the browser. If you enable this policy setting, ActiveX controls are run, loaded with parameters and scripted without setting object safety for untrusted data or scripts. If you disable this policy setting, ActiveX controls that cannot be made safe are not loaded with parameters or scripted. This setting is not recommended, except for secure and administered zones.","group_id_src":"V-223046"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223048r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Check if HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Ext\\RunThisTimeEnabled is set to 0)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Ext\\RunThisTimeEnabled'.  Existence requirement is 'all_exist' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI1105-IE11","rule_title":"Run once selection for running outdated ActiveX controls must be disabled.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:585"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"In the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Security Features &gt;&gt; Add-on Management, verify \"Remove the Run this time button for outdated ActiveX controls in IE\" is set to âEnabledâ. \n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKLM\\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Ext \n\nIf the value \"RunThisTimeEnabled\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223048r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B38C7A7-6D7C-1014-BD10-BCB8DF9CD0EC","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-87395","V-72757"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223048","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223048"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"In the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Security Features &gt;&gt; Add-on Management, set \"Remove the Run this time button for outdated ActiveX controls in IE\" to \"Enabled\".","discussion":"This feature keeps ActiveX controls up to date and helps make them safer to use in Internet Explorer. Many ActiveX controls are not automatically updated as new versions are released. It is very important to keep ActiveX controls up to date because malicious or compromised webpages can target security flaws in out-of-date ActiveX controls.","group_id_src":"V-223048"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223049r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Check if HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Ext\\VersionCheckEnabled is set to 1)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Ext\\VersionCheckEnabled'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI1110-IE11","rule_title":"Enabling outdated ActiveX controls for Internet Explorer must be blocked.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:586"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"In the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Security Features &gt;&gt; Add-on Management, verify \"Turn off blocking of outdated ActiveX controls for Internet Explorer\" is set to âDisabledâ. \n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKLM\\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Ext \n\nIf the value \"VersionCheckEnabled\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223049r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B38CCFB-6D7C-1014-87A7-A78A767F0946","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-87397","V-72759"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223049","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223049"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"In the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Security Features &gt;&gt; Add-on Management, set \"Turn off blocking of outdated ActiveX controls for Internet Explorer\" to \"Disabled\".","discussion":"This feature keeps ActiveX controls up to date and helps make them safer to use in Internet Explorer. Many ActiveX controls are not automatically updated as new versions are released. It is very important to keep ActiveX controls up to date because malicious or compromised webpages can target security flaws in out-of-date ActiveX controls.","group_id_src":"V-223049"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223050r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     false (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Allow only approved domains to use the TDC ActiveX control)\nResult Analysis :          Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3\\120c'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nCriteria        :     true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :       true (The OS Version is equal to or greater than 6.3)\nTest            :       true (The OS Build is equal to or greater than 14393)\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :     false (All child tests must be true. (AND)) (negated)\nTest            :       true (The OS Version is equal to or greater than 6.3)\nTest            :       true (The OS Build is equal to or greater than 14393)\n","rule_version":"DTBI1115-IE11","rule_title":"Use of the Tabular Data Control (TDC) ActiveX control must be disabled for the Internet Zone.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:583"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"In the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; Security Page &gt;&gt; Internet Zone, verify \"Allow only approved domains to use the TDC ActiveX control\" is âEnabledâ. \n\nIn the Options window, verify the âOnly allow approved domains to use the TDC ActiveX control\" drop-down box is set to âEnableâ. \n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 \n\nCriteria: \n\nIf the value \"120c\" is REG_DWORD = â3â, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223050r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B38D2C6-6D7C-1014-A34C-E6509F36250B","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-87399","V-72761"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223050","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223050"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"In the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Pane &gt;&gt; Security Page &gt;&gt; Internet Zone, set the \"Allow only approved domains to use the TDC ActiveX control\" to âEnabledâ. \n\nIn the Options window, select \"Enable\" from the âOnly allow approved domains to use the TDC ActiveX control\" drop-down box.","discussion":"This policy setting determines whether users can run the Tabular Data Control (TDC) ActiveX control, based on security zone. By default, the TDC ActiveX Control is disabled in the Internet and Restricted Sites security zones. If you enable this policy setting, users will not be able to run the TDC ActiveX control from all sites in the specified zone.","group_id_src":"V-223050"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223051r961089","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Download signed ActiveX controls)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\\1001'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI112-IE11","rule_title":"The Download signed ActiveX controls property must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:436"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-001169"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Download signed ActiveX controls' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1001\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223051r961089_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000209","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B38D7D8-6D7C-1014-A953-E4D308C83717","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59437","V-46573"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223051","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000209","id":"V-223051"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Download signed ActiveX controls' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","discussion":"ActiveX controls can contain potentially malicious code and must only be allowed to be downloaded from trusted sites. Signed code is better than unsigned code in that it may be easier to determine its author, but it is still potentially harmful, especially when coming from an untrusted zone.","group_id_src":"V-223051"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223052r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     false (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Allow only approved domains to use the TDC ActiveX control)\nResult Analysis :          Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\\120c'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nCriteria        :     true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :       true (The OS Version is equal to or greater than 6.3)\nTest            :       true (The OS Build is equal to or greater than 14393)\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :     false (All child tests must be true. (AND)) (negated)\nTest            :       true (The OS Version is equal to or greater than 6.3)\nTest            :       true (The OS Build is equal to or greater than 14393)\n","rule_version":"DTBI1120-IE11","rule_title":"Use of the Tabular Data Control (TDC) ActiveX control must be disabled for the Restricted Sites Zone.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:584"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"In the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; Security Page &gt;&gt; Restricted Sites Zone, verify \"Allow only approved domains to use the TDC ActiveX control\" is âEnabledâ. \n\nIn the Options window, verify the âOnly allow approved domains to use the TDC ActiveX control\" drop-down box is set to âEnableâ. \n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 \n\nCriteria: \n\nIf the value \"120c\" is REG_DWORD = â3â, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223052r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B38DD2B-6D7C-1014-AACF-C39D13F1C453","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-87401","V-72763"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223052","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223052"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"In the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; Security Page &gt;&gt; Restricted Sites Zone, set the \"Allow only approved domains to use the TDC ActiveX control\" to âEnabledâ.\n\nIn the Options windows, select \"Enable\" from the âOnly allow approved domains to use the TDC ActiveX control\" drop-down box.\n \n","discussion":"This policy setting determines whether users can run the Tabular Data Control (TDC) ActiveX control, based on security zone. By default, the TDC ActiveX Control is disabled in the Internet and Restricted Sites security zones. If you enable this policy setting, users wonât be able to run the TDC ActiveX control from all sites in the specified zone.","group_id_src":"V-223052"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223053r961089","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Allow VBScript to run in Internet Explorer' setting is set to 'Enable' and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box in Group Policy.)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3\\140C'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND)) (negated)\nTest            :     true (The OS Version is equal to or greater than 6.3)\nTest            :     true (The OS Build is equal to or greater than 15063)\n","rule_version":"DTBI1125-IE11","rule_title":"VBScript must not be allowed to run in Internet Explorer (Internet zone).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:588"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-001169"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; Security Page &gt;&gt; Internet Zone &gt;&gt; \"Allow VBScript to run in Internet Explorer\" must be \"Enabled\", and \"Disable\" must be selected from the drop-down box. \n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3\n\nIf the value for \"140C\" is not REG_DWORD = 3, this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223053r961089_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000209","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B38E253-6D7C-1014-9055-DE2C55AA1C35","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-89849","V-75169"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223053","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000209","id":"V-223053"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; Security Page &gt;&gt; Internet Zone &gt;&gt; \"Allow VBScript to run in Internet Explorer\" to \"Enabled\" and select \"Disable\" from the drop-down box.","discussion":"This policy setting allows the management of whether VBScript can be run on pages from the specified zone in Internet Explorer. By selecting \"Enable\" in the drop-down box, VBScript can run without user intervention. By selecting \"Prompt\" in the drop-down box, users are asked to choose whether to allow VBScript to run. By selecting \"Disable\" in the drop-down box, VBScript is prevented from running. If this policy setting is not configured or disabled, VBScript will run without user intervention.","group_id_src":"V-223053"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223054r961089","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Download unsigned ActiveX controls)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\\1004'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI113-IE11","rule_title":"The Download unsigned ActiveX controls property must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:437"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-001169"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Download unsigned ActiveX controls' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1004\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223054r961089_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000209","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B38E781-6D7C-1014-B3BF-C8F0EF9067C5","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59439","V-46575"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223054","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000209","id":"V-223054"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Download unsigned ActiveX controls' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","discussion":"Unsigned code is potentially harmful, especially when coming from an untrusted zone. ActiveX controls can contain potentially malicious code and must only be allowed to be downloaded from trusted sites. They must also be digitally signed.","group_id_src":"V-223054"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223055r961089","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone-&gt;'Allow VBScript to run in Internet Explorer' setting is set to 'Enable' and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box in Group Policy.)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\\140C'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND)) (negated)\nTest            :     true (The OS Version is equal to or greater than 6.3)\nTest            :     true (The OS Build is equal to or greater than 15063)\n","rule_version":"DTBI1130-IE11","rule_title":"VBScript must not be allowed to run in Internet Explorer (Restricted Sites zone).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:589"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-001169"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; Security Page &gt;&gt; Restricted Sites Zone &gt;&gt; \"Allow VBScript to run in Internet Explorer\" must be \"Enabled\", and \"Disable\" must be selected from the drop-down box.\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\n\nIf the value for \"140C\" is not REG_DWORD = 3, this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223055r961089_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000209","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B38EC93-6D7C-1014-97BC-A23E9F09B938","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-89851","V-75171"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223055","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000209","id":"V-223055"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; Security Page &gt;&gt; Restricted Sites Zone &gt;&gt; \"Allow VBScript to run in Internet Explorer\" to \"Enabled\" and select \"Disable\" from the drop-down box.","discussion":"This policy setting allows the management of whether VBScript can be run on pages from the specified zone in Internet Explorer. By selecting \"Enable\" in the drop-down box, VBScript can run without user intervention. By selecting \"Prompt\" in the drop-down box, users are asked to choose whether to allow VBScript to run. By selecting \"Disable\" in the drop-down box, VBScript is prevented from running. If this policy setting is not configured or disabled, VBScript will run without user intervention.","group_id_src":"V-223055"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223056r961167","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Developer Tools are disabled)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\IEDevTools\\Disabled'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI1135-IE11","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Development Tools Must Be Disabled.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:591"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-001312"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Toolbars &gt;&gt; âTurn off Developer Toolsâ must be âEnabledâ. \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKEY_LOCAL_Machine\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\IEDevTools\nCriteria: If the value \"Disabled\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223056r961167_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000266","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B38F1C7-6D7C-1014-A289-DF873A43B380","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"low","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-106631","V-97527"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223056","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000266","id":"V-223056"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Toolbars &gt;&gt; âTurn off Developer Toolsâ to âEnabledâ.","discussion":"While the risk associated with browser development tools is more related to the proper design of a web application, a risk vector remains within the browser. The developer tools allow end users and application developers to view and edit all types of web application related data via the browser. Page elements, source code, javascript, API calls, application data, etc. may all be viewed and potentially manipulated. Manipulation could be useful for troubleshooting legitimate issues, and this may be performed in a development environment. Manipulation could also be malicious and must be addressed.","group_id_src":"V-223056"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223057r961092","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Initialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safe)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\\1201'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI114-IE11","rule_title":"The Initialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safe property must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:438"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Initialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safe' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1201\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223057r961092_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B38F716-6D7C-1014-B988-ACE4F9B534CE","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59441","V-46577"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223057","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000210","id":"V-223057"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Initialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safe' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","discussion":"ActiveX controls not marked safe for scripting should not be executed. Although this is not a complete security measure for a control to be marked safe for scripting, if a control is not marked safe, it should not be initialized and executed.","group_id_src":"V-223057"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223058r961863","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Run ActiveX controls and plugins)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\\1200'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI115-IE11","rule_title":"ActiveX controls and plug-ins must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:439"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Run ActiveX controls and plugins' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1200\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223058r961863_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B38FC32-6D7C-1014-BB48-87FE4281854E","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59443","V-46579"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223058","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000516","id":"V-223058"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Run ActiveX controls and plugins' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether ActiveX controls and plug-ins can be run on pages from the specified zone. ActiveX controls not marked as safe should not be executed. If you enable this policy setting, controls and plug-ins can run without user intervention. If you disable this policy setting, controls and plug-ins are prevented from running.","group_id_src":"V-223058"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223059r961092","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Script ActiveX controls marked safe for scripting)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\\1405'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI116-IE11","rule_title":"ActiveX controls marked safe for scripting must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:440"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Script ActiveX controls marked safe for scripting' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1405\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223059r961092_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B390140-6D7C-1014-9B00-EC7DC5F4677C","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59445","V-46581"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223059","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000210","id":"V-223059"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Script ActiveX controls marked safe for scripting' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","discussion":"This policy setting allows management of whether ActiveX controls marked safe for scripting can interact with a script. If you enable this policy setting, script interaction can occur automatically without user intervention. ActiveX controls not marked as safe for scripting should not be executed. Although this is not a complete security measure for a control to be marked safe for scripting, if a control is not marked safe, it should not be initialized and executed.","group_id_src":"V-223059"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223060r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Allow file downloads)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\\1803'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI119-IE11","rule_title":"File downloads must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:441"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow file downloads' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1803\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223060r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B39071F-6D7C-1014-A15A-F176614ED2CF","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59447","V-46583"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223060","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223060"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow file downloads' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","discussion":"Sites located in the Restricted Sites Zone are more likely to contain malicious payloads and therefore downloads from this zone should be blocked. Files should not be able to be downloaded from sites that are considered restricted. This policy setting allows you to manage whether file downloads are permitted from the zone. This option is determined by the zone of the page with the link causing the download, not the zone from which the file is delivered.","group_id_src":"V-223060"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223061r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Java permissions)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\\1C00'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI121-IE11","rule_title":"Java permissions must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:453"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Java permissions' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable Java' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1C00\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223061r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B390C53-6D7C-1014-A07A-B8122E4E6569","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59451","V-46587"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223061","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223061"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Java permissions' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable Java' from the drop-down box.  ","discussion":"Java applications could contain malicious code; sites located in this security zone are more likely to be hosted by malicious individuals. This policy setting allows you to manage permissions for Java applets. If you enable this policy setting, options can be chosen from the drop-down box. Use of the Custom permission will control permissions settings individually. Use of the Low Safety permission enables applets to perform all operations. Use of the Medium Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox (an area in memory outside of which the program cannot make calls), plus adds capabilities like scratch space (a safe and secure storage area on the client computer) and a user-controlled file I/O. Use of the High Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox. If you disable this policy setting, Java applets cannot run. If you do not configure this policy setting, the permission is set to High Safety.","group_id_src":"V-223061"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223062r1117169","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Access data sources across domains)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\\1406'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI122-IE11","rule_title":"Accessing data sources across domains must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:443"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-001414"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Access data sources across domains' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1406\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223062r1117169_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000039","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B3911C0-6D7C-1014-A483-BDC83B04CECB","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59453","V-46589"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223062","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000039","id":"V-223062"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Access data sources across domains' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","discussion":"The ability to access data zones across domains could cause the user to unknowingly access content hosted on an unauthorized server. This policy setting allows you to manage whether Internet Explorer can access data from another security zone using the Microsoft XML Parser (MSXML) or ActiveX Data Objects (ADO).","group_id_src":"V-223062"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223063r961863","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Allow META REFRESH)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\\1608'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI123-IE11","rule_title":"The Allow META REFRESH property must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:444"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow META REFRESH' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1608\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223063r961863_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B391982-6D7C-1014-AC5F-AAFC854D2F46","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59455","V-46591"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223063","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000516","id":"V-223063"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow META REFRESH' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.","discussion":"It is possible that users will unknowingly be redirected to a site hosting malicious content. 'Allow META REFRESH' must have a level of protection based upon the site being browsed. This policy setting allows you to manage whether a user's browser can be redirected to another web page if the author of the web page uses the Meta Refresh setting to redirect browsers to another web page.","group_id_src":"V-223063"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223064r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Allow drag and drop or copy and paste files)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\\1802'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI126-IE11","rule_title":"Functionality to drag and drop or copy and paste files must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:445"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow drag and drop or copy and paste files' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1802\" is REG_DWORD=3, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223064r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B392130-6D7C-1014-9055-A707632E7B06","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59457","V-46593"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223064","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223064"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow drag and drop or copy and paste files' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","discussion":"Content hosted on sites located in the Restricted Sites zone are more likely to contain malicious payloads and therefore this feature should be blocked for this zone. Drag and drop or copy and paste files must have a level of protection based upon the site being accessed.","group_id_src":"V-223064"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223065r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Launching applications and files in an IFRAME)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\\1804'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI128-IE11","rule_title":"Launching programs and files in IFRAME must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:447"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Launching applications and files in an IFRAME' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1804\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223065r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B3928AF-6D7C-1014-8B83-91580AF62DC3","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59461","V-46597"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223065","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223065"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Launching applications and files in an IFRAME' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether applications may be run and files may be downloaded from an IFRAME reference in the HTML of the pages in this zone. Launching of programs in IFRAME must have a level of protection based upon the site being accessed. If you enable this policy setting, applications can run and files can be downloaded from IFRAMEs on the pages in this zone without user intervention. If you disable this setting, users are prevented from running applications and downloading files from IFRAMEs on the pages in this zone.","group_id_src":"V-223065"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223066r1117169","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Navigate windows and frames across different domains)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\\1607'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI129-IE11","rule_title":"Navigating windows and frames across different domains must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:448"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-001414"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Navigate windows and frames across different domains' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1607\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223066r1117169_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000039","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B392E1B-6D7C-1014-97BA-E3AF1F008932","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59463","V-46599"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223066","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000039","id":"V-223066"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Navigate windows and frames across different domains' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box. ","discussion":"Frames navigating across different domains are a security concern, because the user may think they are accessing pages on one site while they are actually accessing pages on another site. It is possible that a website hosting malicious content could use this feature in a manner similar to cross-site scripting (XSS). This policy setting allows you to manage the opening of sub-frames and access of applications across different domains.","group_id_src":"V-223066"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223067r961128","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Userdata persistence)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\\1606'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI132-IE11","rule_title":"Userdata persistence must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:449"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-001199"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Userdata persistence' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1606\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223067r961128_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000231","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B393357-6D7C-1014-A103-AF011D29DD54","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59465","V-46601"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223067","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000231","id":"V-223067"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Userdata persistence' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box","discussion":"Userdata persistence must have a level of protection based upon the site being accessed. This policy setting allows you to manage the preservation of information in the browser's history, in Favorites, in an XML store, or directly within a web page saved to disk. When a user returns to a persisted page, the state of the page can be restored if this policy setting is not appropriately configured.","group_id_src":"V-223067"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223068r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Allow active scripting)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\\1400'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI133-IE11","rule_title":"Active scripting must be disallowed (Restricted Sites Zone).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:450"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow active scripting' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1400\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223068r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B393894-6D7C-1014-85C9-B89F1A5A748E","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59467","V-46603"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223068","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223068"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow active scripting' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box. ","discussion":"Active scripts hosted on sites located in this zone are more likely to contain malicious code. Active scripting must have a level of protection based upon the site being accessed. This policy setting allows you to manage whether script code on pages in the zone are run.","group_id_src":"V-223068"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223069r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Allow cut, copy, or paste operations from the clipboard via script)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\\1407'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI134-IE11","rule_title":"Clipboard operations via script must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:451"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow cut, copy or paste operations from the clipboard via script' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1407\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223069r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B393DB8-6D7C-1014-B647-C2B3D5F1CA13","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59469","V-46605"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223069","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223069"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow cut, copy or paste operations from the clipboard via script' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box. ","discussion":"A malicious script could use the clipboard in an undesirable manner, for example, if the user had recently copied confidential information to the clipboard while editing a document, a malicious script could harvest that information. It might be possible to exploit other vulnerabilities in order to send the harvested data to the attacker. Allow paste operations via script must have a level of protection based upon the site being accessed.","group_id_src":"V-223069"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223070r1043178","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Logon options)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\\1A00'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI136-IE11","rule_title":"Logon options must be configured and enforced (Restricted Sites zone).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:452"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-001184"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Logon options' must be 'Enabled', and 'Anonymous logon' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1A00\" is REG_DWORD = 196608 (decimal), this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223070r1043178_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000219","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B39439B-6D7C-1014-A650-CE6F17CDE4C8","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59471","V-46607"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223070","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000219","id":"V-223070"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Logon options' to 'Enabled', and select 'Anonymous logon' from the drop-down box.","discussion":"Users could submit credentials to servers operated by malicious individuals who could then attempt to connect to legitimate servers with those captured credentials. Care must be taken with user credentials, automatic logon performance, and how default Windows credentials are passed to the websites. This policy setting allows management of settings for logon options. If you enable this policy setting, you can choose from varying logon options. âAnonymous logonâ disables HTTP authentication and uses the guest account only for the Common Internet File System (CIFS) protocol. âPrompt for user name and passwordâ queries users for user IDs and passwords. After a user is queried, these values can be used silently for the remainder of the session. âAutomatic logon only in Intranet zoneâ queries users for user IDs and passwords in other zones. After a user is queried, these values can be used silently for the remainder of the session. âAutomatic logon with current user name and passwordâ attempts logon using Windows NT Challenge Response. If Windows NT Challenge Response is supported by the server, the logon uses the user's network user name and password for login. If Windows NT Challenge Response is not supported by the server, the user is queried to provide the user name and password. If you disable this policy setting, logon is set to âAutomatic logon only in Intranet zoneâ. If you do not configure this policy setting, logon is set to âAutomatic logon only in Intranet zoneâ. The most secure option is to configure this setting to âEnabledâ; âAnonymous logonâ. This will prevent users from submitting credentials to servers in this security zone.","group_id_src":"V-223070"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223071r960879","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Delete Browsing History\\Disable Configuring History must be Enabled)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Control Panel\\History'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Delete Browsing History\\40 entered in Days to keep pages in History)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Url History\\DaysToKeep'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI300-IE11","rule_title":"Configuring History setting must be set to 40 days.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:513"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000169"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Delete Browsing History -&gt; 'Disable Configuring History' must be 'Enabled', and '40' entered in 'Days to keep pages in History'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Control Panel Criteria: If the value \"History\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding. AND  Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Url History Criteria: If the value \"DaysToKeep\" is REG_DWORD = 40 (decimal), this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223071r960879_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000089","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B394907-6D7C-1014-B7D8-9785052F2BBB","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59473","V-46609"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223071","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000089","id":"V-223071"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Delete Browsing History -&gt; 'Disable Configuring History' to 'Enabled', and enter '40' in 'Days to keep pages in History'.","discussion":"This setting specifies the number of days that Internet Explorer keeps track of the pages viewed in the History List. The delete Browsing History option can be accessed using Tools, Internet Options, \"General\" tab, and then click Settings under Browsing History. If you enable this policy setting, a user cannot set the number of days that Internet Explorer keeps track of the pages viewed in the History List. The number of days that Internet Explorer keeps track of the pages viewed in the History List must be specified. Users will not be able to delete browsing history. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, a user can set the number of days that Internet Explorer tracks views of pages in the History List. Users can delete browsing history.","group_id_src":"V-223071"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223072r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Security Zones: Do Not Allow Users to Add/Delete Sites)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Security_zones_map_edit'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI318-IE11","rule_title":"Internet Explorer must be set to disallow users to add/delete sites.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:419"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer 'Security Zones: Do not allow users to add/delete sites' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings Criteria: If the value \"Security_zones_map_edit\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223072r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B394E42-6D7C-1014-ABC2-8DF988AE75BA","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59479","V-46615"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223072","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223072"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer 'Security Zones: Do not allow users to add/delete sites' to 'Enabled'.","discussion":"This setting prevents users from adding sites to various security zones. Users should not be able to add sites to different zones, as this could allow them to bypass security controls of the system. If you do not configure this policy setting, users will be able to add or remove sites from the Trusted Sites and Restricted Sites zones at will and change settings in the Local Intranet zone. This configuration could allow sites that host malicious mobile code to be added to these zones, and users could execute the code.","group_id_src":"V-223072"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223073r961863","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Security Zones: Do Not Allow Users to Change Policies)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Security_options_edit'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI319-IE11","rule_title":"Internet Explorer must be configured to disallow users to change policies.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:418"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer 'Security Zones: Do not allow users to change policies' must be 'Enabled'.  Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings Criteria: If the value \"Security_options_edit\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223073r961863_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B395409-6D7C-1014-AE2E-BE4EA5B59706","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59481","V-46617"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223073","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000516","id":"V-223073"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer 'Security Zones: Do not allow users to change policies' to 'Enabled'.   ","discussion":"Users who change their Internet Explorer security settings could enable the execution of dangerous types of code from the Internet and websites listed in the Restricted Sites zone in the browser. This setting prevents users from changing the Internet Explorer policies on the machine. Policy changes should be made by administrators only, so this setting should be enabled. If you enable this policy setting, you disable the \"Custom level\" button and \"Security\" level for this zone slider on the Security tab in the Internet Options dialog box. If this policy setting is disabled or not configured, users will be able to change the settings for security zones. It prevents users from changing security zone policy settings that are established by the administrator.","group_id_src":"V-223073"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223074r961863","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Security Zones: Use Only Machine Settings)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Security_HKLM_only'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI320-IE11","rule_title":"Internet Explorer must be configured to use machine settings.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:417"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer 'Security Zones: Use only machine settings' must be 'Enabled'.  Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings Criteria: If the value \"Security_HKLM_only\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223074r961863_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B39591C-6D7C-1014-8560-BA9C528DD76A","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59483","V-46619"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223074","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000516","id":"V-223074"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer 'Security Zones: Use only machine settings' to 'Enabled'. ","discussion":"Users who change their Internet Explorer security settings could enable the execution of dangerous types of code from the Internet and websites listed in the Restricted Sites zone in the browser. This setting enforces consistent security zone settings to all users of the computer. Security zones control browser behavior at various websites and it is desirable to maintain a consistent policy for all users of a machine. This policy setting affects how security zone changes apply to different users. If you enable this policy setting, changes that one user makes to a security zone will apply to all users of that computer. If this policy setting is disabled or not configured, users of the same computer are allowed to establish their own security zone settings.","group_id_src":"V-223074"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223075r961863","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Turn off the Security Settings Check feature)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Security\\DisableSecuritySettingsCheck'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI325-IE11","rule_title":"Security checking features must be enforced.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:457"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; 'Turn off the Security Settings Check feature' must be 'Disabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Security Criteria: If the value \"DisableSecuritySettingsCheck\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223075r961863_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B395EDD-6D7C-1014-B99E-EEC7F60AFC14","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59485","V-46621"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223075","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000516","id":"V-223075"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; 'Turn off the Security Settings Check feature' to 'Disabled'.   ","discussion":"This policy setting turns off the Security Settings Check feature, which checks Internet Explorer security settings to determine when the settings put Internet Explorer at risk. If you enable this policy setting, the security settings check will not be performed. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, the security settings check will be performed.","group_id_src":"V-223075"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223076r961092","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Advanced Page \\Allow Software to Run or Install Even if the Signature is Invalid)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Download\\RunInvalidSignatures'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI350-IE11","rule_title":"Software must be disallowed to run or install with invalid signatures.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:459"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Note: Some legitimate software and controls may have an invalid signature. You should carefully test such software in isolation before it is allowed to be used on an organization's network.\n\nThe policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Advanced Page -&gt; 'Allow software to run or install even if the signature is invalid' must be 'Disabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Download Criteria: If the value \"RunInvalidSignatures\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223076r961092_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B396429-6D7C-1014-AFD3-993939959A8D","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59489","V-46625"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223076","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000210","id":"V-223076"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Advanced Page -&gt; 'Allow software to run or install even if the signature is invalid' to 'Disabled'. ","discussion":"Microsoft ActiveX controls and file downloads often have digital signatures attached that certify the file's integrity and the identity of the signer (creator) of the software. Such signatures help ensure unmodified software is downloaded and the user can positively identify the signer to determine whether you trust them enough to run their software.","group_id_src":"V-223076"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223077r961131","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Advanced Page Turn on 64-bit tab processes when running in Enhanced Protected Mode on 64-bit versions of Windows)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\Isolation64Bit'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI356-IE11","rule_title":"The 64-bit tab processes, when running in Enhanced Protected Mode on 64-bit versions of Windows, must be turned on.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:564"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-001084"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Note: If McAfee ENS Web Control is being used, this is Not Applicable.\n\nThe policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer-&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Advanced Page 'Turn on 64-bit tab processes when running in Enhanced Protected Mode on 64-bit versions of Windows' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main Criteria: If the value \"Isolation64Bit\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223077r961131_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000233","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B39696D-6D7C-1014-9314-8203D5F93F08","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59861","V-46995"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223077","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000233","id":"V-223077"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer-&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Advanced Page 'Turn on 64-bit tab processes when running in Enhanced Protected Mode on 64-bit versions of Windows' to 'Enabled'.   ","discussion":"This policy setting determines whether Internet Explorer 11 uses 64-bit processes (for greater security) or 32-bit processes (for greater compatibility) when running in Enhanced Protected Mode on 64-bit versions of Windows.Important: Some ActiveX controls and toolbars may not be available when 64-bit processes are used. If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer 11 will use 64-bit tab processes when running in Enhanced Protected Mode on 64-bit versions of Windows. If you disable this policy setting, Internet Explorer 11 will use 32-bit tab processes when running in Enhanced Protected Mode on 64-bit versions of Windows. If you don't configure this policy setting, users can turn this feature on or off using Internet Explorer settings. This feature is turned off by default.","group_id_src":"V-223077"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223078r961038","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Advanced Page \\Check for Server Certificate Revocation)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\CertificateRevocation'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI365-IE11","rule_title":"Checking for server certificate revocation must be enforced.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:461"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000185"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Advanced Page -&gt; 'Check for server certificate revocation' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings Criteria: If the value \"CertificateRevocation\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223078r961038_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000175","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B396E92-6D7C-1014-9BA1-F871866C495F","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"low","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59493","V-46629"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223078","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000175","id":"V-223078"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Advanced Page -&gt; 'Check for server certificate revocation' to 'Enabled'.   ","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether Internet Explorer will check revocation status of servers' certificates. Certificates are revoked when they have been compromised or are no longer valid, and this option protects users from submitting confidential data to a site that may be fraudulent or not secure. If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will check to see if server certificates have been revoked. If you disable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will not check server certificates to see if they have been revoked. If you do not configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer will not check server certificates to see if they have been revoked.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-APP-000605","group_id_src":"V-223078"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223079r960954","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Advanced Page \\Check for Signature on Downloaded Programs)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Download\\CheckExeSignatures'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI370-IE11","rule_title":"Checking for signatures on downloaded programs must be enforced.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:462"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-001749"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Advanced Page -&gt; 'Check for signatures on downloaded programs' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Download Criteria: If the value \"CheckExeSignatures\" is REG_SZ = yes, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223079r960954_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000131","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B3973B0-6D7C-1014-9F3D-C310EBAF62AF","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59497","V-46633"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223079","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000131","id":"V-223079"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Advanced Page -&gt; 'Check for signatures on downloaded programs' to 'Enabled'.   ","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether Internet Explorer checks for digital signatures (which identifies the publisher of signed software and verifies it has not been modified or tampered with) on user computers before downloading executable programs. If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will check the digital signatures of executable programs and display their identities before downloading them to the user computers. If you disable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will not check the digital signatures of executable programs or display their identities before downloading them to the user computers. If you do not configure this policy, Internet Explorer will not check the digital signatures of executable programs or display their identities before downloading them to the user computers.","group_id_src":"V-223079"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223080r961863","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Intranet Sites: Include all network paths (UNCs))\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\ZoneMap\\UNCAsIntranet'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI375-IE11","rule_title":"All network paths (UNCs) for Intranet sites must be disallowed.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:463"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; 'Intranet Sites: Include all network paths (UNCs)' must be 'Disabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\ZoneMap Criteria: If the value \"UNCAsIntranet\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223080r961863_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B3978CA-6D7C-1014-A013-ACFDF825E33E","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59499","V-46635"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223080","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000516","id":"V-223080"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; 'Intranet Sites: Include all network paths (UNCs)' to 'Disabled'.   ","discussion":"Some UNC paths could refer to servers not managed by the organization, which means they could host malicious content; and therefore, it is safest to not include all UNC paths in the Intranet Sites zone. This policy setting controls whether URLs representing UNCs are mapped into the local Intranet security zone. If you enable this policy setting, all network paths are mapped into the Intranet Zone. If you disable this policy setting, network paths are not necessarily mapped into the Intranet Zone (other rules might map one there). If you do not configure this policy setting, users choose whether network paths are mapped into the Intranet Zone.","group_id_src":"V-223080"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223081r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Allow script-initiated windows without size or position constraints)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3\\2102'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI385-IE11","rule_title":"Script-initiated windows without size or position constraints must be disallowed (Internet zone).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:464"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Allow script-initiated windows without size or position constraints' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"2102\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223081r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B397E1B-6D7C-1014-9042-A1EE60534729","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59501","V-46637"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223081","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223081"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Allow script-initiated windows without size or position constraints' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box. ","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage restrictions on script-initiated pop-up windows and windows including the title and status bars. If you enable this policy setting, Windows Restrictions security will not apply in this zone. The security zone runs without the added layer of security provided by this feature. If you disable this policy setting, the possible harmful actions contained in script-initiated pop-up windows and windows including the title and status bars cannot be run. This Internet Explorer security feature will be on in this zone as dictated by the Scripted Windows Security Restrictions feature control setting for the process. If you do not configure this policy setting, the possible harmful actions contained in script-initiated pop-up windows and windows including the title and status bars cannot be run. This Internet Explorer security feature will be on in this zone as dictated by the Scripted Windows Security Restrictions feature control setting for the process.","group_id_src":"V-223081"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223082r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Allow script-initiated windows without size or position constraints)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\\2102'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI390-IE11","rule_title":"Script-initiated windows without size or position constraints must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:465"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow script-initiated windows without size or position constraints' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"2102\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223082r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B3983A3-6D7C-1014-A68D-E99E659F5709","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59503","V-46639"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223082","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223082"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow script-initiated windows without size or position constraints' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.  ","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage restrictions on script-initiated pop-up windows and windows including the title and status bars. If you enable this policy setting, Windows Restrictions security will not apply in this zone. The security zone runs without the added layer of security provided by this feature. If you disable this policy setting, the possible harmful actions contained in script-initiated pop-up windows and windows including the title and status bars cannot be run. This Internet Explorer security feature will be on in this zone as dictated by the Scripted Windows Security Restrictions feature control setting for the process. If you do not configure this policy setting, the possible harmful actions contained in script-initiated pop-up windows and windows including the title and status bars cannot be run. This Internet Explorer security feature will be on in this zone as dictated by the Scripted Windows Security Restrictions feature control setting for the process.","group_id_src":"V-223082"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223083r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Allow Scriptlets)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3\\1209'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI395-IE11","rule_title":"Scriptlets must be disallowed (Internet zone).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:466"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Allow Scriptlets' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"1209\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223083r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B398900-6D7C-1014-B258-FD90678F0B84","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59505","V-46641"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223083","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223083"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Allow Scriptlets' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box. ","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether scriptlets can be allowed. Scriptlets hosted on sites located in this zone are more likely to contain malicious code. If you enable this policy setting, users will be able to run scriptlets. If you disable this policy setting, users will not be able to run scriptlets. If you do not configure this policy setting, a scriptlet can be enabled or disabled by the user.","group_id_src":"V-223083"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223084r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Automatic prompting for file downloads)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3\\2200'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI415-IE11","rule_title":"Automatic prompting for file downloads must be disallowed (Internet zone).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:467"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Automatic prompting for file downloads' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"2200\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223084r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B398E3E-6D7C-1014-9966-C848B0E511D0","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59507","V-46643"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223084","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223084"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Automatic prompting for file downloads' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","discussion":"This policy setting determines whether users will be prompted for non user-initiated file downloads. Regardless of this setting, users will receive file download dialogs for user-initiated downloads. Users may accept downloads that they did not request, and those downloaded files may include malicious code. If you enable this setting, users will receive a file download dialog for automatic download attempts. If you disable or do not configure this setting, file downloads that are not user-initiated will be blocked, and users will see the information bar instead of the file download dialog. Users can then click the information bar to allow the file download prompt.","group_id_src":"V-223084"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223085r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Local Machine Zone\\Java permissions)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\0\\1C00'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI425-IE11","rule_title":"Java permissions must be disallowed (Local Machine zone).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:468"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Local Machine Zone -&gt; 'Java permissions' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable Java' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following keys: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\0 Criteria: If the value \"1C00\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223085r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B399590-6D7C-1014-A19D-902E1E4DB591","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59509","V-46645"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223085","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223085"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Local Machine Zone -&gt; 'Java permissions' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable Java' from the drop-down box.   ","discussion":"Java applications could contain malicious code. This policy setting allows you to manage permissions for Java applets. If you enable this policy setting, options can be chosen from the drop-down box. Use of the Custom permission will control permissions settings individually. Use of the Low Safety permission enables applets to perform all operations. Use of the Medium Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox (an area in memory outside of which the program cannot make calls), plus adds capabilities like scratch space (a safe and secure storage area on the client computer) and a user-controlled file I/O. Use of the High Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox. If you disable this policy setting, Java applets cannot run. If you do not configure this policy setting, the permission is set to High Safety.  ","group_id_src":"V-223085"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223086r961086","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Local Machine Zone Don't run antimalware programs against ActiveX controls)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\0\\270C'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI426-IE11","rule_title":"Anti-Malware programs against ActiveX controls must be run for the Local Machine zone.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:567"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-001662"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer-&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt;Local Machine Zone 'Don't run antimalware programs against ActiveX controls' must be 'Enabled' and 'Disable' selected in the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\0  Criteria: If the value \"270C\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223086r961086_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000207","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B399ADC-6D7C-1014-BAC2-B39119AFD0DE","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59869","V-47003"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223086","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000207","id":"V-223086"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer-&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Local Machine Zone 'Don't run antimalware programs against ActiveX controls' to 'Enabled' and select 'Disable' in the drop-down box.   ","discussion":"This policy setting determines whether Internet Explorer runs Anti-Malware programs against ActiveX controls, to check if they're safe to load on pages.      If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer won't check with your Anti-Malware program to see if it's safe to create an instance of the ActiveX control. If you disable this policy setting, Internet Explorer always checks with your Anti-Malware program to see if it's safe to create an instance of the ActiveX control. If you don't configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer won't check with your Anti-Malware program to see if it's safe to create an instance of the ActiveX control. Users can turn this behavior on or off, using Internet Explorer Security settings.","group_id_src":"V-223086"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223087r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Locked Down Local Machine Zone\\Java permissions)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Lockdown_Zones\\0\\1C00'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI430-IE11","rule_title":"Java permissions must be disallowed (Locked Down Local Machine zone).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:469"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Locked-Down Local Machine Zone -&gt; 'Java permissions' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable Java' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following keys: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Lockdown_Zones\\0 Criteria: If the value \"1C00\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223087r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B39A01F-6D7C-1014-9C24-BA99A655F59F","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59511","V-46647"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223087","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223087"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Locked-Down Local Machine Zone -&gt; 'Java permissions' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable Java' from the drop-down box.   ","discussion":"Java applications could contain malicious code. This policy setting allows you to manage permissions for Java applets. If you enable this policy setting, options can be chosen from the drop-down box. Use of the Custom permission will control permissions settings individually. Use of the Low Safety permission enables applets to perform all operations. Use of the Medium Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox (an area in memory outside of which the program cannot make calls), plus adds capabilities like scratch space (a safe and secure storage area on the client computer) and a user-controlled file I/O. Use of the High Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox. If you disable this policy setting, Java applets cannot run. If you do not configure this policy setting, the permission is set to High Safety.","group_id_src":"V-223087"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223088r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Locked Down Intranet Zone\\Java permissions)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Lockdown_Zones\\1\\1C00'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI435-IE11","rule_title":"Java permissions must be disallowed (Locked Down Intranet zone).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:470"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Locked-Down Intranet Zone -&gt; 'Java permissions' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable Java' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following keys: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Lockdown_Zones\\1 Criteria: If the value\" 1C00\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223088r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B39A557-6D7C-1014-AAFE-973152058DE0","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59513","V-46649"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223088","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223088"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Locked-Down Intranet Zone -&gt; 'Java permissions' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable Java' from the drop-down box.   ","discussion":"Java applications could contain malicious code. This policy setting allows you to manage permissions for Java applets. If you enable this policy setting, options can be chosen from the drop-down box. Use of the Custom permission will control permissions settings individually. Use of the Low Safety permission enables applets to perform all operations. Use of the Medium Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox (an area in memory outside of which the program cannot make calls), plus adds capabilities like scratch space (a safe and secure storage area on the client computer) and a user-controlled file I/O. Use of the High Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox. If you disable this policy setting, Java applets cannot run. If you do not configure this policy setting, the permission is set to High Safety.","group_id_src":"V-223088"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223089r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Locked Down Trusted Sites Zone\\Java permissions)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Lockdown_Zones\\2\\1C00'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI440-IE11","rule_title":"Java permissions must be disallowed (Locked Down Trusted Sites zone).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:471"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Locked-Down Trusted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Java permissions' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable Java' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following keys: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Lockdown_Zones\\2 Criteria: If the value \"1C00\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223089r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B39AB6E-6D7C-1014-B91E-EE8A9FC30354","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59517","V-46653"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223089","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223089"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Locked-Down Trusted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Java permissions' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable Java' from the drop-down box.   ","discussion":"Java applications could contain malicious code; sites located in this security zone are more likely to be hosted by malicious individuals. This policy setting allows you to manage permissions for Java applets. If you enable this policy setting, options can be chosen from the drop-down box. Use of the Custom permission will control permissions settings individually. Use of the Low Safety permission enables applets to perform all operations. Use of the Medium Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox (an area in memory outside of which the program cannot make calls), plus adds capabilities like scratch space (a safe and secure storage area on the client computer) and a user-controlled file I/O. Use of the High Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox. If you disable this policy setting, Java applets cannot run. If you do not configure this policy setting, the permission is set to High Safety. ","group_id_src":"V-223089"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223090r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Locked Down restricted Sites Zone\\Java permissions)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Lockdown_Zones\\4\\1C00'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI450-IE11","rule_title":"Java permissions must be disallowed (Locked Down Restricted Sites zone).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:473"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Locked-Down Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Java permissions' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable Java' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following keys: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Lockdown_Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1C00\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223090r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B39B184-6D7C-1014-A3A8-AE6D087146EA","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59527","V-46663"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223090","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223090"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Locked-Down Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Java permissions' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable Java' from the drop-down box.  ","discussion":"Java applications could contain malicious code. This policy setting allows you to manage permissions for Java applets. If you enable this policy setting, options can be chosen from the drop-down box. Use of the Custom permission will control permissions settings individually. Use of the Low Safety permission enables applets to perform all operations. Use of the Medium Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox (an area in memory outside of which the program cannot make calls), plus adds capabilities like scratch space (a safe and secure storage area on the client computer) and a user-controlled file I/O. Use of the High Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox. If you disable this policy setting, Java applets cannot run. If you do not configure this policy setting, the permission is set to High Safety. ","group_id_src":"V-223090"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223091r961863","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Loose or un-compiled XAML files)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3\\2402'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI455-IE11","rule_title":"XAML files must be disallowed (Internet zone).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:474"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Allow loading of XAML files' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"2402\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223091r961863_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B39B7A9-6D7C-1014-967B-F76D9FC12C7F","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59529","V-46665"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223091","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000516","id":"V-223091"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Allow loading of XAML files' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","discussion":"These are eXtensible Application Markup Language (XAML) files. XAML is an XML-based declarative markup language commonly used for creating rich user interfaces and graphics that leverage the Windows Presentation Foundation. If you enable this policy setting and the drop-down box is set to Enable, XAML files will be automatically loaded inside Internet Explorer. Users will not be able to change this behavior. If the drop-down box is set to Prompt, users will receive a prompt for loading XAML files. If you disable this policy setting, XAML files will not be loaded inside Internet Explorer. Users will not be able to change this behavior. If you do not configure this policy setting, users will have the freedom to decide whether to load XAML files inside Internet Explorer.","group_id_src":"V-223091"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223092r961863","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Loose XAML files)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\\2402'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI460-IE11","rule_title":"XAML files must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:475"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow loading of XAML files' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"2402\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223092r961863_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B39BCC5-6D7C-1014-9321-F1A638190E0D","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59533","V-46669"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223092","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000516","id":"V-223092"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow loading of XAML files' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","discussion":"These are eXtensible Application Markup Language (XAML) files. XAML is an XML-based declarative markup language commonly used for creating rich user interfaces and graphics that leverage the Windows Presentation Foundation. If you enable this policy setting and the drop-down box is set to Enable, XAML files will be automatically loaded inside Internet Explorer. Users will not be able to change this behavior. If the drop-down box is set to Prompt, users will receive a prompt for loading XAML files. If you disable this policy setting, XAML files will not be loaded inside Internet Explorer. Users will not be able to change this behavior. If you do not configure this policy setting, users will have the freedom to decide whether to load XAML files inside Internet Explorer.","group_id_src":"V-223092"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223093r961131","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Turn On Protected Mode)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3\\2500'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI485-IE11","rule_title":"Protected Mode must be enforced (Internet zone).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:480"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-001084"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Turn on Protected Mode' must be 'Enabled', and 'Enable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"2500\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223093r961131_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000233","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B39C1FC-6D7C-1014-9882-A472431CD96C","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59545","V-46681"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223093","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000233","id":"V-223093"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Turn on Protected Mode' to 'Enabled', and select 'Enable' from the drop-down box.   ","discussion":"Protected Mode protects Internet Explorer from exploited vulnerabilities by reducing the locations Internet Explorer can write to in the registry and the file system. If you enable this policy setting, Protected Mode will be turned on. Users will not be able to turn off Protected Mode. If you disable this policy setting, Protected Mode will be turned off. It will revert to Internet Explorer 6 behavior that allows for Internet Explorer to write to the registry and the file system. Users will not be able to turn on Protected Mode. If you do not configure this policy, users will be able to turn on or off Protected Mode.","group_id_src":"V-223093"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223094r961131","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Turn On Protected Mode)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\\2500'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI490-IE11","rule_title":"Protected Mode must be enforced (Restricted Sites zone).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:481"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-001084"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Turn on Protected Mode' must be 'Enabled', and 'Enable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"2500\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223094r961131_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000233","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B39C715-6D7C-1014-A654-F2557ED94496","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59549","V-46685"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223094","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000233","id":"V-223094"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Turn on Protected Mode' to 'Enabled' and select 'Enable', from the drop-down box.  ","discussion":"Protected Mode protects Internet Explorer from exploited vulnerabilities by reducing the locations Internet Explorer can write to in the registry and the file system. If you enable this policy setting, Protected Mode will be turned on. Users will not be able to turn off Protected Mode. If you disable this policy setting, Protected Mode will be turned off. It will revert to Internet Explorer 6 behavior that allows for Internet Explorer to write to the registry and the file system. Users will not be able to turn on Protected Mode. If you do not configure this policy, users will be able to turn on or off Protected Mode.","group_id_src":"V-223094"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223095r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Use Pop-up Blocker)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3\\1809'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI495-IE11","rule_title":"Pop-up Blocker must be enforced (Internet zone).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:482"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Use Pop-up Blocker' must be 'Enabled', and 'Enable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"1809\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223095r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B39CC41-6D7C-1014-B32C-F03DB4726304","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59553","V-46689"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223095","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223095"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Use Pop-up Blocker' to 'Enabled', and select 'Enable' from the drop-down box.  ","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether unwanted pop-up windows appear. Pop-up windows that are opened when the end user clicks a link are not blocked. If you enable this policy setting, most unwanted pop-up windows are prevented from appearing. If you disable this policy setting, pop-up windows are not prevented from appearing. If you do not configure this policy setting, most unwanted pop-up windows are prevented from appearing.","group_id_src":"V-223095"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223096r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Use Pop-up Blocker)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\\1809'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI500-IE11","rule_title":"Pop-up Blocker must be enforced (Restricted Sites zone).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:483"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Use Pop-up Blocker' must be 'Enabled', and 'Enable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1809\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223096r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B39D14E-6D7C-1014-B92C-F033C299C3BD","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59555","V-46691"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223096","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223096"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Use Pop-up Blocker' to 'Enabled', and select 'Enable' from the drop-down box. ","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether unwanted pop-up windows appear. Pop-up windows that are opened when the end user clicks a link are not blocked. If you enable this policy setting, most unwanted pop-up windows are prevented from appearing. If you disable this policy setting, pop-up windows are not prevented from appearing. If you do not configure this policy setting, most unwanted pop-up windows are prevented from appearing.","group_id_src":"V-223096"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223097r1117169","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Web sites in less privileged Web content zones can navigate into this zone)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3\\2101'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI515-IE11","rule_title":"Websites in less privileged web content zones must be prevented from navigating into the Internet zone.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:484"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-001414"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Web sites in less privileged Web content zones can navigate into this zone' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"2101\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223097r1117169_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000039","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B39DA63-6D7C-1014-B343-DEB87126DC4C","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59557","V-46693"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223097","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000039","id":"V-223097"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Web sites in less privileged Web content zones can navigate into this zone' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","discussion":"This policy setting allows a user to manage whether websites from less privileged zones, such as Restricted Sites, can navigate into the Internet zone. If this policy setting is enabled, websites from less privileged zones can open new windows in, or navigate into, this zone. The security zone will run without the added layer of security that is provided by the Protection from Zone Elevation security feature. If \"Prompt\" is selected in the drop-down box, a warning is issued to the user that potentially risky navigation is about to occur. If this policy setting is disabled, the potentially risky navigation is prevented. The Internet Explorer security feature will be on in this zone as set by the Protection from Zone Elevation feature control. If this policy setting is not configured, websites from less privileged zones can open new windows in, or navigate into, this zone.","group_id_src":"V-223097"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223098r1117169","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Web sites in less privileged Web content zones can navigate into this zone)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\\2101'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI520-IE11","rule_title":"Websites in less privileged web content zones must be prevented from navigating into the Restricted Sites zone.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:485"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-001414"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Web sites in less privileged Web content zones can navigate into this zone' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"2101\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223098r1117169_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000039","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B39E0CE-6D7C-1014-ABAC-8B6C435F4CAD","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59559","V-46695"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223098","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000039","id":"V-223098"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Web sites in less privileged Web content zones can navigate into this zone' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether websites from less privileged zones, such as Restricted Sites, can navigate into the Restricted zone. If this policy setting is enabled, websites from less privileged zones can open new windows in, or navigate into, this zone. The security zone will run without the added layer of security that is provided by the Protection from Zone Elevation security feature. If Prompt is selected in the drop-down box, a warning is issued to the user that potentially risky navigation is about to occur. If this policy setting is disabled, the potentially risky navigation is prevented. The Internet Explorer security feature will be on in this zone as set by the Protection from Zone Elevation feature control. If this policy setting is not configured, websites from less privileged zones can open new windows in, or navigate into, this zone.","group_id_src":"V-223098"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223099r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Allow binary and script behaviors)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\\2000'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI575-IE11","rule_title":"Allow binary and script behaviors must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:486"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow binary and script behaviors' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"2000\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223099r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B39E610-6D7C-1014-AD96-8C9B066A7B5F","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59565","V-46701"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223099","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223099"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow binary and script behaviors' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box. ","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage dynamic binary and script behaviors of components that encapsulate specific functionality for HTML elements, to which they were attached. If you enable this policy setting, binary and script behaviors are available.   If you select \"Administrator approved\" in the drop-down box, only the behaviors listed in the Admin-approved Behaviors under Binary Behaviors Security Restriction policy are available.    If you disable this policy setting, binary and script behaviors are not available unless applications have implemented a custom security manager. If you do not configure this policy setting, binary and script behaviors are available.","group_id_src":"V-223099"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223100r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Automatic prompting for file downloads)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\\2200'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI580-IE11","rule_title":"Automatic prompting for file downloads must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:487"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Automatic prompting for file downloads' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"2200\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223100r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B39EB2B-6D7C-1014-88D8-FB524811AEFF","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59569","V-46705"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223100","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223100"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Automatic prompting for file downloads' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","discussion":"This policy setting determines whether users will be prompted for non user-initiated file downloads. Regardless of this setting, users will receive file download dialogs for user-initiated downloads. Users may accept downloads that they did not request, and those downloaded files may include malicious code. If you enable this setting, users will receive a file download dialog for automatic download attempts. If you disable or do not configure this setting, file downloads that are not user-initiated will be blocked, and users will see the information bar instead of the file download dialog. Users can then click the information bar to allow the file download prompt.","group_id_src":"V-223100"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223101r961083","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Consistent Mime Handling\\Internet Explorer Processes)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_MIME_HANDLING\\(Reserved)'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI590-IE11","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for MIME handling must be enforced. (Reserved)","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:488"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-001166"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Consistent Mime Handling -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_MIME_HANDLING Criteria: If the value \"(Reserved)\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223101r961083_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000206","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B39F052-6D7C-1014-ACC6-9D2F3BAB6D9B","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59573","V-46709"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223101","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000206","id":"V-223101"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Consistent Mime Handling -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.  ","discussion":"Internet Explorer uses Multipurpose Internet Mail Extensions (MIME) data to determine file handling procedures for files received through a web server. The Consistent MIME Handling\\Internet Explorer Processes policy setting determines whether Internet Explorer requires all file-type information provided by web servers to be consistent. For example, if the MIME type of a file is text/plain but the MIME data indicates the file is really an executable file, Internet Explorer changes its extension to reflect this executable status. This capability helps ensure executable code cannot masquerade as other types of data that may be trusted. If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer examines all received files and enforces consistent MIME data for them. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer does not require consistent MIME data for all received files and will use the MIME data provided by the file. MIME file-type spoofing is a potential threat to an organization. Ensuring these files are consistent and properly labeled helps prevent malicious file downloads from infecting your network.","group_id_src":"V-223101"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223102r961083","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Consistent Mime Handling\\Internet Explorer Processes)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_MIME_HANDLING\\explorer.exe'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI592-IE11","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for MIME handling must be enforced (Explorer).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:502"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-001166"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Consistent Mime Handling -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_MIME_HANDLING Criteria: If the value \"explorer.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223102r961083_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000206","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B39F575-6D7C-1014-95CC-B1AB766B1105","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59575","V-46711"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223102","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000206","id":"V-223102"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Consistent Mime Handling -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   ","discussion":"Internet Explorer uses Multipurpose Internet Mail Extensions (MIME) data to determine file handling procedures for files received through a web server. The Consistent MIME Handling\\Internet Explorer Processes policy setting determines whether Internet Explorer requires all file-type information provided by web servers to be consistent. For example, if the MIME type of a file is text/plain but the MIME data indicates the file is really an executable file, Internet Explorer changes its extension to reflect this executable status. This capability helps ensure executable code cannot masquerade as other types of data that may be trusted. If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer examines all received files and enforces consistent MIME data for them. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer does not require consistent MIME data for all received files and will use the MIME data provided by the file. MIME file-type spoofing is a potential threat to the organization. Ensuring these files are consistent and properly labeled helps prevent malicious file downloads from infecting the network. This guide recommends configuring this policy as \"Enabled\" for all environments specified in this guide.","group_id_src":"V-223102"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223103r961083","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Consistent Mime Handling\\Internet Explorer Processes)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_MIME_HANDLING\\iexplore.exe'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI594-IE11","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for MIME handling must be enforced (iexplore).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:503"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-001166"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Consistent Mime Handling -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_MIME_HANDLING Criteria: If the value \"iexplore.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223103r961083_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000206","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B39FB04-6D7C-1014-BA75-AE03E7EB2DCE","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59577","V-46713"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223103","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000206","id":"V-223103"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Consistent Mime Handling -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   ","discussion":"Internet Explorer uses Multipurpose Internet Mail Extensions (MIME) data to determine file handling procedures for files received through a web server. The Consistent MIME Handling\\Internet Explorer Processes policy setting determines whether Internet Explorer requires all file-type information provided by web servers to be consistent. For example, if the MIME type of a file is text/plain but the MIME data indicates that the file is really an executable file, Internet Explorer changes its extension to reflect this executable status. This capability helps ensure that executable code cannot masquerade as other types of data that may be trusted. If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer examines all received files and enforces consistent MIME data for them. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer does not require consistent MIME data for all received files and will use the MIME data provided by the file. MIME file-type spoofing is a potential threat to an organization. Ensuring these files are consistent and properly labeled helps prevent malicious file downloads from infecting the network. This guide recommends configuring this policy as \"Enabled\" for all environments specified in this guide.","group_id_src":"V-223103"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223104r961083","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Mime Sniffing Safety Feature\\Internet Explorer Processes)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_MIME_SNIFFING\\(Reserved)'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI595-IE11","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for MIME sniffing must be enforced (Reserved).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:489"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-001166"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Mime Sniffing Safety Feature -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_MIME_SNIFFING Criteria: If the value \"(Reserved)\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223104r961083_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000206","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B3A002C-6D7C-1014-92BC-DC77B1A15BB1","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59579","V-46715"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223104","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000206","id":"V-223104"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Mime Sniffing Safety Feature -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   ","discussion":"MIME sniffing is the process of examining the content of a MIME file to determine its context - whether it is a data file, an executable file, or some other type of file. This policy setting determines whether Internet Explorer MIME sniffing will prevent promotion of a file of one type to a more dangerous file type. When set to \"Enabled\", MIME sniffing will never promote a file of one type to a more dangerous file type. Disabling MIME sniffing configures Internet Explorer processes to allow a MIME sniff that promotes a file of one type to a more dangerous file type. For example, promoting a text file to an executable file is a dangerous promotion because any code in the supposed text file would be executed. MIME file-type spoofing is a potential threat to an organization. Ensuring these files are consistently handled helps prevent malicious file downloads from infecting the network. This guide recommends you configure this policy as \"Enabled\" for all environments specified in this guide. Note: This setting works in conjunction with, but does not replace, the Consistent MIME Handling settings.","group_id_src":"V-223104"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223105r961083","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Mime Sniffing Safety Feature\\Internet Explorer Processes must be Enabled)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_MIME_SNIFFING\\explorer.exe'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI596-IE11","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for MIME sniffing must be enforced (Explorer).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:510"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-001166"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Mime Sniffing Safety Feature -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_MIME_SNIFFING Criteria: If the value \"explorer.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223105r961083_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000206","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B3A05BA-6D7C-1014-86D6-ABE76CC5853E","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","p