plorer Processes must be Enabled)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_MIME_SNIFFING\\iexplore.exe'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI597-IE11","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for MIME sniffing must be enforced (iexplore).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:511"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-001166"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Mime Sniffing Safety Feature -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_MIME_SNIFFING Criteria: If the value \"iexplore.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223106r961083_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000206","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B3A0ABF-6D7C-1014-84A9-D3EC237E4772","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59583","V-46719"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223106","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000206","id":"V-223106"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Mime Sniffing Safety Feature -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   ","discussion":"MIME sniffing is the process of examining the content of a MIME file to determine its context - whether it is a data file, an executable file, or some other type of file. This policy setting determines whether Internet Explorer MIME sniffing will prevent promotion of a file of one type to a more dangerous file type. When set to \"Enabled\", MIME sniffing will never promote a file of one type to a more dangerous file type. Disabling MIME sniffing configures Internet Explorer processes to allow a MIME sniff that promotes a file of one type to a more dangerous file type. For example, promoting a text file to an executable file is a dangerous promotion because any code in the supposed text file would be executed. MIME file-type spoofing is a potential threat to an organization. Ensuring these files are consistently handled helps prevent malicious file downloads from infecting the network. This guide recommends configuring this policy as \"Enabled\" for all environments specified in this guide. Note: This setting works in conjunction with, but does not replace, the Consistent MIME Handling settings.","group_id_src":"V-223106"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223107r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\MK Protocol Security Restriction\\Internet Explorer Processes)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_DISABLE_MK_PROTOCOL\\(Reserved)'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI599-IE11","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for MK protocol must be enforced (Reserved).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:504"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; MK Protocol Security Restriction -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_DISABLE_MK_PROTOCOL Criteria: If the value \"(Reserved)\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223107r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B3A0FBC-6D7C-1014-89FB-EA0A003606F1","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59585","V-46721"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223107","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223107"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; MK Protocol Security Restriction -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   ","discussion":"The MK Protocol Security Restriction policy setting reduces attack surface area by blocking the seldom used MK protocol. Some older web applications use the MK protocol to retrieve information from compressed files. Because the MK protocol is not widely used, it should be blocked wherever it is not needed. Setting this policy to \"Enabled\"; blocks the MK protocol for Windows Explorer and Internet Explorer, which causes resources that use the MK protocol to fail. Disabling this setting allows applications to use the MK protocol API. This guide recommends configuring this setting to \"Enabled\" to block the MK protocol unless it is specifically needed in the environment. Note: Because resources that use the MK protocol will fail when deploying this setting, ensure none of the applications use the MK protocol.","group_id_src":"V-223107"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223108r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\MK Protocol Security Restriction\\Internet Explorer Processes)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_DISABLE_MK_PROTOCOL\\explorer.exe'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI600-IE11","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for MK protocol must be enforced (Explorer).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:490"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; MK Protocol Security Restriction -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_DISABLE_MK_PROTOCOL Criteria: If the value \"explorer.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223108r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B3A14E1-6D7C-1014-9613-AB447B427C8A","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59587","V-46723"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223108","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223108"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; MK Protocol Security Restriction -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   ","discussion":"The MK Protocol Security Restriction policy setting reduces attack surface area by blocking the seldom used MK protocol. Some older web applications use the MK protocol to retrieve information from compressed files. Because the MK protocol is not widely used, it should be blocked wherever it is not needed. Setting this policy to \"Enabled\"; blocks the MK protocol for Windows Explorer and Internet Explorer, which causes resources that use the MK protocol to fail. Disabling this setting allows applications to use the MK protocol API. This guide recommends you configure this setting to \"Enabled\" to block the MK protocol unless it is specifically needed in the environment. Note: Because resources that use the MK protocol will fail when deploying this setting, ensure none of the applications use the MK protocol.","group_id_src":"V-223108"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223109r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\MK Protocol Security Restriction\\Internet Explorer Processes)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_DISABLE_MK_PROTOCOL\\iexplore.exe'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI605-IE11","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for MK protocol must be enforced (iexplore).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:491"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; MK Protocol Security Restriction -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_DISABLE_MK_PROTOCOL Criteria: If the value \"iexplore.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223109r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B3A1BFA-6D7C-1014-9451-983A634ECCE5","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59589","V-46725"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223109","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223109"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; MK Protocol Security Restriction -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'. ","discussion":"The MK Protocol Security Restriction policy setting reduces attack surface area by blocking the seldom used MK protocol. Some older web applications use the MK protocol to retrieve information from compressed files. Because the MK protocol is not widely used, it should be blocked wherever it is not needed. Setting this policy to \"Enabled\"; blocks the MK protocol for Windows Explorer and Internet Explorer, which causes resources that use the MK protocol to fail. Disabling this setting allows applications to use the MK protocol API. This guide recommends you configure this setting to \"Enabled\" to block the MK protocol unless specifically needed in the environment. Note: Because resources that use the MK protocol will fail when deploying this setting, ensure none of the applications use the MK protocol.","group_id_src":"V-223109"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223110r961131","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Protection From Zone Elevation\\Internet Explorer Processes)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_ZONE_ELEVATION\\(Reserved)'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI610-IE11","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for Zone Elevation must be enforced (Reserved).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:492"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-001084"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Protection From Zone Elevation -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'.  Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_ZONE_ELEVATION Criteria: If the value \"(Reserved)\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223110r961131_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000233","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B3A22DF-6D7C-1014-8DF4-E50E7F2BE0A3","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59591","V-46727"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223110","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000233","id":"V-223110"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Protection From Zone Elevation -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   ","discussion":"Internet Explorer places restrictions on each web page it opens that are dependent upon the location of the web page (such as Internet Zone, Intranet Zone, or Local Machine Zone). Web pages on a local computer have the fewest security restrictions and reside in the Local Machine Zone, which makes the Local Machine Security Zone a prime target for malicious attackers. If you enable this policy setting, any zone can be protected from zone elevation by Internet Explorer processes. This approach stops content running in one zone from gaining the elevated privileges of another zone. If you disable this policy setting, no zone receives such protection from Internet Explorer processes. Because of the severity and relative frequency of zone elevation attacks, this guide recommends that you configure this setting as \"Enabled\" in all environments.","group_id_src":"V-223110"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223111r961131","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Protection From Zone Elevation\\Internet Explorer Processes)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_ZONE_ELEVATION\\explorer.exe'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI612-IE11","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for Zone Elevation must be enforced (Explorer).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:505"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-001084"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Protection From Zone Elevation -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_ZONE_ELEVATION Criteria: If the value \"explorer.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223111r961131_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000233","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B3A28EB-6D7C-1014-B023-C46BFB6E7A60","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59593","V-46729"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223111","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000233","id":"V-223111"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Protection From Zone Elevation -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   ","discussion":"Internet Explorer places restrictions on each web page it opens that are dependent upon the location of the web page (such as Internet Zone, Intranet Zone, or Local Machine Zone). Web pages on a local computer have the fewest security restrictions and reside in the Local Machine Zone, which makes the Local Machine Security Zone a prime target for malicious attackers. If you enable this policy setting, any zone can be protected from zone elevation by Internet Explorer processes. This approach stops content running in one zone from gaining the elevated privileges of another zone. If you disable this policy setting, no zone receives such protection from Internet Explorer processes. Because of the severity and relative frequency of zone elevation attacks, this guide recommends configuring this setting as \"Enabled\" in all environments.","group_id_src":"V-223111"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223112r961131","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Protection From Zone Elevation\\Internet Explorer Processes)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_ZONE_ELEVATION\\iexplore.exe'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI614-IE11","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for Zone Elevation must be enforced (iexplore).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:506"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-001084"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Protection From Zone Elevation -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_ZONE_ELEVATION Criteria: If the value \"iexplore.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223112r961131_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000233","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B3A2EEE-6D7C-1014-97C0-CC1595DC5CAE","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59595","V-46731"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223112","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000233","id":"V-223112"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Protection From Zone Elevation -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   ","discussion":"Internet Explorer places restrictions on each web page it opens that are dependent upon the location of the web page (such as Internet Zone, Intranet Zone, or Local Machine Zone). Web pages on a local computer have the fewest security restrictions and reside in the Local Machine Zone, which makes the Local Machine Security Zone a prime target for malicious attackers. If you enable this policy setting, any zone can be protected from zone elevation by Internet Explorer processes. This approach stops content running in one zone from gaining the elevated privileges of another zone. If you disable this policy setting, no zone receives such protection from Internet Explorer processes. Because of the severity and relative frequency of zone elevation attacks, this guide recommends that you configure this setting as \"Enabled\" in all environments.","group_id_src":"V-223112"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223113r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\ Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Restrict File Download\\Internet Explorer Processes)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_RESTRICT_FILEDOWNLOAD\\(Reserved)'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI630-IE11","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for Restrict File Download must be enforced (Reserved).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:493"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Restrict File Download -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_RESTRICT_FILEDOWNLOAD Criteria: If the value \"(Reserved)\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223113r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B3A34C2-6D7C-1014-8421-A89990903FE3","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59597","V-46733"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223113","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223113"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Restrict File Download -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   ","discussion":"In certain circumstances, websites can initiate file download prompts without interaction from users. This technique can allow websites to put unauthorized files on users' hard drives if they click the wrong button and accept the download. If you configure the Restrict File Download\\Internet Explorer Processes policy setting to \"Enabled\", file download prompts that are not user-initiated are blocked for Internet Explorer processes. If you configure this policy setting as \"Disabled\", prompting will occur for file downloads that are not user-initiated for Internet Explorer processes. Note: This setting is configured as \"Enabled\" in all environments specified in this guide to help prevent attackers from placing arbitrary code on users' computers.","group_id_src":"V-223113"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223114r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Restrict File Download\\Internet Explorer Processes)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_RESTRICT_FILEDOWNLOAD\\explorer.exe'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI635-IE11","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for Restrict File Download must be enforced (Explorer).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:494"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Restrict File Download -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_RESTRICT_FILEDOWNLOAD Criteria: If the value \"explorer.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223114r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B3A3A56-6D7C-1014-AC42-BD92D33E7656","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59645","V-46779"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223114","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223114"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Restrict File Download -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.  ","discussion":"In certain circumstances, websites can initiate file download prompts without interaction from users. This technique can allow websites to put unauthorized files on users' hard drives if they click the wrong button and accept the download. If you configure the Restrict File Download\\Internet Explorer Processes policy setting to \"Enabled\", file download prompts that are not user-initiated are blocked for Internet Explorer processes. If you configure this policy setting as \"Disabled\", prompting will occur for file downloads that are not user-initiated for Internet Explorer processes. Note: This setting is configured as \"Enabled\" in all environments specified in this guide to help prevent attackers from placing arbitrary code on users' computers.","group_id_src":"V-223114"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223115r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Restrict File Download\\Internet Explorer Processes)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_RESTRICT_FILEDOWNLOAD\\iexplore.exe'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI640-IE11","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for Restrict File Download must be enforced (iexplore).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:495"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Restrict File Download -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_RESTRICT_FILEDOWNLOAD Criteria: If the value \"iexplore.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223115r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B3A3FFC-6D7C-1014-A742-F66903E9A60E","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59647","V-46781"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223115","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223115"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Restrict File Download -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   ","discussion":"In certain circumstances, websites can initiate file download prompts without interaction from users. This technique can allow websites to put unauthorized files on users' hard drives if they click the wrong button and accept the download. If you configure the Restrict File Download\\Internet Explorer Processes policy setting to \"Enabled\", file download prompts that are not user-initiated are blocked for Internet Explorer processes. If you configure this policy setting as \"Disabled\", prompting will occur for file downloads that are not user-initiated for Internet Explorer processes. Note: This setting is configured as \"Enabled\" in all environments specified in this guide to help prevent attackers from placing arbitrary code on users' computers.","group_id_src":"V-223115"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223116r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Scripted Window Security Restrictions\\Internet Explorer Processes)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_WINDOW_RESTRICTIONS\\(Reserved)'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI645-IE11","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for restricting pop-up windows must be enforced (Reserved).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:496"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Scripted Window Security Restrictions -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_WINDOW_RESTRICTIONS Criteria: If the value \"(Reserved)\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223116r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B3A460A-6D7C-1014-AA8F-9D55D8D17342","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59653","V-46787"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223116","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223116"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Scripted Window Security Restrictions -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'. ","discussion":"Internet Explorer allows scripts to programmatically open, resize, and reposition various types of windows. Often, disreputable websites will resize windows to either hide other windows or force the user to interact with a window containing malicious code. The Scripted Window Security Restrictions security feature restricts pop-up windows and prohibits scripts from displaying windows in which the title and status bars are not visible to the user, or which hide other windows' title and status bars. If you enable the Scripted Window Security Restrictions\\Internet Explorer Processes policy setting, pop-up windows and other restrictions apply for Windows Explorer and Internet Explorer processes. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, scripts can continue to create pop-up windows, and create windows that hide other windows. Recommend configuring this setting to \"Enabled\" to help prevent malicious websites from controlling the Internet Explorer windows or fooling users into clicking on the wrong window.","group_id_src":"V-223116"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223117r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Scripted Window Security Restrictions\\Internet Explorer Processes)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_WINDOW_RESTRICTIONS\\explorer.exe'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI647-IE11","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for restricting pop-up windows must be enforced (Explorer).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:507"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Scripted Window Security Restrictions -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_WINDOW_RESTRICTIONS Criteria: If the value \"explorer.exe is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223117r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B3A4C06-6D7C-1014-986E-FF07C2F3C3FF","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59655","V-46789"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223117","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223117"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Scripted Window Security Restrictions -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.  ","discussion":"Internet Explorer allows scripts to programmatically open, resize, and reposition various types of windows. Often, disreputable websites will resize windows to either hide other windows or force a user to interact with a window that contains malicious code. The Scripted Window Security Restrictions security feature restricts pop-up windows and prohibits scripts from displaying windows in which the title and status bars are not visible to the user, or which hide other windows' title and status bars. If you enable the Scripted Window Security Restrictions\\Internet Explorer Processes policy setting, pop-up windows and other restrictions apply for Windows Explorer and Internet Explorer processes. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, scripts can continue to create pop-up windows and create windows that hide other windows. This guide recommends configuring this setting to \"Enabled\" to help prevent malicious websites from controlling the Internet Explorer windows or fooling users into clicking on the wrong window.","group_id_src":"V-223117"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223118r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Scripted Window Security Restrictions\\Internet Explorer Processes)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_WINDOW_RESTRICTIONS\\iexplore.exe'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI649-IE11","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for restricting pop-up windows must be enforced (iexplore).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:508"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Scripted Window Security Restrictions -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_WINDOW_RESTRICTIONS Criteria: If the value \"iexplore.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223118r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B3A51B5-6D7C-1014-A969-AFBC9A9E1F95","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59657","V-46791"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223118","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223118"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Scripted Window Security Restrictions -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   ","discussion":"Internet Explorer allows scripts to programmatically open, resize, and reposition various types of windows. Often, disreputable websites will resize windows to either hide other windows or force a user to interact with a window that contains malicious code. The Scripted Window Security Restrictions security feature restricts pop-up windows and prohibits scripts from displaying windows in which the title and status bars are not visible to the user, or which hide other windows' title and status bars. If you enable the Scripted Window Security Restrictions\\Internet Explorer Processes policy setting, pop-up windows and other restrictions apply for Windows Explorer and Internet Explorer processes. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, scripts can continue to create pop-up windows and create windows that hide other windows. This guide recommends configuring this setting to \"Enabled\" to help prevent malicious websites from controlling the Internet Explorer windows or fooling users into clicking on the wrong window.","group_id_src":"V-223118"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223119r961863","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Run .NET Framework-reliant components not signed with Authenticode)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\\2004'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI650-IE11","rule_title":".NET Framework-reliant components not signed with Authenticode must be disallowed to run (Restricted Sites Zone).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:497"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Run .NET Framework-reliant components not signed with Authenticode' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"2004\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223119r961863_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B3A5700-6D7C-1014-A0DE-B5C67A7E86EE","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59663","V-46797"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223119","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000516","id":"V-223119"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Run .NET Framework-reliant components not signed with Authenticode' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether .NET Framework-reliant components that are not signed with Authenticode can be executed from Internet Explorer. These components include managed controls referenced from an object tag and managed executables referenced from a link. If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will execute unsigned managed components. If you select \"Prompt\" in the drop-down box, Internet Explorer will prompt the user to determine whether to execute unsigned managed components. If you disable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will not execute unsigned managed components. If you do not configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer will execute unsigned managed components.","group_id_src":"V-223119"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223120r961863","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Run .NET Framework-reliant components signed with Authenticode)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\\2001'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI655-IE11","rule_title":".NET Framework-reliant components signed with Authenticode must be disallowed to run (Restricted Sites Zone).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:498"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Run .NET Framework-reliant components signed with Authenticode' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"2001\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223120r961863_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B3A5EEF-6D7C-1014-8CBE-84055C639B4C","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59665","V-46799"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223120","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000516","id":"V-223120"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Run .NET Framework-reliant components signed with Authenticode' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether .NET Framework-reliant components that are signed with Authenticode can be executed from Internet Explorer. It may be possible for malicious content hosted on a website to take advantage of these components. These components include managed controls referenced from an object tag and managed executables referenced from a link. If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will execute signed managed components. If you select \"Prompt\" in the drop-down box, Internet Explorer will prompt the user to determine whether to execute signed managed components. If you disable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will not execute signed managed components. If you do not configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer will execute signed managed components.","group_id_src":"V-223120"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223121r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Scripting of Java applets)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\\1402'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI670-IE11","rule_title":"Scripting of Java applets must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:499"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Scripting of Java applets' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1402\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223121r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B3A65B5-6D7C-1014-9E12-D56D1E85078A","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59667","V-46801"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223121","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223121"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Scripting of Java applets' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box. ","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether applets are exposed to scripts within the zone. If you enable this policy setting, scripts can access applets automatically without user intervention. If you select \"Prompt\" in the drop-down box, users are queried to choose whether to allow scripts to access applets. If you disable this policy setting, scripts are prevented from accessing applets. If you do not configure this policy setting, scripts can access applets automatically without user intervention. ","group_id_src":"V-223121"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223122r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (AutoComplete feature for forms must be disallowed.)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\Use FormSuggest'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n                :        For 'MAXHEALTH\\katessem.admin':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\Use FormSuggest'.  \n                :        For 'MAXHEALTH\\katessem':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\Use FormSuggest'.  \n                :        For 'MHL-PW06M2V2\\Administrator':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\Use FormSuggest'.  \n","rule_version":"DTBI690-IE11","rule_title":"AutoComplete feature for forms must be disallowed.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.ie:def:223122"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for User Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; 'Disable AutoComplete for forms' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKCU\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main Criteria: If the value \"Use FormSuggest\" is REG_SZ = no, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223122r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B3A6B51-6D7C-1014-882D-E3B177CDDFE7","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59673","V-46807"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223122","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223122"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; 'Disable AutoComplete for forms' to 'Enabled'.   ","discussion":"This AutoComplete feature suggests possible matches when users are filling in forms. It is possible that this feature will cache sensitive data and store it in the user's profile, where it might not be protected as rigorously as required by organizational policy. If you enable this setting, the user is not presented with suggested matches when filling in forms. If you disable this setting, the user is presented with suggested possible matches when filling forms. If you do not configure this setting, the user has the freedom to turn on the auto-complete feature for forms. To display this option, the user opens the Internet Options dialog box, clicks the \"Contents\" tab, and clicks the \"Settings\" button.","group_id_src":"V-223122"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223123r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Turn Off Crash Detection)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Restrictions\\NoCrashDetection'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI715-IE11","rule_title":"Crash Detection management must be enforced.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:509"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; 'Turn off Crash Detection' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Restrictions Criteria: If the value \"NoCrashDetection\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223123r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B3A70D8-6D7C-1014-98C4-CB0F6A19F4D5","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59677","V-46811"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223123","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223123"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; 'Turn off Crash Detection' to 'Enabled'.   ","discussion":"The 'Turn off Crash Detection' policy setting allows you to manage the crash detection feature of add-on management in Internet Explorer. A crash report could contain sensitive information from the computer's memory. If you enable this policy setting, a crash in Internet Explorer will be similar to one on a computer running Windows XP Professional Service Pack 1 and earlier, where Windows Error Reporting will be invoked. If you disable this policy setting, the crash detection feature in add-on management will be functional. ","group_id_src":"V-223123"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223124r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Turn on the auto-complete feature for user names and passwords on forms must be disabled.)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FormSuggest PW Ask'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n                :        For 'MAXHEALTH\\katessem.admin':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FormSuggest PW Ask'.  \n                :        For 'MAXHEALTH\\katessem':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FormSuggest PW Ask'.  \n                :        For 'MHL-PW06M2V2\\Administrator':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FormSuggest PW Ask'.  \n","rule_version":"DTBI725-IE11","rule_title":"Turn on the auto-complete feature for user names and passwords on forms must be disabled.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.ie:def:223124"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for User Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; 'Turn on the auto-complete feature for user names and passwords on forms' must be 'Disabled'. \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKCU\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main Criteria: If the value \"FormSuggest Passwords\" is REG_SZ = 'no', this is not a finding. AND Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKCU\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main Criteria: If the value \"FormSuggest PW Ask\" is REG_SZ = 'no', this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223124r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B3A7637-6D7C-1014-BEBC-AC1B3EA78B37","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59681","V-46815"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223124","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223124"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; 'Turn on the auto-complete feature for user names and passwords on forms' to 'Disabled'.   ","discussion":"This policy setting controls automatic completion of fields in forms on web pages. It is possible that malware could be developed which would be able to extract the cached user names and passwords from the currently logged on user, which an attacker could then use to compromise that user's online accounts.  If you enable this setting, the user cannot change the 'User name and passwords on forms' or 'prompt me to save passwords'. The Auto Complete feature for\" User names and passwords on forms\" will be turned on. If you disable this setting, the user cannot change the 'User name and passwords on forms' or 'prompt me to save passwords'. The Auto Complete feature for \"User names and passwords on forms\" is turned off. The user also cannot opt to be prompted to save passwords. If you do not configure this setting, the user has the freedom of turning on Auto Complete for \"User name and passwords on forms\", and the option of prompting to save passwords.","group_id_src":"V-223124"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223125r961083","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Prevent Managing SmartScreen Filter)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\PhishingFilter\\EnabledV9'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI740-IE11","rule_title":"Managing SmartScreen Filter use must be enforced.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:514"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-001166"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"If the system is on the SIPRNet, this requirement is NA.\n\nThe policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; \"Prevent Managing SmartScreen Filter\" must be \"Enabled\", and \"On\" selected from the drop-down box. \n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\PhishingFilter \n\nCriteria: If the value \"EnabledV9\" is \"REG_DWORD = 1\", this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223125r961083_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000206","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B3A7B6C-6D7C-1014-B84E-9277B78FC5CB","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59685","V-46819"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223125","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000206","id":"V-223125"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"If the system is on the SIPRNet, this requirement is NA.\n\nSet the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; \"Prevent Managing SmartScreen Filter\" to \"Enabled\", and select \"On\" from the drop-down box.","discussion":"This setting is important from a security perspective because Microsoft has extensive data illustrating the positive impact the SmartScreen filter has had on reducing the risk of malware infection via visiting malicious websites. This policy setting allows users to enable the SmartScreen Filter, which will warn if the website being visited is known for fraudulent attempts to gather personal information through 'phishing' or is known to host malware. If you enable this setting the user will not be prompted to enable the SmartScreen Filter. It must be specified which mode the SmartScreen Filter uses: On or Off. If the feature is On, all website addresses not contained on the filters allow list, will be sent automatically to Microsoft without prompting the user. If this feature is set to Off, the feature will not run. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, the user is prompted to decide whether to turn on SmartScreen Filter during the first-run experience.","group_id_src":"V-223125"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223126r960879","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Delete Browsing History\\Configure Delete Browsing History on exit)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Privacy\\ClearBrowsingHistoryOnExit'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI760-IE11","rule_title":"Browser must retain history on exit.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:516"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000169"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Delete Browsing History -&gt; 'Allow deleting browsing history on exit' must be 'Disabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Privacy Criteria: If the value \"ClearBrowsingHistoryOnExit\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223126r960879_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000089","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B3A8112-6D7C-1014-B11C-A077D419C06C","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59695","V-46829"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223126","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000089","id":"V-223126"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Delete Browsing History -&gt; 'Allow deleting browsing history on exit' to 'Disabled'.   ","discussion":"Delete Browsing History on exit automatically deletes specified items when the last browser window closes.  Disabling this function will prevent users from deleting their browsing history, which could be used to identify malicious websites and files that could later be used for anti-virus and Intrusion Detection System (IDS) signatures.  Furthermore, preventing users from deleting browsing history could be used to identify abusive web surfing on government systems.","group_id_src":"V-223126"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223127r960879","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Delete Browsing History\\Prevent Deleting Web sites that the User has Visited)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Privacy\\CleanHistory'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI770-IE11","rule_title":"Deleting websites that the user has visited must be disallowed.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:517"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000169"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Delete Browsing History -&gt; 'Prevent Deleting Web sites that the User has Visited' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Privacy Criteria: If the value \"CleanHistory\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223127r960879_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000089","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B3A8646-6D7C-1014-9E55-9E7C63DC9AFE","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59707","V-46841"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223127","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000089","id":"V-223127"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Delete Browsing History -&gt; 'Prevent Deleting Web sites that the User has Visited' to 'Enabled'.   ","discussion":"This policy prevents users from deleting the history of websites the user has visited. If you enable this policy setting, websites the user has visited will be preserved when the user clicks \"Delete\". If you disable this policy setting, websites that the user has visited will be deleted when the user clicks \"Delete\". If you do not configure this policy setting, the user will be able to select whether to delete or preserve websites the user visited when the user clicks \"Delete\".","group_id_src":"V-223127"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223128r960864","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\InPrivate\\Turn off InPrivate Browsing)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Privacy\\EnableInPrivateBrowsing'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI780-IE11","rule_title":"InPrivate Browsing must be disallowed.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:518"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000166"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Privacy -&gt; 'Turn off InPrivate Browsing' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Privacy Criteria: If the value \"EnableInPrivateBrowsing\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223128r960864_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000080","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B3A8BD0-6D7C-1014-B730-C82EB9BB4BB6","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59713","V-46847"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223128","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000080","id":"V-223128"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Privacy -&gt; 'Turn off InPrivate Browsing' to 'Enabled'.   ","discussion":"InPrivate Browsing lets the user control whether or not Internet Explorer saves the browsing history, cookies, and other data. User control of settings is not the preferred control method. The InPrivate Browsing feature in Internet Explorer makes browser privacy easy by not storing history, cookies, temporary Internet files, or other data. If you enable this policy setting, InPrivate Browsing will be disabled. If you disable this policy setting, InPrivate Browsing will be available for use. If you do not configure this setting, InPrivate Browsing can be turned on or off through the registry.","group_id_src":"V-223128"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223129r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Allow scripting of Internet Explorer web browser control)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3\\1206'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI800-IE11","rule_title":"Scripting of Internet Explorer WebBrowser control property must be disallowed (Internet zone).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:519"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Allow scripting of Internet Explorer WebBrowser controls' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"1206\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223129r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B3A9111-6D7C-1014-94BB-D5A2B9E9A826","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59715","V-46849"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223129","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223129"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Allow scripting of Internet Explorer WebBrowser controls' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether a page may control embedded WebBrowser control via script. Scripted code hosted on sites located in this zone is more likely to contain malicious code. If you enable this policy setting, script access to the WebBrowser control is allowed. If you disable this policy setting, script access to the WebBrowser control is not allowed. If you do not configure this policy setting, script access to the WebBrowser control can be enabled or disabled by the user. By default, script access to the WebBrowser control is only allowed in the Local Machine and Intranet Zones.","group_id_src":"V-223129"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223130r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Include local directory path when uploading files to a server)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3\\160A'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI810-IE11","rule_title":"When uploading files to a server, the local directory path must be excluded (Internet zone).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:520"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Include local path when user is uploading files to a server' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"160A\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223130r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B3A96D1-6D7C-1014-A6B6-F315C3949085","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59719","V-46853"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223130","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223130"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Include local path when user is uploading files to a server' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.  ","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether or not the local path information will be sent when uploading a file via a HTML form. If the local path information is sent, some information may be unintentionally revealed to the server. If you do not configure this policy setting, the user can choose whether path information will be sent when uploading a file via a form. By default, path information will be sent.","group_id_src":"V-223130"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223131r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Notification Bar\\Internet Explorer Processes)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_SECURITYBAND\\(Reserved)'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI815-IE11","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for Notification Bars must be enforced (Reserved).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:541"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features-&gt; Notification Bar-&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_SECURITYBAND Criteria: If the value \"(Reserved)\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223131r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B3A9C33-6D7C-1014-8821-A08136CFBE6C","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59723","V-46857"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223131","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223131"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features-&gt; Notification Bar-&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   ","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether the Notification Bar is displayed for Internet Explorer processes when file or code installs are restricted. By default, the Notification Bar is displayed for Internet Explorer processes. If you enable this policy setting, the Notification Bar will be displayed for Internet Explorer processes. If you disable this policy setting, the Notification Bar will not be displayed for Internet Explorer processes. If you do not configure this policy setting, the Notification Bar will be displayed for Internet Explorer processes.","group_id_src":"V-223131"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223132r961863","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Launching programs and unsafe files)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3\\1806'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI820-IE11","rule_title":"Security Warning for unsafe files must be set to prompt (Internet zone).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:521"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Show security warning for potentially unsafe files' must be 'Enabled', and 'Prompt' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"1806\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223132r961863_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B3AA1BC-6D7C-1014-983D-F8BDA2EF7683","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59725","V-46859"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223132","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000516","id":"V-223132"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Show security warning for potentially unsafe files' to 'Enabled', and select 'Prompt' from the drop-down box.   ","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether or not the 'Open File - Security Warning' message appears when the user tries to open executable files or other potentially unsafe files (from an intranet file shared by using Windows Explorer, for example). If you enable this policy setting and set the drop-down box to \"Enable\", these files open without a security warning. If you set the drop-down box to \" Prompt\", a security warning appears before the files open. If you disable this policy these files do not open. If you do not configure this policy setting, the user can configure how the computer handles these files.","group_id_src":"V-223132"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223133r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Notification Bar\\Internet Explorer Processes)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_SECURITYBAND\\explorer.exe'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI825-IE11","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for Notification Bars must be enforced (Explorer).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:542"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features-&gt; Notification Bar-&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_SECURITYBAND Criteria: If the value \"explorer.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223133r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B3AA6FF-6D7C-1014-9B83-8FBA3FC24BE4","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59727","V-46861"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223133","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223133"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features-&gt; Notification Bar-&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'. ","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether the Notification Bar is displayed for Internet Explorer processes when file or code installs are restricted. By default, the Notification Bar is displayed for Internet Explorer processes. If you enable this policy setting, the Notification Bar will be displayed for Internet Explorer processes. If you disable this policy setting, the Notification Bar will not be displayed for Internet Explorer processes. If you do not configure this policy setting, the Notification Bar will be displayed for Internet Explorer processes.","group_id_src":"V-223133"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223134r961092","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Only allow approved domains to use ActiveX controls without prompt)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3\\120B'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI830-IE11","rule_title":"ActiveX controls without prompt property must be used in approved domains only (Internet zone).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:522"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; ' Allow only approved domains to use ActiveX controls without prompt' must be 'Enabled', and 'Enable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"120b\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223134r961092_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B3AAC57-6D7C-1014-84D1-D1AB0D564C25","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59729","V-46865"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223134","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000210","id":"V-223134"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Allow only approved domains to use ActiveX controls without prompt' to 'Enabled', and select 'Enable' from the drop-down box.   ","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether or not the user is prompted to allow ActiveX controls to run on websites other than the website that installed the ActiveX control. If the user were to disable the setting for the zone, malicious ActiveX controls could be executed without the user's knowledge. Disabling this setting would allow the possibility for malicious ActiveX controls to be executed from non-approved domains within this zone without the user's knowledge. Enabling this setting enforces the default value and prohibits the user from changing the value. Websites should be moved into another zone if permissions need to be changed.","group_id_src":"V-223134"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223135r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Notification Bar\\Internet Explorer Processes)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_SECURITYBAND\\iexplore.exe'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI835-IE11","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for Notification Bars must be enforced (iexplore).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:543"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features-&gt; Notification Bar-&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_SECURITYBAND Criteria: If the value \"iexplore.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223135r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B3AB174-6D7C-1014-85B7-ED3EC07F3EFF","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59735","V-46869"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223135","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223135"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features-&gt; Notification Bar-&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   ","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether the Notification Bar is displayed for Internet Explorer processes when file or code installs are restricted. By default, the Notification Bar is displayed for Internet Explorer processes. If you enable this policy setting, the Notification Bar will be displayed for Internet Explorer processes. If you disable this policy setting, the Notification Bar will not be displayed for Internet Explorer processes. If you do not configure this policy setting, the Notification Bar will be displayed for Internet Explorer processes.","group_id_src":"V-223135"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223136r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Turn on Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) Filter must be Enabled and Enable selected)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3\\1409'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI840-IE11","rule_title":"Cross-Site Scripting Filter must be enforced (Internet zone).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:523"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Turn on Cross-Site Scripting Filter' must be 'Enabled', and 'Enable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"1409\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223136r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B3AB6A6-6D7C-1014-8A04-B02D1EF45501","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59745","V-46879"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223136","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223136"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Turn on Cross-Site Scripting Filter' to 'Enabled', and select 'Enable' from the drop-down box.   ","discussion":"The Cross-Site Scripting Filter is designed to prevent users from becoming victims of unintentional information disclosure. This setting controls if the Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) Filter detects and prevents cross-site script injection into websites in this zone. If you enable this policy setting, the XSS Filter will be enabled for sites in this zone, and the XSS Filter will attempt to block cross-site script injections. If you disable this policy setting, the XSS Filter will be disabled for sites in this zone, and Internet Explorer will permit cross-site script injections.","group_id_src":"V-223136"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223137r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Allow scripting of Internet Explorer web browser control)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\\1206'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI850-IE11","rule_title":"Scripting of Internet Explorer WebBrowser Control must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:524"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow scripting of Internet Explorer WebBrowser controls' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1206\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223137r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B3ABBDF-6D7C-1014-AFD0-D8CB43F1507E","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59749","V-46883"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223137","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223137"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow scripting of Internet Explorer WebBrowser controls' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether a page may control embedded WebBrowser Control via script. Scripted code hosted on sites located in this zone is more likely to contain malicious code. If you enable this policy setting, script access to the WebBrowser Control is allowed. If you disable this policy setting, script access to the WebBrowser Control is not allowed. If you do not configure this policy setting, script access to the WebBrowser Control can be enabled or disabled by the user. By default, script access to the WebBrowser Control is only allowed in the Local Machine and Intranet Zones.","group_id_src":"V-223137"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223138r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Include local directory path when uploading files to a server)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\\160A'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI860-IE11","rule_title":"When uploading files to a server, the local directory path must be excluded (Restricted Sites zone).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:525"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Include local path when user is uploading files to a server' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"160A\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223138r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B3AC103-6D7C-1014-8F3C-CF9828B311B7","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59751","V-46885"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223138","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223138"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Include local path when user is uploading files to a server' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether or not the local path information will be sent when uploading a file via a HTML form. If the local path information is sent, some information may be unintentionally revealed to the server. If you do not configure this policy setting, the user can choose whether path information will be sent when uploading a file via a form. By default, path information will be sent.","group_id_src":"V-223138"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223139r961863","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Launching programs and unsafe files)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\\1806'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI870-IE11","rule_title":"Security Warning for unsafe files must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:526"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Show security warning for potentially unsafe files' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1806\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223139r961863_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B3AC63F-6D7C-1014-83BA-8791D9C06641","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59755","V-46889"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223139","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000516","id":"V-223139"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Show security warning for potentially unsafe files' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether or not the 'Open File - Security Warning' message appears when the user tries to open executable files or other potentially unsafe files (from an intranet file shared by using Windows Explorer, for example). If you enable this policy setting and set the drop-down box to \"Enable\", these files open without a security warning. If you set the drop-down box to \"Prompt\", a security warning appears before the files open. If you disable this policy these files do not open. If you do not configure this policy setting, the user can configure how the computer handles these files.","group_id_src":"V-223139"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223140r961092","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Only allow approved domains to use ActiveX controls without prompt)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\\120B'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI880-IE11","rule_title":"ActiveX controls without prompt property must be used in approved domains only (Restricted Sites zone).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:527"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow only approved domains to use ActiveX controls without prompt' must be 'Enabled', and 'Enable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"120b\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223140r961092_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B3ACBEB-6D7C-1014-9E6B-F68804C2F22A","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59759","V-46893"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223140","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000210","id":"V-223140"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow only approved domains to use ActiveX controls without prompt' to 'Enabled', and select 'Enable' from the drop-down box.   ","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether or not the user is prompted to allow ActiveX controls to run on websites other than the website that installed the ActiveX control. If the user were to disable the setting for the zone, malicious ActiveX controls could be executed without the user's knowledge. Disabling this setting would allow the possibility for malicious ActiveX controls to be executed from non-approved domains within this zone without the user's knowledge. Enabling this setting enforces the default value and prohibits the user from changing the value. Websites should be moved into another zone if permissions need to be changed.","group_id_src":"V-223140"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223141r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Turn on Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) Filter)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\\1409'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI890-IE11","rule_title":"Cross-Site Scripting Filter property must be enforced (Restricted Sites zone).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:528"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Turn on Cross-Site Scripting Filter' must be 'Enabled', and 'Enable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1409\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223141r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B3AD160-6D7C-1014-9485-DE6E2DF21521","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59761","V-46895"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223141","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223141"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Turn on Cross-Site Scripting Filter' to 'Enabled', and select 'Enable' from the drop-down box.   ","discussion":"The Cross-Site Scripting Filter is designed to prevent users from becoming victims of unintentional information disclosure. This setting controls if the Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) Filter detects and prevents cross-site script injection into websites in this zone. If you enable this policy setting, the XSS Filter will be enabled for sites in this zone, and the XSS Filter will attempt to block cross-site script injections. If you disable this policy setting, the XSS Filter will be disabled for sites in this zone, and Internet Explorer will permit cross-site script injections.","group_id_src":"V-223141"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223142r960921","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Restrict ActiveX Install\\Internet Explorer Processes must be Enabled)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_RESTRICT_ACTIVEXINSTALL\\(Reserved)'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI900-IE11","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes Restrict ActiveX Install must be enforced (Reserved).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:529"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-001695"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Restrict ActiveX Install -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_RESTRICT_ACTIVEXINSTALL   Criteria: If the value \"(Reserved)\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223142r960921_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000112","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B3AD6EA-6D7C-1014-93A3-9D5FFE816E86","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59763","V-46897"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223142","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000112","id":"V-223142"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Restrict ActiveX Install -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   ","discussion":"Users often choose to install software such as ActiveX controls that are not permitted by their organization's security policy. Such software can pose significant security and privacy risks to networks. This policy setting enables blocking of ActiveX control installation prompts for Internet Explorer processes. If you enable this policy setting, prompts for ActiveX control installations will be blocked for Internet Explorer processes. If you disable this policy setting, prompts for ActiveX control installations will not be blocked and these prompts will be displayed to users. If you do not configure this policy setting, the user's preference will be used to determine whether to block ActiveX control installations for Internet Explorer processes.","group_id_src":"V-223142"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223143r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone Allow status bar updates via script must be Enabled and Disable selected)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3\\2103'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI910-IE11","rule_title":"Status bar updates via script must be disallowed (Internet zone).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:530"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone 'Allow updates to status bar via script' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"2103\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223143r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B3ADC93-6D7C-1014-9638-CCDABF5F59B3","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59769","V-46903"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223143","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223143"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone 'Allow updates to status bar via script' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether script is allowed to update the status bar within the zone. A script running in the zone could cause false information to be displayed on the status bar, which could confuse the user and cause them to perform an undesirable action. If you enable this policy setting, script is allowed to update the status bar. If you disable this policy setting, script is not allowed to update the status bar. If you do not configure this policy setting, status bar updates via scripts will be disabled.","group_id_src":"V-223143"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223144r961863","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Run .NET Framework-reliant components not signed with Authenticode)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3\\2004'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI920-IE11","rule_title":".NET Framework-reliant components not signed with Authenticode must be disallowed to run (Internet zone).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:531"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone 'Run .NET Framework-reliant components not signed with Authenticode' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"2004\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223144r961863_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B3AE30C-6D7C-1014-A21D-9E8AAD0FA8F0","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59773","V-46907"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223144","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000516","id":"V-223144"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone 'Run .NET Framework-reliant components not signed with Authenticode' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","discussion":"Unsigned components are more likely to contain malicious code and it is more difficult to determine the author of the application - therefore they should be avoided if possible. This policy setting allows you to manage whether .NET Framework components that are not signed with Authenticode can be executed from Internet Explorer. These components include managed controls referenced from an object tag and managed executables referenced from a link. If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will execute unsigned managed components. If you select \"Prompt\" in the drop-down box, Internet Explorer will prompt the user to determine whether to execute unsigned managed components. If you disable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will not execute unsigned managed components. If you do not configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer will not execute unsigned managed components.","group_id_src":"V-223144"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223145r961863","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Run .NET Framework-reliant components signed with Authenticode)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3\\2001'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI930-IE11","rule_title":".NET Framework-reliant components signed with Authenticode must be disallowed to run (Internet zone).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:532"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone 'Run .NET Framework-reliant components signed with Authenticode' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"2001\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223145r961863_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B3AE8D8-6D7C-1014-892D-E5D8E625F5FE","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59787","V-46921"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223145","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000516","id":"V-223145"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone 'Run .NET Framework-reliant components signed with Authenticode' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.  ","discussion":"It may be possible for someone to host malicious content on a website that takes advantage of these components. This policy setting allows you to manage whether .NET Framework components that are signed with Authenticode can be executed from Internet Explorer. These components include managed controls referenced from an object tag and managed executables referenced from a link. If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will execute signed managed components. If you select \"Prompt\" in the drop-down box, Internet Explorer will prompt the user to determine whether to execute signed managed components. If you disable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will not execute signed managed components. If you do not configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer will not execute signed managed components.","group_id_src":"V-223145"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223146r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Allow Scriptlets)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\\1209'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI940-IE11","rule_title":"Scriptlets must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:533"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone 'Allow Scriptlets' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box.  Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1209\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223146r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B3AEE44-6D7C-1014-A2B2-D7ABA4753F1A","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59793","V-46927"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223146","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223146"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone 'Allow Scriptlets' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether scriptlets can be allowed. Scriptlets hosted on sites located in this zone are more likely to contain malicious code. If you enable this policy setting, users will be able to run scriptlets. If you disable this policy setting, users will not be able to run scriptlets. If you do not configure this policy setting, a scriptlet can be enabled or disabled by the user.","group_id_src":"V-223146"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223147r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone Allow status bar updates via script must be Enabled and Disabled selected)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\\2103'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI950-IE11","rule_title":"Status bar updates via script must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:534"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone 'Allow updates to status bar via script' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"2103\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223147r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B3AF36B-6D7C-1014-9D38-DD8F4CF2C083","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59805","V-46939"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223147","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223147"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone 'Allow updates to status bar via script' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box. ","discussion":"A script running in the zone could cause false information to be displayed on the status bar, which could confuse the user and cause an undesirable action. This policy setting allows you to manage whether script is allowed to update the status bar within the zone. If you enable this policy setting, script is allowed to update the status bar. If you disable this policy setting, script is not allowed to update the status bar. If you do not configure this policy setting, status bar updates via scripts will be disabled.","group_id_src":"V-223147"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223148r961863","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Windows Components/Internet Explorer/Internet Control Panel/Advanced Page/Do not allow ActiveX controls to run in Protected Mode when Enhanced Protected Mode )\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\DisableEPMCompat'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI985-IE11","rule_title":"When Enhanced Protected Mode is enabled, ActiveX controls must be disallowed to run in Protected Mode.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:556"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Note: If McAfee ENS Web Control is being used, this is Not Applicable.\n\nThe policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer-&gt; Internet Control Panel-&gt; Advanced Page 'Do not allow ActiveX controls to run in Protected Mode when Enhanced Protected Mode is enabled' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main Criteria: If the value \"DisableEPMCompat\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.\n","rule_id_src":"SV-223148r961863_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B3AF8AA-6D7C-1014-BED3-E6F9F132A242","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59841","V-46975"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223148","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000516","id":"V-223148"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer-&gt; Internet Control Panel-&gt; Advanced Page 'Do not allow ActiveX controls to run in Protected Mode when Enhanced Protected Mode is enabled' to 'Enabled'.   ","discussion":"This setting prevents ActiveX controls from running in Protected Mode when Enhanced Protected Mode is enabled. When a user has an ActiveX control installed that is not compatible with Enhanced Protected Mode and a website attempts to load the control, Internet Explorer notifies the user and gives the option to run the website in regular Protected Mode. This policy setting disables this notification and forces all websites to run in Enhanced Protected Mode. Enhanced Protected Mode provides additional protection against malicious websites by using 64-bit processes on 64-bit versions of Windows. For computers running at least Windows 8, Enhanced Protected Mode also limits the locations Internet Explorer can read from in the registry and the file system. If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will not give the user the option to disable Enhanced Protected Mode. All Protected Mode websites will run in Enhanced Protected Mode. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer notifies users and provides an option to run websites with incompatible ActiveX controls in regular Protected Mode.","group_id_src":"V-223148"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223149r1117169","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Enable dragging of content from different domains across windows)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3\\2709'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI990-IE11","rule_title":"Dragging of content from different domains across windows must be disallowed (Internet zone).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:547"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-001414"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer-&gt; Internet Control Panel-&gt; Security Page-&gt; Internet Zone 'Enable dragging of content from different domains across windows' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disabled' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"2709\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-223149r1117169_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000039","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B3AFDD8-6D7C-1014-B330-FDB05DCFA60B","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59847","V-46981"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-223149","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000039","id":"V-223149"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer-&gt; Internet Control Panel-&gt; Security Page-&gt; Internet Zone 'Enable dragging of content from different domains across windows' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disabled' from the drop-down box.   ","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to set options for dragging content from one domain to a different domain when the source and destination are in different windows. If you enable this policy setting, users can drag content from one domain to a different domain when the source and destination are in different windows. Users cannot change this setting. If you disable this policy setting, users cannot drag content from one domain to a different domain when both the source and destination are in different windows. Users cannot change this setting. If you do not configure this policy setting, users cannot drag content from one domain to a different domain when the source and destination are in different windows. Users can change this setting in the Internet Options dialog box.","group_id_src":"V-223149"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-250540r1117186","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true ('turn off encryption support' setting is handled by Group Policy.)\nTest            :   false (TLS 1.2 must be selected for the IE option 'turn off encryption support' via Group Policy.)\nResult Analysis :        HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\SecureProtocols\\value = '2688' failed test of 'equals' compared to '2048' \n","rule_version":"DTBI014-IE11","rule_title":"Turn off Encryption Support must be enabled.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:580"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-002450"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; Advanced Page &gt;&gt; \"Turn off Encryption Support\" must be \"Enabled\".\n\nVerify the only option selected is \"Only use TLS 1.2\" from the drop-down box.\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings!SecureProtocols.\n\nCriteria: If the value for \"SecureProtocols\" is not REG_DWORD = \"2048\", this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-250540r1117186_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000416","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B3B0307-6D7C-1014-A47D-8F21148974F9","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59337","V-46473"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-250540","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000416","id":"V-250540"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; Advanced Page &gt;&gt; \"Turn off Encryption Support\" to \"Enabled\".\n\nSelect only \"Only use TLS 1.2\" from the drop-down box.","discussion":"This parameter ensures only DOD-approved ciphers and algorithms are enabled for use by the web browser by allowing the user to turn on/off support for TLS and SSL. TLS is a protocol for protecting communications between the browser and the target server. When the browser attempts to set up a protected communication with the target server, the browser and server negotiate which protocol and version to use. The browser and server attempt to match each other's list of supported protocols and versions and pick the most preferred match.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-APP-000514, SRG-APP-000555, SRG-APP-000625, SRG-APP-000630, SRG-APP-000635","group_id_src":"V-250540"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-250541r1117186","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false ('Allow Fallback to SSL 3.0 (Internet Explorer)' is set to 'Enabled' with 'Allow insecure fallback for:' set to 'No Sites')\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\EnableSSL3Fallback'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"DTBI1100-IE11","rule_title":"Allow Fallback to SSL 3.0 (Internet Explorer) must be disabled.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:581"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-002450"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Security Features &gt;&gt; \"Allow fallback to SSL 3.0 (Internet Explorer)\" must be \"Enabled\", and \"No Sites\" selected from the drop-down box. If \"Allow fallback to SSL 3.0 (Internet Explorer)\" is not \"Enabled\" or any other drop-down option is selected, this is a finding. \n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings. \n\nCriteria: If the value \"EnableSSL3Fallback\" is REG_DWORD=0, this is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-250541r1117186_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000416","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B3B0868-6D7C-1014-9792-BD4B782F0B13","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":["SV-79219","V-64729"],"status":"open","group_id":"V-250541","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000416","id":"V-250541"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Security Features &gt;&gt; \"Allow fallback to SSL 3.0 (Internet Explorer)\" to \"Enabled\", and select \"No Sites\" from the drop-down box.\n","discussion":"This parameter ensures only DoD-approved ciphers and algorithms are enabled for use by the web browser by blocking an insecure fallback to SSL when TLS 1.0 or greater fails.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-APP-000514, SRG-APP-000555, SRG-APP-000625, SRG-APP-000630, SRG-APP-000635","group_id_src":"V-250541"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-252910r1156566","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND)) (negated)\nTest            :     true (Internet Explorer 11 is installed)\n","rule_version":"DTBI999-IE11","rule_title":"The version of Internet Explorer running on the system must be a supported version.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.win:def:252910"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-002605"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Internet Explorer 11 is no longer supported by the vendor.\n\nIf Internet Explorer 11 is installed, this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-252910r1156566_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000456","false_positives":"","uuid":"2B3B0DD4-6D7C-1014-92D1-FC5B6ECC9D65","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"4095","stig_uuid":"2B28994A-6D7C-1014-BE5F-9A21F0DFF560","severity":"high","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_id":"V-252910","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000456","id":"V-252910"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Remove the Internet Explorer 11 application.","discussion":"Security flaws with software applications are discovered daily. Vendors are constantly updating and patching their products to address newly discovered security vulnerabilities. Organizations (including any contractor to the organization) are required to promptly install security-relevant software updates (e.g., patches, service packs, and hot fixes). Flaws discovered during security assessments, continuous monitoring, incident response activities, or information system error handling must also be addressed expeditiously.\n\nOrganization-defined time periods for updating security-relevant software may vary based on a variety of factors including, for example, the security category of the information system or the criticality of the update (i.e., severity of the vulnerability related to the discovered flaw).\n\nThis requirement will apply to software patch management solutions that are used to install patches across the enclave and also to applications that are not part of that patch management solution. For example, many browsers today provide the capability to install their own patch software. Patch criticality, as well as system criticality, will vary. Therefore, the tactical situations regarding the patch management process will also vary. This means the time period used must be a configurable parameter. Time frames for application of security-relevant software updates may depend on the Information Assurance Vulnerability Management (IAVM) process.","group_id_src":"V-252910"}],"display_name":"Microsoft Internet Explorer 11","release_info":"Release: 6 Benchmark Date: 05 Jan 2026"},{"uuid":"6FDFF1B9-6D7C-1014-8C20-99EC6B15618D","stig_name":"Microsoft Windows 11 Security Technical Implementation Guide","version":"2","size":263,"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","reference_identifier":"5471","stig_id":"Microsoft_Windows_11_STIG","rules":[{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-253254r991589","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:51\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true (EditionID is Enterprise or EnterpriseS)\n","rule_version":"WN11-00-000005","rule_title":"Domain-joined systems must use Windows 11 Enterprise Edition 64-bit version.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows11:def:253254"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Verify domain-joined systems are using Windows 11 Enterprise Edition 64-bit version.\n\nFor standalone systems, this is NA.\n\nOpen \"Settings\".\n\nSelect \"System\", then \"About\".\n\nIf \"Edition\" is not \"Windows 11 Enterprise\", this is a finding.\n\nIf \"System type\" is not \"64-bit operating system...\", this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-253254r991589_rule","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","false_positives":"","uuid":"7002516C-6D7C-1014-9804-DC51DE9ED471","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5471","stig_uuid":"6FDFF1B9-6D7C-1014-8C20-99EC6B15618D","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_id":"V-253254","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","id":"V-253254"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Use Windows 11 Enterprise 64-bit version for domain-joined systems.","discussion":"Features such as Credential Guard use virtualization-based security to protect information that could be used in credential theft attacks if compromised. There are a number of system requirements that must be met in order for Credential Guard to be configured and enabled properly. Virtualization-based security and Credential Guard are only available with Windows 11 Enterprise 64-bit version.","group_id_src":"V-253254"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-253255r1117271","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:51\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Windows must have TPM and must be ready to use)\nTest            :   true (Windows TPM Specific Version should be 1.2 or 2.0)\n","rule_version":"WN11-00-000010","rule_title":"Windows 11 domain-joined systems must have a Trusted Platform Module (TPM) enabled.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows:def:253255"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-002421"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Verify domain-joined systems have a TPM enabled and ready for use.\n\nFor standalone systems, this is NA.\n\nVirtualization-based security, including Credential Guard, currently cannot be implemented in virtual desktop implementations (VDI) due to specific supporting requirements including a TPM, UEFI with Secure Boot, and the capability to run the Hyper-V feature within the virtual desktop.\n\nFor VDIs where the virtual desktop instance is deleted or refreshed upon logoff, this is NA.\n\nVerify the system has a TPM and is ready for use.\nRun \"tpm.msc\".\nReview the sections in the center pane.\n\"Status\" must indicate it has been configured with a message such as \"The TPM is ready for use\" or \"The TPM is on and ownership has been taken\".\nTPM Manufacturer Information - Specific Version = 2.0\n\nIf a TPM is not found or is not ready for use, this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-253255r1117271_rule","group_title":"SRG-OS-000424-GPOS-00188","false_positives":"","uuid":"700258FC-6D7C-1014-A1B3-885DBAABEA36","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5471","stig_uuid":"6FDFF1B9-6D7C-1014-8C20-99EC6B15618D","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_id":"V-253255","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000424-GPOS-00188","id":"V-253255"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"For standalone systems, this is NA.\n\nVirtualization-based security, including Credential Guard, currently cannot be implemented in virtual desktop implementations (VDI) due to specific supporting requirements including a TPM, UEFI with Secure Boot, and the capability to run the Hyper-V feature within the virtual desktop.\n\nFor VDIs where the virtual desktop instance is deleted or refreshed upon logoff, this is NA.\n\nEnsure domain-joined systems must have a TPM that is configured for use. (Versions 2.0 support Credential Guard.)\n\nThe TPM must be enabled in the firmware.\nRun \"tpm.msc\" for configuration options in Windows.","discussion":"Credential Guard uses virtualization-based security to protect information that could be used in credential theft attacks if compromised. There are a number of system requirements that must be met in order for Credential Guard to be configured and enabled properly. Without a TPM enabled and ready for use, Credential Guard keys are stored in a less secure method using software.","group_id_src":"V-253255"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-253256r1117271","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:51\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Unified Extensible Firmware Interface (UEFI) firmware must exist and be configured to run in UEFI mode, not Legacy BIOS.)\n","rule_version":"WN11-00-000015","rule_title":"Windows 11 systems must have Unified Extensible Firmware Interface (UEFI) firmware and be configured to run in UEFI mode, not Legacy BIOS.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows:def:253256"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-002421"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"For virtual desktop implementations (VDIs) where the virtual desktop instance is deleted or refreshed upon logoff, this is NA.\n\nVerify the system firmware is configured to run in UEFI mode, not Legacy BIOS.\n\nRun \"System Information\".\n\nUnder \"System Summary\", if \"BIOS Mode\" does not display \"UEFI\", this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-253256r1117271_rule","group_title":"SRG-OS-000424-GPOS-00188","false_positives":"","uuid":"70025E3D-6D7C-1014-A744-BC7676666779","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5471","stig_uuid":"6FDFF1B9-6D7C-1014-8C20-99EC6B15618D","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_id":"V-253256","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000424-GPOS-00188","id":"V-253256"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Configure UEFI firmware to run in UEFI mode, not Legacy BIOS mode.","discussion":"UEFI provides additional security features in comparison to legacy BIOS firmware, including Secure Boot. UEFI is required to support additional security features in Windows 11, including virtualization-based Security and Credential Guard. Systems with UEFI that are operating in Legacy BIOS mode will not support these security features.","group_id_src":"V-253256"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-253257r1117271","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:51\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Run a PowerShell command to determine if Secure Boot must be enabled.)\n","rule_version":"WN11-00-000020","rule_title":"Secure Boot must be enabled on Windows 11 systems.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows:def:253257"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-002421"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Verify the system firmware is configured for Secure Boot.\n\nFor virtual desktop implementations (VDIs) where the virtual desktop instance is deleted or refreshed upon logoff, this is NA.\n\nRun \"System Information\".\n\nUnder \"System Summary\", if \"Secure Boot State\" does not display \"On\", this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-253257r1117271_rule","group_title":"SRG-OS-000424-GPOS-00188","false_positives":"","uuid":"70026320-6D7C-1014-AEA2-FBB3D0D31CA7","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5471","stig_uuid":"6FDFF1B9-6D7C-1014-8C20-99EC6B15618D","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_id":"V-253257","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000424-GPOS-00188","id":"V-253257"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Enable Secure Boot in the system firmware.","discussion":"Secure Boot is a standard that ensures systems boot only to a trusted operating system. Secure Boot is required to support additional security features in Windows 11, including virtualization-based Security and Credential Guard. If Secure Boot is turned off, these security features will not function.","group_id_src":"V-253257"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-253258r1000099","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:51\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT II, V-253258, SV-253258r1000099, SRG-OS-000191-GPOS-00080)\n","rule_version":"WN11-00-000025","rule_title":"Windows 11 must employ automated mechanisms to determine the state of system components with regard to flaw remediation using the following frequency: Continuously, where ESS is used; 30 days, for any additional internal network scans not covered by ESS; and annually, for external scans by Computer Network Defense Service Provider (CNDSP).","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-ocil.xml","name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows11:questionnaire:901"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Verify DOD-approved ESS software is installed and properly operating. Ask the site information system security manager (ISSM) for documentation of the ESS software installation and configuration.\n\nIf the ISSM is not able to provide a documented configuration for an installed ESS or if the ESS software is not properly maintained or used, this is a finding.\n\nNote: Example of documentation can be a copy of the site's CCB approved Software Baseline with version of software noted or a memo from the ISSM stating current ESS software and version.","rule_id_src":"SV-253258r1000099_rule","group_title":"SRG-OS-000191-GPOS-00080","false_positives":"","uuid":"70026820-6D7C-1014-9081-B1F2A2DB06E1","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5471","stig_uuid":"6FDFF1B9-6D7C-1014-8C20-99EC6B15618D","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_reviewed","group_id":"V-253258","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000191-GPOS-00080","id":"V-253258"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Install DOD-approved ESS software and ensure it is operating continuously.","discussion":"An approved tool for continuous network scanning must be installed and configured to run.\n\nWithout the use of automated mechanisms to scan for security flaws on a continuous and/or periodic basis, the operating system or other system components may remain vulnerable to the exploits presented by undetected software flaws.\n\nTo support this requirement, the operating system may have an integrated solution incorporating continuous scanning using ESS and periodic scanning using other tools, as specified in the requirement.","group_id_src":"V-253258"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-253259r958870","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:51\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true (BitLocker must be enabled on all fixed drives.)\n","rule_version":"WN11-00-000030","rule_title":"Windows 11 information systems must use BitLocker to encrypt all disks to protect the confidentiality and integrity of all information at rest.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows11:def:253259"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-002475"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Verify all Windows 11 information systems (including SIPRNet) employ BitLocker for full disk encryption.\n\nFor virtual desktop implementations (VDIs) in which the virtual desktop instance is deleted or refreshed upon logoff, this is NA.\nFor AVD implementations with no data at rest, this is NA.\n\nIf full disk encryption using BitLocker is not implemented, this is a finding.\n\nVerify BitLocker is turned on for the operating system drive and any fixed data drives.\n\nOpen \"BitLocker Drive Encryption\" from the Control Panel.\n\nIf the operating system drive or any fixed data drives have \"Turn on BitLocker\", this is a finding.\n\nNote: An alternate encryption application may be used in lieu of BitLocker providing it is configured for full disk encryption and satisfies the pre-boot authentication requirements (WN11-00-000031 and WN11-00-000032).","rule_id_src":"SV-253259r958870_rule","group_title":"SRG-OS-000404-GPOS-00183","false_positives":"","uuid":"70026E0B-6D7C-1014-8269-8B484FC7E020","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5471","stig_uuid":"6FDFF1B9-6D7C-1014-8C20-99EC6B15618D","severity":"high","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_id":"V-253259","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000404-GPOS-00183","id":"V-253259"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Enable full disk encryption on all information systems (including SIPRNet) using BitLocker.\n\nBitLocker, included in Windows, can be enabled in the Control Panel under \"BitLocker Drive Encryption\" as well as other management tools.\n\nNote: An alternate encryption application may be used in lieu of BitLocker providing it is configured for full disk encryption and satisfies the pre-boot authentication requirements (WN11-00-000031 and WN11-00-000032).","discussion":"If data at rest is unencrypted, it is vulnerable to disclosure. Even if the operating system enforces permissions on data access, an adversary can remove non-volatile memory and read it directly, thereby circumventing operating system controls. Encrypting the data ensures that confidentiality is protected even when the operating system is not running.","group_id_src":"V-253259"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-253260r958872","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:51\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :     false (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nCriteria        :       false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :         false (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :           false ('Configure TPM startup PIN' is set to 'Require startup PIN with TPM'.)\nResult Analysis :                HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\FVE\\UseTPMPIN\\value = '2' failed test of 'equals' compared to '1' \nTest            :           false ('Configure TPM startup key and PIN' is set to 'Require startup key and PIN with TPM'.)\nResult Analysis :                HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\FVE\\UseTPMKeyPIN\\value = '2' failed test of 'equals' compared to '1' \nTest            :         true ('Allow network unlock at startup' is Enabled.) (negated)\nCriteria        :       false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :         true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :           true ('Configure TPM startup PIN' is set to 'Allow startup PIN with TPM'.)\nTest            :           true ('Configure TPM startup key and PIN' is set to 'Allow startup key and PIN with TPM'.)\nTest            :         false ('Allow network unlock at startup' is Enabled.)\nResult Analysis :              Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\FVE\\OSManageNKP'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nTest            :     true ('Require additional authentication at startup' is Enabled.)\n","rule_version":"WN11-00-000031","rule_title":"Windows 11 systems must use a BitLocker PIN for pre-boot authentication.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows11:def:253260"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-002476"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nFor virtual desktop implementations (VDIs) in which the virtual desktop instance is deleted or refreshed upon logoff, this is NA.\n\nFor AVD implementations with no data at rest, this is NA.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\FVE\\\n\nValue Name: UseAdvancedStartup\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)\n\nIf one of the following registry values does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\FVE\\\n\nValue Name: UseTPMPIN\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)\n\nValue Name: UseTPMKeyPIN\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)\n\nWhen BitLocker network unlock is used:\n\nValue Name: UseTPMPIN\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000002 (2)\n\nValue Name: UseTPMKeyPIN\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000002 (2)\n\nBitLocker network unlock may be used in conjunction with a BitLocker PIN. See the article below regarding information about network unlock.\n\nhttps://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/security/information-protection/bitlocker/bitlocker-how-to-enable-network-unlock","rule_id_src":"SV-253260r958872_rule","group_title":"SRG-OS-000405-GPOS-00184","false_positives":"","uuid":"700272E2-6D7C-1014-A7D3-B31CA875FADE","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5471","stig_uuid":"6FDFF1B9-6D7C-1014-8C20-99EC6B15618D","severity":"high","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_id":"V-253260","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000405-GPOS-00184","id":"V-253260"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; BitLocker Drive Encryption &gt;&gt; Operating System Drives \"Require additional authentication at startup\" to \"Enabled\" with \"Configure TPM Startup PIN:\" set to \"Require startup PIN with TPM\" or with \"Configure TPM startup key and PIN:\" set to \"Require startup key and PIN with TPM\".","discussion":"If data at rest is unencrypted, it is vulnerable to disclosure. Even if the operating system enforces permissions on data access, an adversary can remove non-volatile memory and read it directly, thereby circumventing operating system controls. Encrypting the data ensures that confidentiality is protected even when the operating system is not running. Pre-boot authentication prevents unauthorized users from accessing encrypted drives.","group_id_src":"V-253260"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-253261r958504","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:51\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     false (BitLocker must be 6 digits or more.)\nResult Analysis :          Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\FVE\\MinimumPIN'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"WN11-00-000032","rule_title":"Windows 11 systems must use a BitLocker PIN with a minimum length of six digits for pre-boot authentication.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows11:def:253261"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000804"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nFor virtual desktop implementations (VDIs) in which the virtual desktop instance is deleted or refreshed upon logoff, this is NA.\n\nFor AVD implementations with no data at rest, this is NA.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\FVE\\\n\nValue Name: MinimumPIN\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000006 (6) or greater","rule_id_src":"SV-253261r958504_rule","group_title":"SRG-OS-000121-GPOS-00062","false_positives":"","uuid":"700277B1-6D7C-1014-8120-9C8E2666A2F3","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5471","stig_uuid":"6FDFF1B9-6D7C-1014-8C20-99EC6B15618D","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_id":"V-253261","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000121-GPOS-00062","id":"V-253261"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; BitLocker Drive Encryption &gt;&gt; Operating System Drives \"Configure minimum PIN length for startup\" to \"Enabled\" with \"Minimum characters:\" set to \"6\" or greater.","discussion":"If data at rest is unencrypted, it is vulnerable to disclosure. Even if the operating system enforces permissions on data access, an adversary can remove non-volatile memory and read it directly, thereby circumventing operating system controls. Encrypting the data ensures that confidentiality is protected even when the operating system is not running. Pre-boot authentication prevents unauthorized users from accessing encrypted drives. Increasing the pin length requires a greater number of guesses for an attacker.","group_id_src":"V-253261"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-253262r958808","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:51\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT II, V-253262, SV-253262r958808, SRG-OS-000370-GPOS-00155)\n","rule_version":"WN11-00-000035","rule_title":"The operating system must employ a deny-all, permit-by-exception policy to allow the execution of authorized software programs.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-ocil.xml","name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows11:questionnaire:1701"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-001774"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Verify the operating system employs a deny-all, permit-by-exception policy to allow the execution of authorized software programs. This must include packaged apps such as the universal apps installed by default on systems.\n\nIf an application allowlisting program is not in use on the system, this is a finding.\n\nConfiguration of allowlisting applications will vary by the program.\n\nAppLocker is an allowlisting application built into Windows 11 Enterprise. A deny-by-default implementation is initiated by enabling any AppLocker rules within a category, only allowing what is specified by defined rules.\n\nIf AppLocker is used, perform the following to view the configuration of AppLocker:\nRun \"PowerShell\".\n\nExecute the following command, substituting [c:\\temp\\file.xml] with a location and file name appropriate for the system:\nGet-AppLockerPolicy -Effective -XML &gt; c:\\temp\\file.xml\n\nThis will produce an xml file with the effective settings that can be viewed in a browser or opened in a program such as Excel for review.\n\nImplementation guidance for AppLocker is available at the following link:\n\nhttps://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/security/threat-protection/windows-defender-application-control/applocker/applocker-policies-deployment-guide","rule_id_src":"SV-253262r958808_rule","group_title":"SRG-OS-000370-GPOS-00155","false_positives":"","uuid":"70027C7E-6D7C-1014-A7CC-BEBA1743A8DB","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5471","stig_uuid":"6FDFF1B9-6D7C-1014-8C20-99EC6B15618D","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_reviewed","group_id":"V-253262","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000370-GPOS-00155","id":"V-253262"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Configure an application allowlisting program to employ a deny-all, permit-by-exception policy to allow the execution of authorized software programs.\n\nConfiguration of allowlisting applications will vary by the program. AppLocker is an allowlisting application built into Windows 11 Enterprise.\n\nIf AppLocker is used, it is configured through group policy in Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Application Control Policies &gt;&gt; AppLocker.\n\nImplementation guidance for AppLocker is available in the NSA paper \"Application allowlisting using Microsoft AppLocker\" at the following link:\n\nhttps://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/security/threat-protection/windows-defender-application-control/applocker/applocker-policies-deployment-guide","discussion":"Utilizing an allowlist provides a configuration management method for allowing the execution of only authorized software. Using only authorized software decreases risk by limiting the number of potential vulnerabilities.\n\nThe organization must identify authorized software programs and only permit execution of authorized software. The process used to identify software programs that are authorized to execute on organizational information systems is commonly referred to as allowlisting.","group_id_src":"V-253262"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-253263r1016364","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:51\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true (The OS Version is equal to or greater than 6.3)\nTest            :     true (The OS Build is equal to or greater than 22621)\n","rule_version":"WN11-00-000040","rule_title":"Windows 11 systems must be maintained at a supported servicing level.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows11:def:253263"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Run \"winver.exe\".\n\nIf the \"About Windows\" dialog box does not display \"Microsoft Windows 11 Version 22H2 (OS Build 22621.380)\" or greater, this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-253263r1016364_rule","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","false_positives":"","uuid":"700281D3-6D7C-1014-AE81-F259D3C2D33F","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5471","stig_uuid":"6FDFF1B9-6D7C-1014-8C20-99EC6B15618D","severity":"high","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_id":"V-253263","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","id":"V-253263"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Update systems on the Semi-Annual Channel to \"Microsoft Windows 11 Version 22H2 (OS Build 22621.380)\" or greater.","discussion":"Windows 11 is maintained by Microsoft at servicing levels for specific periods of time to support Windows as a Service. Systems at unsupported servicing levels or releases will not receive security updates for new vulnerabilities which leaves them subject to exploitation.\n\nNew versions with feature updates are planned to be released on a semi-annual basis with an estimated support timeframe of 18 to 30 months depending on the release. Support for previously released versions has been extended for Enterprise editions.\n\nA separate servicing branch intended for special purpose systems is the Long-Term Servicing Channel (LTSC, formerly Branch - LTSB) which will receive security updates for 10 years but excludes feature updates.","group_id_src":"V-253263"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-253264r991589","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:51\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Windows must use an antivirus program)\n","rule_version":"WN11-00-000045","rule_title":"The Windows 11 system must use an antivirus program.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows:def:253264"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Verify an antivirus solution is installed on the system and in use. The antivirus solution may be bundled with an approved Endpoint Security Solution.\n\nVerify if Microsoft Defender Antivirus is in use or enabled:\n\nOpen \"PowerShell\".\n\nEnter \"get-service | where {$_.DisplayName -Like \"*Defender*\"} | Select Status,DisplayName\"\n\nVerify third-party antivirus is in use or enabled:\n\nOpen \"PowerShell\".\n\nEnter \"get-service | where {$_.DisplayName -Like \"*mcafee*\"} | Select Status,DisplayName\"\n\nEnter \"get-service | where {$_.DisplayName -Like \"*symantec*\"} | Select Status,DisplayName\"\n\nIf there is no antivirus solution installed on the system, this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-253264r991589_rule","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","false_positives":"","uuid":"7002871D-6D7C-1014-B2E4-AAF5B3695AA5","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5471","stig_uuid":"6FDFF1B9-6D7C-1014-8C20-99EC6B15618D","severity":"high","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_id":"V-253264","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","id":"V-253264"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Install Microsoft Defender Antivirus or a third-party antivirus solution.","discussion":"Malicious software can establish a base on individual desktops and servers. Employing an automated mechanism to detect this type of software will aid in elimination of the software from the operating system.","group_id_src":"V-253264"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-253265r1137691","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:51\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true (Local volumes use NTFS)\n","rule_version":"WN11-00-000050","rule_title":"Local volumes must be formatted using NTFS.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows11:def:253265"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000213"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Run \"Computer Management\".\nNavigate to Storage &gt;&gt; Disk Management.\n\nIf the \"File System\" column does not indicate \"NTFS\" for each volume assigned a drive letter, this is a finding.\n\nThis does not apply to system partitions such the Recovery and EFI System Partition.","rule_id_src":"SV-253265r1137691_rule","group_title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","false_positives":"","uuid":"70028C8F-6D7C-1014-8227-81FCE0FDF4A7","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5471","stig_uuid":"6FDFF1B9-6D7C-1014-8C20-99EC6B15618D","severity":"high","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_id":"V-253265","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","id":"V-253265"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Format all local volumes to use NTFS.","discussion":"The ability to set access permissions and auditing is critical to maintaining the security and proper access controls of a system. To support this, volumes must be formatted using the NTFS file system.","group_id_src":"V-253265"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-253266r991589","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:51\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Review Installed OS via PowerShell)\n","rule_version":"WN11-00-000055","rule_title":"Alternate operating systems must not be permitted on the same system.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows:def:253266"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Verify the system does not include other operating system installations.\n\nRun \"Advanced System Settings\".\nSelect the \"Advanced\" tab.\nClick the \"Settings\" button in the \"Startup and Recovery\" section.\n\nIf the drop-down list box \"Default operating system:\" shows any operating system other than Windows 11, this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-253266r991589_rule","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","false_positives":"","uuid":"7002923B-6D7C-1014-8D46-8137A6F61D70","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5471","stig_uuid":"6FDFF1B9-6D7C-1014-8C20-99EC6B15618D","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_id":"V-253266","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","id":"V-253266"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Ensure Windows 11 is the only operating system on a device. Remove alternate operating systems.","discussion":"Allowing other operating systems to run on a secure system may allow security to be circumvented.","group_id_src":"V-253266"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-253267r1137695","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:51\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT II, V-253267, SV-253267r1137695, SRG-OS-000138-GPOS-00069)\n","rule_version":"WN11-00-000060","rule_title":"Non-system-created file shares on a system must limit access to groups that require it.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-ocil.xml","name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows11:questionnaire:2701"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-001090"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Non-system-created shares must not exist on workstations.\n\nIf only system-created shares exist on the system, this is NA.\n\nRun \"Computer Management\".\nNavigate to System Tools &gt;&gt; Shared Folders &gt;&gt; Shares.\n\nIf the only shares listed are \"ADMIN$\", \"C$\" and \"IPC$\", this is NA.\n(Selecting Properties for system-created shares will display a message that it has been shared for administrative purposes.)\n\nRight-click any non-system-created shares.\nSelect \"Properties\".\nSelect the \"Share Permissions\" tab.\n\nVerify the necessity of any shares found.\nIf the file shares have not been reconfigured to restrict permissions to the specific groups or accounts that require access, this is a finding.\n\nSelect the \"Security\" tab.\n\nIf the NTFS permissions have not been reconfigured to restrict permissions to the specific groups or accounts that require access, this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-253267r1137695_rule","group_title":"SRG-OS-000138-GPOS-00069","false_positives":"","uuid":"70029AAB-6D7C-1014-96A4-CF846EB85F15","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5471","stig_uuid":"6FDFF1B9-6D7C-1014-8C20-99EC6B15618D","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_reviewed","group_id":"V-253267","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000138-GPOS-00069","id":"V-253267"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"If a non-system-created share is required on a system, configure the share and NTFS permissions to limit access to the specific groups or accounts that require it.\n\nRemove any unnecessary non-system-created shares.","discussion":"Shares which provide network access, must not exist on a workstation except for system-created administrative shares, and could potentially expose sensitive information. If a share is necessary, share permissions, as well as NTFS permissions, must be reconfigured to give the minimum access to those accounts that require it.","group_id_src":"V-253267"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-253268r1051039","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:51\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT III, V-253268, SV-253268r1051039, SRG-OS-000468-GPOS-00212)\n","rule_version":"WN11-00-000065","rule_title":"Unused accounts must be disabled or removed from the system after 35 days of inactivity.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-ocil.xml","name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows11:questionnaire:2901"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000172","CCI-003627","CCI-000795"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Run \"PowerShell\".\nCopy the lines below to the PowerShell window and enter.\n\n\"([ADSI]('WinNT://{0}' -f $env:COMPUTERNAME)).Children | Where { $_.SchemaClassName -eq 'user' } | ForEach {\n  $user = ([ADSI]$_.Path)\n  $lastLogin = $user.Properties.LastLogin.Value\n  $enabled = ($user.Properties.UserFlags.Value -band 0x2) -ne 0x2\n  if ($lastLogin -eq $null) {\n   $lastLogin = 'Never'\n  }\n  Write-Host $user.Name $lastLogin $enabled \n}\"\n\nThis will return a list of local accounts with the account name, last logon, and if the account is enabled (True/False).\nFor example: User1 10/31/2015 5:49:56 AM True\n\nReview the list to determine the finding validity for each account reported.\n\nExclude the following accounts:\nBuilt-in administrator account (Disabled, SID ending in 500)\nBuilt-in guest account (Disabled, SID ending in 501)\nBuilt-in DefaultAccount (Disabled, SID ending in 503)\nLocal administrator account\n\nIf any enabled accounts have not been logged on to within the past 35 days, this is a finding.\n\nInactive accounts that have been reviewed and deemed to be required must be documented with the information system security officer (ISSO).","rule_id_src":"SV-253268r1051039_rule","group_title":"SRG-OS-000468-GPOS-00212","false_positives":"","uuid":"7002A0CE-6D7C-1014-BA05-AABE41D58A22","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5471","stig_uuid":"6FDFF1B9-6D7C-1014-8C20-99EC6B15618D","severity":"low","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_reviewed","group_id":"V-253268","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000468-GPOS-00212","id":"V-253268"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Review local accounts and verify their necessity. Disable or delete any active accounts that have not been used in the last 35 days.","discussion":"Outdated or unused accounts provide penetration points that may go undetected. Inactive accounts must be deleted if no longer necessary or, if still required, disable until needed.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000468-GPOS-00212, SRG-OS-000118-GPOS-00060","group_id_src":"V-253268"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-253269r958702","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:51\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT I, V-253269, SV-253269r958702, SRG-OS-000312-GPOS-00123)\n","rule_version":"WN11-00-000070","rule_title":"Only accounts responsible for the administration of a system must have Administrator rights on the system.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-ocil.xml","name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows11:questionnaire:3101"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-002165"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Run \"Computer Management\".\nNavigate to System Tools &gt;&gt; Local Users and Groups &gt;&gt; Groups.\nReview the members of the Administrators group.\nOnly the appropriate administrator groups or accounts responsible for administration of the system may be members of the group.\n\nFor domain-joined workstations, the Domain Admins group must be replaced by a domain workstation administrator group.\n\nStandard user accounts must not be members of the local administrator group.\n\nIf prohibited accounts are members of the local administrators group, this is a finding.\n\nThe built-in Administrator account or other required administrative accounts would not be a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-253269r958702_rule","group_title":"SRG-OS-000312-GPOS-00123","false_positives":"","uuid":"7002A651-6D7C-1014-9261-CB58DD603FB8","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5471","stig_uuid":"6FDFF1B9-6D7C-1014-8C20-99EC6B15618D","severity":"high","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_reviewed","group_id":"V-253269","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000312-GPOS-00123","id":"V-253269"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Configure the system to include only administrator groups or accounts that are responsible for the system in the local Administrators group.\n\nFor domain-joined workstations, the Domain Admins group must be replaced by a domain workstation administrator group.\n\nRemove any standard user accounts.","discussion":"An account that does not have Administrator duties must not have Administrator rights. Such rights would allow the account to bypass or modify required security restrictions on that machine and make it vulnerable to attack.\n\nSystem administrators must log on to systems only using accounts with the minimum level of authority necessary.\n\nFor domain-joined workstations, the Domain Admins group must be replaced by a domain workstation administrator group (see V-36434 in the Active Directory Domain STIG). Restricting highly privileged accounts from the local Administrators group helps mitigate the risk of privilege escalation resulting from credential theft attacks.\n\nStandard user accounts must not be members of the local administrators group.","group_id_src":"V-253269"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-253270r991589","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:51\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT II, V-253270, SV-253270r991589, SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227)\n","rule_version":"WN11-00-000075","rule_title":"Only accounts responsible for the backup operations must be members of the Backup Operators group.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-ocil.xml","name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows11:questionnaire:3301"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Run \"Computer Management\".\nNavigate to System Tools &gt;&gt; Local Users and Groups &gt;&gt; Groups.\nReview the members of the Backup Operators group.\n\nIf the group contains no accounts, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the group contains any accounts, the accounts must be specifically for backup functions.\n\nIf the group contains any standard user accounts used for performing normal user tasks, this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-253270r991589_rule","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","false_positives":"","uuid":"7002AB3D-6D7C-1014-BF05-AAC8A374ADCA","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5471","stig_uuid":"6FDFF1B9-6D7C-1014-8C20-99EC6B15618D","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_reviewed","group_id":"V-253270","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","id":"V-253270"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Create separate accounts for backup operations for users with this privilege.","discussion":"Backup Operators are able to read and write to any file in the system, regardless of the rights assigned to it. Backup and restore rights permit users to circumvent the file access restrictions present on NTFS disk drives for backup and restore purposes. Members of the Backup Operators group must have separate logon accounts for performing backup duties.","group_id_src":"V-253270"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-253271r958702","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:51\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT II, V-253271, SV-253271r958702, SRG-OS-000312-GPOS-00124)\n","rule_version":"WN11-00-000080","rule_title":"Only authorized user accounts must be allowed to create or run virtual machines on Windows 11 systems.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-ocil.xml","name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows11:questionnaire:3501"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-002165"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"If a hosted hypervisor (Hyper-V, VMware Workstation, etc.) is installed on the system, verify only authorized user accounts are allowed to run virtual machines.\n\nFor Hyper-V, run \"Computer Management\".\nNavigate to System Tools &gt;&gt; Local Users and Groups &gt;&gt; Groups.\nDouble click on \"Hyper-V Administrators\".\n\nIf any unauthorized groups or user accounts are listed in \"Members:\", this is a finding.\n\nFor hosted hypervisors other than Hyper-V, verify only authorized user accounts have access to run the virtual machines. Restrictions may be enforced by access to the physical system, software restriction policies, or access restrictions built into the application.\n\nIf any unauthorized groups or user accounts have access to create or run virtual machines, this is a finding.\n\nAll users authorized to create or run virtual machines must be documented with the ISSM/ISSO. Accounts nested within group accounts must be documented as individual accounts and not the group accounts.","rule_id_src":"SV-253271r958702_rule","group_title":"SRG-OS-000312-GPOS-00124","false_positives":"","uuid":"7002B005-6D7C-1014-A064-D31FC17F81A6","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5471","stig_uuid":"6FDFF1B9-6D7C-1014-8C20-99EC6B15618D","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_reviewed","group_id":"V-253271","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000312-GPOS-00124","id":"V-253271"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"For Hyper-V, remove any unauthorized groups or user accounts from the \"Hyper-V Administrators\" group.\n\nFor hosted hypervisors other than Hyper-V, restrict access to create or run virtual machines to authorized user accounts only.","discussion":"Allowing other operating systems to run on a secure system may allow users to circumvent security. For Hyper-V, preventing unauthorized users from being assigned to the Hyper-V Administrators group will prevent them from accessing or creating virtual machines on the system. The Hyper-V Hypervisor is used by virtualization-based Security features such as Credential Guard on Windows 11; however, it is not the full Hyper-V installation.","group_id_src":"V-253271"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-253272r991589","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:51\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT III, V-253272, SV-253272r991589, SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227)\n","rule_version":"WN11-00-000085","rule_title":"Standard local user accounts must not exist on a system in a domain.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-ocil.xml","name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows11:questionnaire:3701"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Run \"Computer Management\".\nNavigate to System Tools &gt;&gt; Local Users and Groups &gt;&gt; Users.\n\nIf local users other than the accounts listed below exist on a workstation in a domain, this is a finding. \n\nFor standalone or nondomain-joined systems, this is Not Applicable.\n\nBuilt-in Administrator account (Disabled)\nBuilt-in Guest account (Disabled)\nBuilt-in DefaultAccount (Disabled)\nBuilt-in defaultuser0 (Disabled)\nBuilt-in WDAGUtilityAccount (Disabled)\nLocal administrator account(s)\n\nAll of the built-in accounts may not exist on a system, depending on the Windows 11 version.","rule_id_src":"SV-253272r991589_rule","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","false_positives":"","uuid":"7002B4A9-6D7C-1014-AD18-CDBA72B89B18","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5471","stig_uuid":"6FDFF1B9-6D7C-1014-8C20-99EC6B15618D","severity":"low","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_reviewed","group_id":"V-253272","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","id":"V-253272"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Limit local user accounts on domain-joined systems. Remove any unauthorized local accounts.","discussion":"To minimize potential points of attack, local user accounts, other than built-in accounts and local administrator accounts, must not exist on a workstation in a domain. Users must log on to workstations in a domain with their domain accounts.","group_id_src":"V-253272"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-253273r1051040","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:51\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Accounts must be configured to require password expiration.)\nResult Analysis :        Existence requirement is 'none_exists' and 1 collected item exists, so result is false\n","rule_version":"WN11-00-000090","rule_title":"Accounts must be configured to require password expiration.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows:def:253273"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-004066","CCI-000199"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Run \"Computer Management\".\nNavigate to System Tools &gt;&gt; Local Users and Groups &gt;&gt; Users.\nDouble-click each active account.\n\nIf \"Password never expires\" is selected for any account, this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-253273r1051040_rule","group_title":"SRG-OS-000076-GPOS-00044","false_positives":"","uuid":"7002B967-6D7C-1014-8074-90B11874C6DF","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5471","stig_uuid":"6FDFF1B9-6D7C-1014-8C20-99EC6B15618D","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_id":"V-253273","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000076-GPOS-00044","id":"V-253273"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Configure all passwords to expire.\nRun \"Computer Management\".\nNavigate to System Tools &gt;&gt; Local Users and Groups &gt;&gt; Users.\nDouble-click each active account.\nEnsure \"Password never expires\" is not checked on all active accounts.","discussion":"Passwords that do not expire increase exposure with a greater probability of being discovered or cracked.","group_id_src":"V-253273"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-253274r1016661","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:51\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Network access: Let Everyone permissions apply to anonymous users is set to 'Disabled')\nTest            :   true (System drive root directory permissions must conform to minimum requirements.)\nTest            :   true (Windows installation directory permissions must conform to minimum requirements.)\nTest            :   true (Program Files directory permissions must conform to minimum requirements.)\nTest            :   true (Program Files (x86) directory permissions must conform to minimum requirements.)\n","rule_version":"WN11-00-000095","rule_title":"Permissions for system files and directories must conform to minimum requirements.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows:def:253274"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-002165"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The default file system permissions are adequate when the Security Option \"Network access: Let Everyone permissions apply to anonymous users\" is set to \"Disabled\" (WN11-SO-000160).\n\nIf the default file system permissions are maintained and the referenced option is set to \"Disabled\", this is not a finding.\n\nVerify the default permissions for the sample directories below. Non-privileged groups such as Users or Authenticated Users must not have greater than read &amp; execute permissions except where noted as defaults. (Individual accounts must not be used to assign permissions.)\n\nSelect the \"Security\" tab, and the \"Advanced\" button.\n\nC:\\\nType - \"Allow\" for all\nInherited from - \"None\" for all\nPrincipal - Access - Applies to\nAdministrators - Full control - This folder, subfolders, and files\nSYSTEM - Full control - This folder, subfolders, and files\nUsers - Read &amp; execute - This folder, subfolders, and files\nAuthenticated Users - Modify - Subfolders and files only\nAuthenticated Users - Create folders / append data - This folder only\n\n\\Program Files\nType - \"Allow\" for all\nInherited from - \"None\" for all\nPrincipal - Access - Applies to\nTrustedInstaller - Full control - This folder and subfolders\nSYSTEM - Modify - This folder only\nSYSTEM - Full control - Subfolders and files only\nAdministrators - Modify - This folder only\nAdministrators - Full control - Subfolders and files only\nUsers - Read &amp; execute - This folder, subfolders, and files\nCREATOR OWNER - Full control - Subfolders and files only\nALL APPLICATION PACKAGES - Read &amp; execute - This folder, subfolders, and files\nALL RESTRICTED APPLICATION PACKAGES - Read &amp; execute - This folder, subfolders, and files\n\n\\Windows\nType - \"Allow\" for all\nInherited from - \"None\" for all\nPrincipal - Access - Applies to\nTrustedInstaller - Full control - This folder and subfolders\nSYSTEM - Modify - This folder only\nSYSTEM - Full control - Subfolders and files only\nAdministrators - Modify - This folder only\nAdministrators - Full control - Subfolders and files only\nUsers - Read &amp; execute - This folder, subfolders, and files\nCREATOR OWNER - Full control - Subfolders and files only\nALL APPLICATION PACKAGES - Read &amp; execute - This folder, subfolders, and files\nALL RESTRICTED APPLICATION PACKAGES - Read &amp; execute - This folder, subfolders, and files\n\nAlternately use icacls.\n\nRun \"CMD\" as administrator.\nEnter \"icacls\" followed by the directory.\n\nicacls c:\\\nicacls \"c:\\program files\"\nicacls c:\\windows\n\nThe following results will be displayed as each is entered:\n\nc:\\\nS-1-15-3-65536-1888954469-739942743-1668119174-2468466756-4239452838-1296943325-355587736-700089176 (S,RD,X,RA)\nBUILTIN\\Administrators:(OI)(CI)(F)\nNT AUTHORITY\\SYSTEM:(OI)(CI)(F)\nBUILTIN\\Users:(OI)(CI)(RX)\nNT AUTHORITY\\Authenticated Users:(OI)(CI)(IO)(M)\nNT AUTHORITY\\Authenticated Users:(AD)\nMandatory Label\\High Mandatory Level:(OI)(NP)(IO)(NW)\nSuccessfully processed 1 files; Failed processing 0 files\n\nc:\\program files \nNT SERVICE\\TrustedInstaller:(F)\nNT SERVICE\\TrustedInstaller:(CI)(IO)(F)\nNT AUTHORITY\\SYSTEM:(M)\nNT AUTHORITY\\SYSTEM:(OI)(CI)(IO)(F)\nBUILTIN\\Administrators:(M)\nBUILTIN\\Administrators:(OI)(CI)(IO)(F)\nBUILTIN\\Users:(RX)\nBUILTIN\\Users:(OI)(CI)(IO)(GR,GE)\nCREATOR OWNER:(OI)(CI)(IO)(F)\nAPPLICATION PACKAGE AUTHORITY\\ALL APPLICATION PACKAGES:(RX)\nAPPLICATION PACKAGE AUTHORITY\\ALL APPLICATION PACKAGES:(OI)(CI)(IO)(GR,GE)\nAPPLICATION PACKAGE AUTHORITY\\ALL RESTRICTED APPLICATION PACKAGES:(RX)\nAPPLICATION PACKAGE AUTHORITY\\ALL RESTRICTED APPLICATION PACKAGES:(OI)(CI)(IO)(GR,GE)\nSuccessfully processed 1 files; Failed processing 0 files\n\nc:\\windows\nNT SERVICE\\TrustedInstaller:(F)\nNT SERVICE\\TrustedInstaller:(CI)(IO)(F)\nNT AUTHORITY\\SYSTEM:(M)\nNT AUTHORITY\\SYSTEM:(OI)(CI)(IO)(F)\nBUILTIN\\Administrators:(M)\nBUILTIN\\Administrators:(OI)(CI)(IO)(F)\nBUILTIN\\Users:(RX)\nBUILTIN\\Users:(OI)(CI)(IO)(GR,GE)\nCREATOR OWNER:(OI)(CI)(IO)(F)\nAPPLICATION PACKAGE AUTHORITY\\ALL APPLICATION PACKAGES:(RX)\nAPPLICATION PACKAGE AUTHORITY\\ALL APPLICATION PACKAGES:(OI)(CI)(IO)(GR,GE)\nAPPLICATION PACKAGE AUTHORITY\\ALL RESTRICTED APPLICATION PACKAGES:(RX)\nAPPLICATION PACKAGE AUTHORITY\\ALL RESTRICTED APPLICATION PACKAGES:(OI)(CI)(IO)(GR,GE)\nSuccessfully processed 1 files; Failed processing 0 files","rule_id_src":"SV-253274r1016661_rule","group_title":"SRG-OS-000312-GPOS-00122","false_positives":"","uuid":"7002BF9D-6D7C-1014-B625-B91579B02E56","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5471","stig_uuid":"6FDFF1B9-6D7C-1014-8C20-99EC6B15618D","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_id":"V-253274","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000312-GPOS-00122","id":"V-253274"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Maintain the default file system permissions and configure the Security Option: \"Network access: Let everyone permissions apply to anonymous users\" to \"Disabled\" (WN11-SO-000160).","discussion":"Changing the system's file and directory permissions allows the possibility of unauthorized and anonymous modification to the operating system and installed applications.","group_id_src":"V-253274"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-253275r958478","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:51\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('Internet Information Services' feature is not installed)\nTest            :     true ('Internet Information Services Hostable Web Core' feature is not installed)\n","rule_version":"WN11-00-000100","rule_title":"Internet Information System (IIS) or its subcomponents must not be installed on a workstation.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows11:def:253275"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Verify it has not been installed on the system.\n\nRun \"Programs and Features\".\nSelect \"Turn Windows features on or off\".\n\nIf the entries for \"Internet Information Services\" or \"Internet Information Services Hostable Web Core\" are selected, this is a finding.\n\nIf an application requires IIS or a subset to be installed to function, this needs be documented with the ISSO. In addition, any applicable requirements from the IIS STIG must be addressed.","rule_id_src":"SV-253275r958478_rule","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","false_positives":"","uuid":"7002C4A7-6D7C-1014-B135-C293F9D9DAF0","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5471","stig_uuid":"6FDFF1B9-6D7C-1014-8C20-99EC6B15618D","severity":"high","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_id":"V-253275","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","id":"V-253275"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Uninstall \"Internet Information Services\" or \"Internet Information Services Hostable Web Core\" from the system.","discussion":"IIS is not installed by default. Installation of Internet Information System (IIS) may allow unauthorized internet services to be hosted. Websites must only be hosted on servers that have been designed for that purpose and can be adequately secured.","group_id_src":"V-253275"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-253276r958480","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:51\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (SNMP Shall Not Be Installed)\n","rule_version":"WN11-00-000105","rule_title":"Simple Network Management Protocol (SNMP) must not be installed on the system.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows:def:253276"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000382"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Verify SNMP has not been installed.\n\nNavigate to the Windows\\System32 directory.\n\nIf the \"SNMP\" application exists, this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-253276r958480_rule","group_title":"SRG-OS-000096-GPOS-00050","false_positives":"","uuid":"7002C95C-6D7C-1014-A94C-F92EF708DA18","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5471","stig_uuid":"6FDFF1B9-6D7C-1014-8C20-99EC6B15618D","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_id":"V-253276","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000096-GPOS-00050","id":"V-253276"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Uninstall \"Simple Network Management Protocol (SNMP)\" from the system.\n\nRun \"Programs and Features\".\nSelect \"Turn Windows Features on or off\".\nDe-select \"Simple Network Management Protocol (SNMP)\".","discussion":"\"SNMP\" is not installed by default. Some protocols and services do not support required security features, such as encrypting passwords or traffic.","group_id_src":"V-253276"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-253277r958478","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:51\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true (Check to make sure the Simple TCP/IP Services server feature is not present.)\n","rule_version":"WN11-00-000110","rule_title":"Simple TCP/IP Services must not be installed on the system.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows11:def:253277"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Verify Simple TCP/IP Services has not been installed.\n\nRun \"Services.msc\".\n\nIf \"Simple TCP/IP Services\" is listed, this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-253277r958478_rule","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","false_positives":"","uuid":"7002CE06-6D7C-1014-8C27-D221DD9F1483","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5471","stig_uuid":"6FDFF1B9-6D7C-1014-8C20-99EC6B15618D","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_id":"V-253277","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","id":"V-253277"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Uninstall \"Simple TCPIP Services (i.e. echo, daytime etc.)\" from the system.\n\nRun \"Programs and Features\".\nSelect \"Turn Windows Features on or off\".\nDe-select \"Simple TCPIP Services (i.e. echo, daytime etc.)\".","discussion":"\"Simple TCP/IP Services\" is not installed by default. Some protocols and services do not support required security features, such as encrypting passwords or traffic.","group_id_src":"V-253277"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-253278r958480","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:51\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true (The Telnet Client is not installed on the system)\n","rule_version":"WN11-00-000115","rule_title":"The Telnet Client must not be installed on the system.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows11:def:253278"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000382"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Verify Telnet Client has not been installed.\n\nNavigate to the Windows\\System32 directory.\n\nIf the \"telnet\" application exists, this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-253278r958480_rule","group_title":"SRG-OS-000096-GPOS-00050","false_positives":"","uuid":"7002D3C0-6D7C-1014-AD63-BB3FA8AE07BD","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5471","stig_uuid":"6FDFF1B9-6D7C-1014-8C20-99EC6B15618D","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_id":"V-253278","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000096-GPOS-00050","id":"V-253278"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Uninstall \"Telnet Client\" from the system.\n\nRun \"Programs and Features\".\nSelect \"Turn Windows Features on or off\".\n\nDe-select \"Telnet Client\".","discussion":"The \"Telnet Client\" is not installed by default. Some protocols and services do not support required security features, such as encrypting passwords or traffic.","group_id_src":"V-253278"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-253279r958480","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:51\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true (The TFTP Client is not installed on the system)\n","rule_version":"WN11-00-000120","rule_title":"The TFTP Client must not be installed on the system.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows11:def:253279"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000382"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Verify TFTP Client has not been installed.\n\nNavigate to the Windows\\System32 directory.\n\nIf the \"TFTP\" application exists, this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-253279r958480_rule","group_title":"SRG-OS-000096-GPOS-00050","false_positives":"","uuid":"7002D9A5-6D7C-1014-AAB8-C540BE14853B","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5471","stig_uuid":"6FDFF1B9-6D7C-1014-8C20-99EC6B15618D","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_id":"V-253279","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000096-GPOS-00050","id":"V-253279"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Uninstall \"TFTP Client\" from the system.\n\nRun \"Programs and Features\".\nSelect \"Turn Windows Features on or off\".\nDe-select \"TFTP Client\".","discussion":"The \"TFTP Client\" is not installed by default. Some protocols and services do not support required security features, such as encrypting passwords or traffic.","group_id_src":"V-253279"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-253280r991589","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:51\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Software certificate installation files must be removed. Remove .p12 files)\nResult Analysis :        Existence requirement is 'none_exists' and 8 collected items exist, so result is false\nTest            :   true (Software certificate installation files must be removed. Remove .pfx files)\n","rule_version":"WN11-00-000130","rule_title":"Software certificate installation files must be removed from Windows 11.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows:def:253280"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Search all drives for *.p12 and *.pfx files.\n\nIf any files with these extensions exist, this is a finding.\n\nThis does not apply to server-based applications that have a requirement for .p12 certificate files (e.g., Oracle Wallet Manager) or Adobe PreFlight certificate files. Some applications create files with extensions of .p12 that are not certificate installation files. Removal of non-certificate installation files from systems is not required. These must be documented with the ISSO.","rule_id_src":"SV-253280r991589_rule","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","false_positives":"","uuid":"7002E2C8-6D7C-1014-944C-960F38C629D8","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5471","stig_uuid":"6FDFF1B9-6D7C-1014-8C20-99EC6B15618D","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_id":"V-253280","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","id":"V-253280"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Remove any certificate installation files (*.p12 and *.pfx) found on a system.\n\nNote: This does not apply to server-based applications that have a requirement for .p12 certificate files (e.g., Oracle Wallet Manager) or Adobe PreFlight certificate files.","discussion":"Use of software certificates and their accompanying installation files for end users to access resources is less secure than the use of hardware-based certificates.","group_id_src":"V-253280"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-253281r991589","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:51\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :   false (Verify a 3rd party firewall is installed and enabled via Security Center.)\nTest            :   true (Verify Windows defender firewall is enabled.)\n","rule_version":"WN11-00-000135","rule_title":"A host-based firewall must be installed and enabled on the system.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows:def:253281"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Determine if a host-based firewall is installed and enabled on the system. If a host-based firewall is not installed and enabled on the system, this is a finding.\n\nThe configuration requirements will be determined by the applicable firewall STIG.","rule_id_src":"SV-253281r991589_rule","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","false_positives":"","uuid":"7002E8A9-6D7C-1014-A4C7-9BC348EB212C","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5471","stig_uuid":"6FDFF1B9-6D7C-1014-8C20-99EC6B15618D","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_id":"V-253281","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","id":"V-253281"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Install and enable a host-based firewall on the system.","discussion":"A firewall provides a line of defense against attack, allowing or blocking inbound and outbound connections based on a set of rules.","group_id_src":"V-253281"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-253282r991593","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:51\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT II, V-253282, SV-253282r991593, SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00232)\n","rule_version":"WN11-00-000140","rule_title":"Inbound exceptions to the firewall on Windows 11 domain workstations must only allow authorized remote management hosts.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-ocil.xml","name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows11:questionnaire:5701"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Verify firewall exceptions to inbound connections on domain workstations include only authorized remote management hosts.\n\nIf allowed inbound exceptions are not limited to authorized remote management hosts, this is a finding.\n\nReview inbound firewall exceptions.\nComputer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Windows Defender Firewall with Advanced Security &gt;&gt; Windows Defender Firewall with Advanced Security &gt;&gt; Inbound Rules (this link will be in the right pane)\n\nFor any inbound rules that allow connections view the Scope for Remote IP address. This may be defined as an IP address, subnet, or range. The rule must apply to all firewall profiles.\n\nIf a third-party firewall is used, ensure comparable settings are in place.","rule_id_src":"SV-253282r991593_rule","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00232","false_positives":"","uuid":"7002EDA6-6D7C-1014-B5E7-C2E56E200E2F","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5471","stig_uuid":"6FDFF1B9-6D7C-1014-8C20-99EC6B15618D","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_reviewed","group_id":"V-253282","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00232","id":"V-253282"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Configure firewall exceptions to inbound connections on domain workstations to include only authorized remote management hosts.\n\nConfigure only inbound connection exceptions for authorized remote management hosts.\nComputer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Windows Defender Firewall with Advanced Security &gt;&gt; Windows Defender Firewall with Advanced Security &gt;&gt; Inbound Rules (this link will be in the right pane)\n\nFor any inbound rules that allow connections, configure the Scope for Remote IP address to those of authorized remote management hosts. This may be defined as an IP address, subnet or range. Apply the rule to all firewall profiles.\n\nIf a third-party firewall is used, configure inbound exceptions to only include authorized remote management hosts.","discussion":"Allowing inbound access to domain workstations from other systems may allow lateral movement across systems if credentials are compromised. Limiting inbound connections only from authorized remote management systems will help limit this exposure.","group_id_src":"V-253282"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-253284r958928","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:51\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     false (SEHOP is turned on and properly configured)\nResult Analysis :          Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Session Manager\\kernel\\DisableExceptionChainValidation'.  Existence requirement is 'all_exist' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"WN11-00-000150","rule_title":"Structured Exception Handling Overwrite Protection (SEHOP) must be enabled.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows11:def:253284"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-002824"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Verify SEHOP is turned on.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Session Manager\\kernel\\\n\nValue Name: DisableExceptionChainValidation\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0)","rule_id_src":"SV-253284r958928_rule","group_title":"SRG-OS-000433-GPOS-00192","false_positives":"","uuid":"7002F266-6D7C-1014-BC40-EDB7F0825C23","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5471","stig_uuid":"6FDFF1B9-6D7C-1014-8C20-99EC6B15618D","severity":"high","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_id":"V-253284","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000433-GPOS-00192","id":"V-253284"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; MS Security Guide &gt;&gt; \"Enable Structured Exception Handling Overwrite Protection (SEHOP)\" to \"Enabled\".\n\nThis policy setting requires the installation of the SecGuide custom templates included with the STIG package. \"SecGuide.admx\" and \"SecGuide.adml\" must be copied to the \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions and \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions\\en-US directories respectively.","discussion":"Attackers are constantly looking for vulnerabilities in systems and applications. Structured Exception Handling Overwrite Protection (SEHOP) blocks exploits that use the Structured Exception Handling overwrite technique, a common buffer overflow attack.","group_id_src":"V-253284"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-253285r1153425","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:51\nResult: notapplicableRule Result     : Not Applicable\n","rule_version":"WN11-00-000155","rule_title":"The Windows PowerShell 2.0 feature must be disabled on the system.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows11:def:253285"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"For Windows 11 version 24H2 and newer, this requirement is Not Applicable.\n\nRun \"Windows PowerShell\" with elevated privileges (run as administrator).\n\nEnter the following:\nGet-WindowsOptionalFeature -Online | Where FeatureName -like *PowerShellv2*\n\nIf either of the following have a \"State\" of \"Enabled\", this is a finding.\n\nFeatureName : MicrosoftWindowsPowerShellV2\nState : Enabled\nFeatureName : MicrosoftWindowsPowerShellV2Root\nState : Enabled\n\nAlternately:\nSearch for \"Features\".\n\nSelect \"Turn Windows features on or off\".\n\nIf \"Windows PowerShell 2.0\" (whether the subcategory of \"Windows PowerShell 2.0 Engine\" is selected or not) is selected, this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-253285r1153425_rule","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","false_positives":"","uuid":"7002F73C-6D7C-1014-B7B6-D549515C1053","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5471","stig_uuid":"6FDFF1B9-6D7C-1014-8C20-99EC6B15618D","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_applicable","group_id":"V-253285","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","id":"V-253285"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Disable \"Windows PowerShell 2.0\" on the system.\n\nRun \"Windows PowerShell\" with elevated privileges (run as administrator).\nEnter the following:\nDisable-WindowsOptionalFeature -Online -FeatureName MicrosoftWindowsPowerShellV2Root\n\nThis command must disable both \"MicrosoftWindowsPowerShellV2Root\" and \"MicrosoftWindowsPowerShellV2\", which correspond to \"Windows PowerShell 2.0\" and \"Windows PowerShell 2.0 Engine\" respectively in \"Turn Windows features on or off\".\n\nAlternately:\nSearch for \"Features\".\nSelect \"Turn Windows features on or off\".\nDe-select \"Windows PowerShell 2.0\".","discussion":"Windows PowerShell 5.0 added advanced logging features, which can provide additional detail when malware has been run on a system. Disabling the Windows PowerShell 2.0 mitigates against a downgrade attack that evades the Windows PowerShell 5.0 script block logging feature.","group_id_src":"V-253285"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-253286r958478","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:51\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nCriteria        :     true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :       true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :         true ('SMB 1.0/CIFS File Sharing Support' feature is not installed)\nTest            :         true ('Configure SMBv1 Server' is set to 'Disabled')\nCriteria        :       true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :         true ('SMB 1.0/CIFS File Sharing Support' feature is not installed)\nTest            :         false ('Configure SMBv1 client driver' is set to 'Enabled' with 'Disable driver (recommended)' selected for 'Configure MrxSmb10 driver')\nTest            :     true ('SMB 1.0/CIFS File Sharing Support' feature is not installed)\n","rule_version":"WN11-00-000160","rule_title":"The Server Message Block (SMB) v1 protocol must be disabled on the system.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows11:def:253286"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Different methods are available to disable SMBv1 on Windows 11. This is the preferred method, however if WN11-00-000165 and WN11-00-000170 are configured, this is NA.\n\nRun \"Windows PowerShell\" with elevated privileges (run as administrator).\n\nEnter the following:\nGet-WindowsOptionalFeature -Online | Where FeatureName -eq SMB1Protocol\n\nIf \"State : Enabled\" is returned, this is a finding.\n\nAlternately:\nSearch for \"Features\".\n\nSelect \"Turn Windows features on or off\".\n\nIf \"SMB 1.0/CIFS File Sharing Support\" is selected, this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-253286r958478_rule","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","false_positives":"","uuid":"7002FC05-6D7C-1014-A6C9-9ED759807259","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5471","stig_uuid":"6FDFF1B9-6D7C-1014-8C20-99EC6B15618D","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_id":"V-253286","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","id":"V-253286"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Disable the SMBv1 protocol.\n\nRun \"Windows PowerShell\" with elevated privileges (run as administrator).\n\nEnter the following:\nDisable-WindowsOptionalFeature -Online -FeatureName SMB1Protocol\n\nAlternately:\nSearch for \"Features\".\n\nSelect \"Turn Windows features on or off\".\n\nDe-select \"SMB 1.0/CIFS File Sharing Support\".","discussion":"SMBv1 is a legacy protocol that uses the MD5 algorithm as part of SMB. MD5 is known to be vulnerable to a number of attacks such as collision and preimage attacks as well as not being FIPS compliant.\n\nDisabling SMBv1 support may prevent access to file or print sharing resources with systems or devices that only support SMBv1. File shares and print services hosted on Windows Server 2003 are an example, however Windows Server 2003 is no longer a supported operating system. Some older Network Attached Storage (NAS) devices may only support SMBv1.","group_id_src":"V-253286"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-253287r958478","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:51\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :     true ('SMB 1.0/CIFS File Sharing Support' feature is not installed)\nTest            :     true ('Configure SMBv1 Server' is set to 'Disabled')\n","rule_version":"WN11-00-000165","rule_title":"The Server Message Block (SMB) v1 protocol must be disabled on the SMB server.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows11:def:253287"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Different methods are available to disable SMBv1 on Windows 11, if WN11-00-000160 is configured, this is NA.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\LanmanServer\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: SMB1\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0)","rule_id_src":"SV-253287r958478_rule","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","false_positives":"","uuid":"70030245-6D7C-1014-8E62-96309FDEFC2D","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5471","stig_uuid":"6FDFF1B9-6D7C-1014-8C20-99EC6B15618D","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_id":"V-253287","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","id":"V-253287"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; MS Security Guide &gt;&gt; \"Configure SMBv1 Server\" to \"Disabled\".\n\nThis policy setting requires the installation of the SecGuide custom templates included with the STIG package. \"SecGuide.admx\" and \"SecGuide.adml\" must be copied to the \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions and \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions\\en-US directories, respectively.  \n\nThe system must be restarted for the change to take effect.","discussion":"SMBv1 is a legacy protocol that uses the MD5 algorithm as part of SMB. MD5 is known to be vulnerable to a number of attacks such as collision and preimage attacks as well as not being FIPS compliant.\n\nDisabling SMBv1 support may prevent access to file or print sharing resources with systems or devices that only support SMBv1. File shares and print services hosted on Windows Server 2003 are an example, however Windows Server 2003 is no longer a supported operating system. Some older network attached devices may only support SMBv1.","group_id_src":"V-253287"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-253288r958478","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:51\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :     true ('SMB 1.0/CIFS File Sharing Support' feature is not installed)\nTest            :     false ('Configure SMBv1 client driver' is set to 'Enabled' with 'Disable driver (recommended)' selected for 'Configure MrxSmb10 driver')\n","rule_version":"WN11-00-000170","rule_title":"The Server Message Block (SMB) v1 protocol must be disabled on the SMB client.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows11:def:253288"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Different methods are available to disable SMBv1 on Windows 11, if WN11-00-000160is configured, this is NA.\n\nIf the following registry value is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\mrxsmb10\\\n\nValue Name: Start\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000004 (4)","rule_id_src":"SV-253288r958478_rule","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","false_positives":"","uuid":"7003087D-6D7C-1014-AD8F-E32F39B90321","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5471","stig_uuid":"6FDFF1B9-6D7C-1014-8C20-99EC6B15618D","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_id":"V-253288","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","id":"V-253288"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; MS Security Guide &gt;&gt; \"Configure SMBv1 client driver\" to \"Enabled\" with \"Disable driver (recommended)\" selected for \"Configure MrxSmb10 driver\".\n\nThis policy setting requires the installation of the SecGuide custom templates included with the STIG package. \"SecGuide.admx\" and \"SecGuide.adml\" must be copied to the \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions and \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions\\en-US directories, respectively.  \n\nThe system must be restarted for the changes to take effect.","discussion":"SMBv1 is a legacy protocol that uses the MD5 algorithm as part of SMB. MD5 is known to be vulnerable to a number of attacks such as collision and preimage attacks as well as not being FIPS compliant.\n\nDisabling SMBv1 support may prevent access to file or print sharing resources with systems or devices that only support SMBv1. File shares and print services hosted on Windows Server 2003 are an example, however Windows Server 2003 is no longer a supported operating system. Some older network attached devices may only support SMBv1.","group_id_src":"V-253288"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-253289r958478","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:51\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     false (The Secondary Logon service Startup Type is Disabled or the service is uninstalled)\nResult Analysis :          startmode = 'Manual' failed test of 'equals' compared to 'Disabled' \n","rule_version":"WN11-00-000175","rule_title":"The Secondary Logon service must be disabled on Windows 11.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows11:def:253289"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Run \"Services.msc\".\n\nLocate the \"Secondary Logon\" service.\n\nIf the \"Startup Type\" is not \"Disabled\" or the \"Status\" is \"Running\", this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-253289r958478_rule","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","false_positives":"","uuid":"70030EAC-6D7C-1014-B0CE-E0B5BCC55F51","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5471","stig_uuid":"6FDFF1B9-6D7C-1014-8C20-99EC6B15618D","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_id":"V-253289","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","id":"V-253289"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Configure the \"Secondary Logon\" service \"Startup Type\" to \"Disabled\".","discussion":"The Secondary Logon service provides a means for entering alternate credentials, typically used to run commands with elevated privileges. Using privileged credentials in a standard user session can expose those credentials to theft.","group_id_src":"V-253289"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-253290r991589","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:51\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Orphaned security identifiers (SIDs) must be removed from user rights.)\n","rule_version":"WN11-00-000190","rule_title":"Orphaned security identifiers (SIDs) must be removed from user rights on Windows 11.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows:def:253290"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Review the effective User Rights setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy &gt;&gt; Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; User Rights Assignment.\n\nReview each User Right listed for any unresolved SIDs to determine whether they are valid, such as due to being temporarily disconnected from the domain. (Unresolved SIDs have the format of \"*S-1-..\".)\n\nIf any unresolved SIDs exist and are not for currently valid accounts or groups, this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-253290r991589_rule","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","false_positives":"","uuid":"70031361-6D7C-1014-9CB0-F62E9D3226AA","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5471","stig_uuid":"6FDFF1B9-6D7C-1014-8C20-99EC6B15618D","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_id":"V-253290","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","id":"V-253290"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Remove any unresolved SIDs found in User Rights assignments and determined to not be for currently valid accounts or groups by removing the accounts or groups from the appropriate group policy.","discussion":"Accounts or groups given rights on a system may show up as unresolved SIDs for various reasons including deletion of the accounts or groups. If the account or group objects are reanimated, there is a potential they may still have rights no longer intended. Valid domain accounts or groups may also show up as unresolved SIDs if a connection to the domain cannot be established for some reason.","group_id_src":"V-253290"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-253291r1153422","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:51\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Bluetooth radio must be turned off.)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\PolicyManager\\current\\device\\Connectivity\\AllowBluetooth'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"WN11-00-000210","rule_title":"Bluetooth must be turned off unless approved by the organization.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows:def:253291"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"This is NA if the system does not have Bluetooth.\n\nVerify the Bluetooth radio is turned off unless approved by the organization. If it is not, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\PolicyManager\\current\\device\\Connectivity\\\n\nValue Name: AllowBluetooth\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0)\n\nApproval must be documented with the ISSO.","rule_id_src":"SV-253291r1153422_rule","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","false_positives":"","uuid":"700318E4-6D7C-1014-B059-E2590B6DB81B","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5471","stig_uuid":"6FDFF1B9-6D7C-1014-8C20-99EC6B15618D","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_id":"V-253291","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","id":"V-253291"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Turn off Bluetooth radios not organizationally approved.\n\nFor systems managed by Intune, apply the DOD Windows 11 STIG Settings Catalog (or equivalent Intune policy) found in the Intune policy package available on cyber.mil.\nSteps to create an Intune policy:\n1. Sign in to the Intune admin center &gt;&gt; Devices &gt;&gt; Configuration &gt;&gt; Create &gt;&gt; New Policy.\n2. Platform: Windows 10 and later. Profile type: Settings Catalog, then click \"Create\".\n3. Basics: Provide a Name and Description of the profile, then click \"Next\".\n4. Configuration settings: Click \"+ Add settings\" and search for connectivity under the Settings picker. Under the Connectivity category, check the box next to Allow Bluetooth setting. Choose the first option, \"Disallow Bluetooth\", then click \"Next\".\n5. Scope tags: (optional), then click \"Next\".\n6. Assignments: Assign the policy to Entra security groups that contain the target users or devices, then click \"Next\".\n7. Review + create: Review the deployment summary, then click \"Create\".","discussion":"If not configured properly, Bluetooth may allow rogue devices to communicate with a system. If a rogue device is paired with a system, there is potential for sensitive information to be compromised.","group_id_src":"V-253291"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-253293r991589","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:51\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (The system must notify the user when a Bluetooth device attempts to connect.)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Microsoft\\BluetoothAuthenticationAgent\\AcceptIncomingRequests'.  Existence requirement is 'all_exist' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n                :        For 'MAXHEALTH\\katessem.admin':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Microsoft\\BluetoothAuthenticationAgent\\AcceptIncomingRequests'.  \n                :        For 'MAXHEALTH\\katessem':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Microsoft\\BluetoothAuthenticationAgent\\AcceptIncomingRequests'.  \n                :        For 'MHL-PW06M2V2\\Administrator':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Microsoft\\BluetoothAuthenticationAgent\\AcceptIncomingRequests'.  \n","rule_version":"WN11-00-000230","rule_title":"The system must notify the user when a Bluetooth device attempts to connect.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows:def:253293"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"This is NA if the system does not have Bluetooth, or if Bluetooth is turned off per the organizations policy.\n\nSearch for \"Bluetooth\".\nView Bluetooth Settings.\nSelect \"More Bluetooth Options\"\nIf \"Alert me when a new Bluetooth device wants to connect\" is not checked, this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-253293r991589_rule","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","false_positives":"","uuid":"70031DFA-6D7C-1014-86E0-CC7D6363EA9A","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5471","stig_uuid":"6FDFF1B9-6D7C-1014-8C20-99EC6B15618D","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_id":"V-253293","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","id":"V-253293"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Configure Bluetooth to notify users if devices attempt to connect.\nView Bluetooth Settings.\nEnsure \"Alert me when a new Bluetooth device wants to connect\" is checked.","discussion":"If not configured properly, Bluetooth may allow rogue devices to communicate with a system. If a rogue device is paired with a system, there is potential for sensitive information to be compromised.","group_id_src":"V-253293"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-253294r991589","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:51\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT I, V-253294, SV-253294r991589, SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227)\n","rule_version":"WN11-00-000240","rule_title":"Administrative accounts must not be used with applications that access the internet, such as web browsers, or with potential internet sources, such as email.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-ocil.xml","name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows11:questionnaire:7701"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Determine whether administrative accounts are prevented from using applications that access the internet, such as web browsers, or with potential internet sources, such as email, except as necessary for local service administration.\n\nThe organization must have a policy that prohibits administrative accounts from using applications that access the internet, such as web browsers, or with potential internet sources, such as email, except as necessary for local service administration. The policy must define specific exceptions for local service administration. These exceptions may include HTTP(S)-based tools that are used for the administration of the local system, services, or attached devices.\n\nTechnical measures such as the removal of applications or application allowlisting must be used where feasible to prevent the use of applications that access the internet. \n\nIf accounts with administrative privileges are not prevented from using applications that access the internet or with potential internet sources, this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-253294r991589_rule","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","false_positives":"","uuid":"700323A7-6D7C-1014-8874-B842518834AD","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5471","stig_uuid":"6FDFF1B9-6D7C-1014-8C20-99EC6B15618D","severity":"high","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_reviewed","group_id":"V-253294","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","id":"V-253294"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Establish and enforce a policy that prohibits administrative accounts from using applications that access the internet, such as web browsers, or with potential internet sources, such as email. Define specific exceptions for local service administration. These exceptions may include HTTP(S)-based tools that are used for the administration of the local system, services, or attached devices.\n\nImplement technical measures where feasible such as removal of applications or use of application allowlisting to restrict the use of applications that can access the internet.","discussion":"Using applications that access the internet or have potential internet sources using administrative privileges exposes a system to compromise. If a flaw in an application is exploited while running as a privileged user, the entire system could be compromised. Web browsers and email are common attack vectors for introducing malicious code and must not be run with an administrative account.\n\nSince administrative accounts may generally change or work around technical restrictions for running a web browser or other applications, it is essential that policy requires administrative accounts to not access the internet or use applications, such as email.\n\nThe policy must define specific exceptions for local service administration. These exceptions may include HTTP(S)-based tools that are used for the administration of the local system, services, or attached devices.\n\nTechnical means such as application allowlisting can be used to enforce the policy to ensure compliance.","group_id_src":"V-253294"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-253295r958552","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:51\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT II, V-253295, SV-253295r958552, SRG-OS-000185-GPOS-00079)\n","rule_version":"WN11-00-000250","rule_title":"Windows 11 nonpersistent VM sessions must not exceed 24 hours.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-ocil.xml","name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows11:questionnaire:7901"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-001199"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Verify there is a documented policy or procedure in place that nonpersistent VM sessions do not exceed 24 hours.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  \n\nIf the system is NOT a nonpersistent VM, this is Not Applicable. \n\nFor Azure Virtual Desktop (AVD) implementations with no data at rest, this is Not Applicable.\n\nIf there is no such documented policy or procedure in place, this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-253295r958552_rule","group_title":"SRG-OS-000185-GPOS-00079","false_positives":"","uuid":"70032920-6D7C-1014-8731-961B02C31095","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5471","stig_uuid":"6FDFF1B9-6D7C-1014-8C20-99EC6B15618D","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_reviewed","group_id":"V-253295","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000185-GPOS-00079","id":"V-253295"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set nonpersistent VM sessions to not exceed 24 hours.","discussion":"For virtual desktop implementations (VDIs) where the virtual desktop instance is deleted or refreshed upon logoff, the organization must enforce that sessions be terminated within 24 hours. This would ensure any data stored on the VM that is not encrypted or covered by Credential Guard is deleted.","group_id_src":"V-253295"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-253296r1051041","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:51\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Review the Windows time service configuration via PowerShell)\n","rule_version":"WN11-00-000260","rule_title":"The Windows 11 time service must synchronize with an appropriate DOD time source.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows:def:253296"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-004923","CCI-001891"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Review the Windows time service configuration.\n\nOpen an elevated \"Command Prompt\" (run as administrator).\n\nEnter \"W32tm /query /configuration\".\n\nDomain-joined systems (excluding the domain controller with the PDC emulator role):\n\nIf the value for \"Type\" under \"NTP Client\" is not \"NT5DS\", this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-253296r1051041_rule","group_title":"SRG-OS-000355-GPOS-00143","false_positives":"","uuid":"70032F90-6D7C-1014-87C1-9286227C23DF","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5471","stig_uuid":"6FDFF1B9-6D7C-1014-8C20-99EC6B15618D","severity":"low","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_id":"V-253296","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000355-GPOS-00143","id":"V-253296"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Configure the system to synchronize time with an appropriate DOD time source.\n\nDomain-joined systems use NT5DS to synchronize time from other systems in the domain by default.\n\nIf the system needs to be configured to an NTP server, configure the system to point to an authorized time server by setting the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; System &gt;&gt; Windows Time Service &gt;&gt; Time Providers &gt;&gt; \"Configure Windows NTP Client\" to \"Enabled\", and configure the \"NtpServer\" field to point to an appropriate DOD time server.\n\nThe US Naval Observatory operates stratum 1 time servers, identified at https://www.cnmoc.usff.navy.mil/Our-Commands/United-States-Naval-Observatory/Precise-Time-Department/Network-Time-Protocol-NTP/. Time synchronization will occur through a hierarchy of time servers down to the local level. Clients and lower-level servers will synchronize with an authorized time server in the hierarchy.","discussion":"The Windows Time Service controls time synchronization settings. Time synchronization is essential for authentication and auditing purposes. If the Windows Time Service is used, it must synchronize with a secure, authorized time source. Domain-joined systems are automatically configured to synchronize with domain controllers. If an NTP server is configured, it must synchronize with a secure, authorized time source.","group_id_src":"V-253296"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-253297r958736","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:51\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :     true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :       false ('Account lockout duration' is set to '0')\nTest            :       true ('Account lockout duration' is set to '15 minutes' or greater)\nTest            :     true ('Account lockout threshold' is not set to '0')\n","rule_version":"WN11-AC-000005","rule_title":"Windows 11 account lockout duration must be configured to 15 minutes or greater.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows11:def:253297"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-002238"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy &gt;&gt; Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Account Policies &gt;&gt; Account Lockout Policy.\n\nIf the \"Account lockout duration\" is less than \"15\" minutes (excluding \"0\"), this is a finding.\n\nConfiguring this to \"0\", requiring an administrator to unlock the account, is more restrictive and is not a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-253297r958736_rule","group_title":"SRG-OS-000329-GPOS-00128","false_positives":"","uuid":"70033578-6D7C-1014-BA2B-A0970C4CC3C1","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5471","stig_uuid":"6FDFF1B9-6D7C-1014-8C20-99EC6B15618D","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_id":"V-253297","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000329-GPOS-00128","id":"V-253297"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Account Policies &gt;&gt; Account Lockout Policy &gt;&gt; \"Account lockout duration\" to \"15\" minutes or greater.\n\nA value of \"0\" is also acceptable, requiring an administrator to unlock the account.","discussion":"The account lockout feature, when enabled, prevents brute-force password attacks on the system. This parameter specifies the amount of time that an account will remain locked after the specified number of failed logon attempts.","group_id_src":"V-253297"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-253298r958388","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:51\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     false ('Account lockout threshold' is set to '3' or less)\nResult Analysis :          lockout_threshold = '5' failed test of 'less than or equal' compared to '3' \nTest            :     true ('Account lockout threshold' is not set to '0')\n","rule_version":"WN11-AC-000010","rule_title":"The number of allowed bad logon attempts must be configured to three or less.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows11:def:253298"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000044"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy &gt;&gt; Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Account Policies &gt;&gt; Account Lockout Policy.\n\nIf the \"Account lockout threshold\" is \"0\" or more than \"3\" attempts, this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-253298r958388_rule","group_title":"SRG-OS-000021-GPOS-00005","false_positives":"","uuid":"70033A48-6D7C-1014-8753-9B97475EB4BD","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5471","stig_uuid":"6FDFF1B9-6D7C-1014-8C20-99EC6B15618D","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_id":"V-253298","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000021-GPOS-00005","id":"V-253298"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Account Policies &gt;&gt; Account Lockout Policy &gt;&gt; \"Account lockout threshold\" to \"3\" or less invalid logon attempts (excluding \"0\" which is unacceptable).","discussion":"The account lockout feature, when enabled, prevents brute-force password attacks on the system. The higher this value is, the less effective the account lockout feature will be in protecting the local system. The number of bad logon attempts must be reasonably small to minimize the possibility of a successful password attack, while allowing for honest errors made during a normal user logon.","group_id_src":"V-253298"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-253299r958388","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:51\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('Reset account lockout counter after' is set to at least the required value)\nTest            :     true ('Account lockout threshold' is not set to '0')\n","rule_version":"WN11-AC-000015","rule_title":"The period of time before the bad logon counter is reset must be configured to 15 minutes.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows11:def:253299"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000044"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy &gt;&gt; Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Account Policies &gt;&gt; Account Lockout Policy.\n\nIf the \"Reset account lockout counter after\" value is less than \"15\" minutes, this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-253299r958388_rule","group_title":"SRG-OS-000021-GPOS-00005","false_positives":"","uuid":"70033F46-6D7C-1014-B095-8EA4D5E8FDA6","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5471","stig_uuid":"6FDFF1B9-6D7C-1014-8C20-99EC6B15618D","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_id":"V-253299","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000021-GPOS-00005","id":"V-253299"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Account Policies &gt;&gt; Account Lockout Policy &gt;&gt; \"Reset account lockout counter after\" to \"15\" minutes.","discussion":"The account lockout feature, when enabled, prevents brute-force password attacks on the system. This parameter specifies the period of time that must pass after failed logon attempts before the counter is reset to 0. The smaller this value is, the less effective the account lockout feature will be in protecting the local system.","group_id_src":"V-253299"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-253300r1000103","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:51\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     false ('Enforce password history' is set to '24' passwords or more)\nResult Analysis :          password_hist_len = '8' failed test of 'greater than or equal' compared to '24' \n","rule_version":"WN11-AC-000020","rule_title":"The password history must be configured to 24 passwords remembered.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows11:def:253300"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-004061"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy &gt;&gt; Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Account Policies &gt;&gt; Password Policy.\n\nIf the value for \"Enforce password history\" is less than \"24\" passwords remembered, this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-253300r1000103_rule","group_title":"SRG-OS-000077-GPOS-00045","false_positives":"","uuid":"700343E1-6D7C-1014-88CB-E5150D935B0B","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5471","stig_uuid":"6FDFF1B9-6D7C-1014-8C20-99EC6B15618D","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_id":"V-253300","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000077-GPOS-00045","id":"V-253300"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Account Policies &gt;&gt; Password Policy &gt;&gt; \"Enforce password history\" to \"24\" passwords remembered.","discussion":"A system is more vulnerable to unauthorized access when system users recycle the same password several times without being required to change a password to a unique password on a regularly scheduled basis. This enables users to effectively negate the purpose of mandating periodic password changes. The default value is 24 for Windows domain systems. DOD has decided this is the appropriate value for all Windows systems.","group_id_src":"V-253300"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-253301r1051042","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:51\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     false (Maximum Password Age is set to 60 days or less, but greater than 0.)\nResult Analysis :          max_passwd_age = '7776000' failed test of 'less than or equal' compared to '5184000' \n","rule_version":"WN11-AC-000025","rule_title":"The maximum password age must be configured to 60 days or less.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows11:def:253301"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-004066","CCI-000199"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy &gt;&gt; Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Account Policies &gt;&gt; Password Policy.\n\nIf the value for the \"Maximum password age\" is greater than \"60\" days, this is a finding. If the value is set to \"0\" (never expires), this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-253301r1051042_rule","group_title":"SRG-OS-000076-GPOS-00044","false_positives":"","uuid":"700348A1-6D7C-1014-B1A4-91530ABC5BBC","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5471","stig_uuid":"6FDFF1B9-6D7C-1014-8C20-99EC6B15618D","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_id":"V-253301","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000076-GPOS-00044","id":"V-253301"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Account Policies &gt;&gt; Password Policy &gt;&gt; \"Maximum Password Age\" to \"60\" days or less (excluding \"0\" which is unacceptable).","discussion":"The longer a password is in use, the greater the opportunity for someone to gain unauthorized knowledge of the passwords. Scheduled changing of passwords hinders the ability of unauthorized system users to crack passwords and gain access to a system.","group_id_src":"V-253301"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-253302r1051043","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:51\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     false ('Minimum Password Age' is set to at least '1' day)\nResult Analysis :          min_passwd_age = '0' failed test of 'greater than or equal' compared to '86400' \n","rule_version":"WN11-AC-000030","rule_title":"The minimum password age must be configured to at least 1 day.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows11:def:253302"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-004066","CCI-000198"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy &gt;&gt; Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Account Policies &gt;&gt; Password Policy.\n\nIf the value for the \"Minimum password age\" is less than \"1\" day, this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-253302r1051043_rule","group_title":"SRG-OS-000075-GPOS-00043","false_positives":"","uuid":"70034D49-6D7C-1014-9A5C-D8474763CFE2","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5471","stig_uuid":"6FDFF1B9-6D7C-1014-8C20-99EC6B15618D","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_id":"V-253302","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000075-GPOS-00043","id":"V-253302"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Account Policies &gt;&gt; Password Policy &gt;&gt; \"Minimum Password Age\" to at least \"1\" day.","discussion":"Permitting passwords to be changed in immediate succession within the same day allows users to cycle passwords through their history database. This enables users to effectively negate the purpose of mandating periodic password changes.","group_id_src":"V-253302"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-253303r1051044","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:51\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     false ('Minimum password length' is set to at least '14' characters)\nResult Analysis :          min_passwd_len = '8' failed test of 'greater than or equal' compared to '14' \n","rule_version":"WN11-AC-000035","rule_title":"Passwords must, at a minimum, be 14 characters.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows11:def:253303"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-004066","CCI-000205"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy &gt;&gt; Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Account Policies &gt;&gt; Password Policy.\n\nIf the value for the \"Minimum password length,\" is less than \"14\" characters, this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-253303r1051044_rule","group_title":"SRG-OS-000078-GPOS-00046","false_positives":"","uuid":"70035322-6D7C-1014-8F60-C96ECA90534B","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5471","stig_uuid":"6FDFF1B9-6D7C-1014-8C20-99EC6B15618D","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_id":"V-253303","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000078-GPOS-00046","id":"V-253303"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Account Policies &gt;&gt; Password Policy &gt;&gt; \"Minimum password length\" to \"14\" characters.","discussion":"Information systems not protected with strong password schemes (including passwords of minimum length) provide the opportunity for anyone to crack the password, thus gaining access to the system and compromising the device, information, or the local network.","group_id_src":"V-253303"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-253304r1051045","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:51\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('Password must meet complexity requirements' is set to 'Enabled')\n","rule_version":"WN11-AC-000040","rule_title":"The built-in Microsoft password complexity filter must be enabled.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows11:def:253304"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-004066","CCI-000192"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy &gt;&gt; Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Account Policies &gt;&gt; Password Policy.\n\nIf the value for \"Password must meet complexity requirements\" is not set to \"Enabled\", this is a finding.\n\nIf the site is using a password filter that requires this setting be set to \"Disabled\" for the filter to be used, this would not be considered a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-253304r1051045_rule","group_title":"SRG-OS-000069-GPOS-00037","false_positives":"","uuid":"70035877-6D7C-1014-9801-DAA8B5B030EF","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5471","stig_uuid":"6FDFF1B9-6D7C-1014-8C20-99EC6B15618D","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_id":"V-253304","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000069-GPOS-00037","id":"V-253304"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Account Policies &gt;&gt; Password Policy &gt;&gt; \"Password must meet complexity requirements\" to \"Enabled\".","discussion":"The use of complex passwords increases their strength against guessing and brute-force attacks. This setting configures the system to verify that newly created passwords conform to the Windows password complexity policy.","group_id_src":"V-253304"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-253305r1051046","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:51\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('Store password using reversible encryption' is set to 'Disabled')\n","rule_version":"WN11-AC-000045","rule_title":"Reversible password encryption must be disabled.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows11:def:253305"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-004062","CCI-000196"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy &gt;&gt; Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Account Policies &gt;&gt; Password Policy.\n\nIf the value for \"Store password using reversible encryption\" is not set to \"Disabled\", this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-253305r1051046_rule","group_title":"SRG-OS-000073-GPOS-00041","false_positives":"","uuid":"70035D1C-6D7C-1014-A784-B4633CDDF3BB","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5471","stig_uuid":"6FDFF1B9-6D7C-1014-8C20-99EC6B15618D","severity":"high","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_id":"V-253305","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000073-GPOS-00041","id":"V-253305"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Account Policies &gt;&gt; Password Policy &gt;&gt; \"Store passwords using reversible encryption\" to \"Disabled\".","discussion":"Storing passwords using reversible encryption is essentially the same as storing clear-text versions of the passwords. For this reason, this policy must never be enabled.","group_id_src":"V-253305"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-253306r991570","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:51\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   false (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :     false ('Audit Credential Validation' is set to 'Failure')\nResult Analysis :          credential_validation = 'AUDIT_NONE' failed test of 'equals' compared to 'AUDIT_FAILURE' \nTest            :     false ('Audit Credential Validation' is set to 'Success' and 'Failure')\nResult Analysis :          credential_validation = 'AUDIT_NONE' failed test of 'equals' compared to 'AUDIT_SUCCESS_FAILURE' \n","rule_version":"WN11-AU-000005","rule_title":"The system must be configured to audit Account Logon - Credential Validation failures.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows11:def:253306"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000172"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Security Option \"Audit: Force audit policy subcategory settings to override audit policy category settings\" must be set to \"Enabled\" (WN11-SO-000030) for the detailed auditing subcategories to be effective.\n\nUse the AuditPol tool to review the current Audit Policy configuration:\nOpen a Command Prompt with elevated privileges (\"Run as Administrator\").\nEnter \"AuditPol /get /category:*\".\n\nCompare the AuditPol settings with the following. If the system does not audit the following, this is a finding:\n\nAccount Logon &gt;&gt; Credential Validation - Failure","rule_id_src":"SV-253306r991570_rule","group_title":"SRG-OS-000458-GPOS-00203","false_positives":"","uuid":"700361B8-6D7C-1014-9B73-A819C50099FD","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5471","stig_uuid":"6FDFF1B9-6D7C-1014-8C20-99EC6B15618D","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_id":"V-253306","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000458-GPOS-00203","id":"V-253306"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Advanced Audit Policy Configuration &gt;&gt; System Audit Policies &gt;&gt; Account Logon &gt;&gt; \"Audit Credential Validation\" with \"Failure\" selected.","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nCredential validation records events related to validation tests on credentials for a user account logon.","group_id_src":"V-253306"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-253307r991570","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:51\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   false (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :     false ('Audit Credential Validation' is set to 'Success')\nResult Analysis :          credential_validation = 'AUDIT_NONE' failed test of 'equals' compared to 'AUDIT_SUCCESS' \nTest            :     false ('Audit Credential Validation' is set to 'Success' and 'Failure')\nResult Analysis :          credential_validation = 'AUDIT_NONE' failed test of 'equals' compared to 'AUDIT_SUCCESS_FAILURE' \n","rule_version":"WN11-AU-000010","rule_title":"The system must be configured to audit Account Logon - Credential Validation successes.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows11:def:253307"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000172"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Security Option \"Audit: Force audit policy subcategory settings to override audit policy category settings\" must be set to \"Enabled\" (WN11-SO-000030) for the detailed auditing subcategories to be effective.\n\nUse the AuditPol tool to review the current Audit Policy configuration:\nOpen a Command Prompt with elevated privileges (\"Run as Administrator\").\nEnter \"AuditPol /get /category:*\".\n\nCompare the AuditPol settings with the following. If the system does not audit the following, this is a finding:\n\nAccount Logon &gt;&gt; Credential Validation - Success","rule_id_src":"SV-253307r991570_rule","group_title":"SRG-OS-000458-GPOS-00203","false_positives":"","uuid":"700366B2-6D7C-1014-BC30-A08612B71642","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5471","stig_uuid":"6FDFF1B9-6D7C-1014-8C20-99EC6B15618D","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_id":"V-253307","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000458-GPOS-00203","id":"V-253307"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Advanced Audit Policy Configuration &gt;&gt; System Audit Policies &gt;&gt; Account Logon &gt;&gt; \"Audit Credential Validation\" with \"Success\" selected.","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nCredential validation records events related to validation tests on credentials for a user account logon.","group_id_src":"V-253307"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-253308r971541","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:51\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     false ('Audit Security Group Management' is set to 'Success' or 'Success and Failure')\nResult Analysis :          security_group_management = 'AUDIT_NONE' failed test of 'equals' compared to 'AUDIT_SUCCESS_FAILURE' \n                : security_group_management = 'AUDIT_NONE' failed test of 'equals' compared to 'AUDIT_SUCCESS' \n","rule_version":"WN11-AU-000030","rule_title":"The system must be configured to audit Account Management - Security Group Management successes.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows11:def:253308"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-001914"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Security Option \"Audit: Force audit policy subcategory settings to override audit policy category settings\" must be set to \"Enabled\" (WN11-SO-000030) for the detailed auditing subcategories to be effective.\n\nUse the AuditPol tool to review the current Audit Policy configuration:\nOpen a Command Prompt with elevated privileges (\"Run as Administrator\").\nEnter \"AuditPol /get /category:*\".\n\nCompare the AuditPol settings with the following. If the system does not audit the following, this is a finding:\n\nAccount Management &gt;&gt; Security Group Management - Success","rule_id_src":"SV-253308r971541_rule","group_title":"SRG-OS-000337-GPOS-00129","false_positives":"","uuid":"70036B41-6D7C-1014-B892-D9A18BE1D69D","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5471","stig_uuid":"6FDFF1B9-6D7C-1014-8C20-99EC6B15618D","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_id":"V-253308","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000337-GPOS-00129","id":"V-253308"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Advanced Audit Policy Configuration &gt;&gt; System Audit Policies &gt;&gt; Account Management &gt;&gt; \"Audit Security Group Management\" with \"Success\" selected.","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nSecurity Group Management records events such as creating, deleting or changing of security groups, including changes in group members.","group_id_src":"V-253308"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-253309r958566","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:51\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   false (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :     false ('Audit User Account Management' is set to 'Failure')\nResult Analysis :          user_account_management = 'AUDIT_NONE' failed test of 'equals' compared to 'AUDIT_FAILURE' \nTest            :     false ('Audit User Account Management' is set to 'Success' and 'Failure')\nResult Analysis :          user_account_management = 'AUDIT_NONE' failed test of 'equals' compared to 'AUDIT_SUCCESS_FAILURE' \n","rule_version":"WN11-AU-000035","rule_title":"The system must be configured to audit Account Management - User Account Management failures.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows11:def:253309"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-001314"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Security Option \"Audit: Force audit policy subcategory settings to override audit policy category settings\" must be set to \"Enabled\" (WN11-SO-000030) for the detailed auditing subcategories to be effective.\n\nUse the AuditPol tool to review the current Audit Policy configuration:\nOpen a Command Prompt with elevated privileges (\"Run as Administrator\").\nEnter \"AuditPol /get /category:*\".\n\nCompare the AuditPol settings with the following. If the system does not audit the following, this is a finding:\n\nAccount Management &gt;&gt; User Account Management - Failure","rule_id_src":"SV-253309r958566_rule","group_title":"SRG-OS-000206-GPOS-00084","false_positives":"","uuid":"70036FC1-6D7C-1014-AB0D-E47AAD5332A5","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5471","stig_uuid":"6FDFF1B9-6D7C-1014-8C20-99EC6B15618D","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_id":"V-253309","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000206-GPOS-00084","id":"V-253309"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Advanced Audit Policy Configuration &gt;&gt; System Audit Policies &gt;&gt; Account Management &gt;&gt; \"Audit User Account Management\" with \"Failure\" selected.","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nUser Account Management records events such as creating, changing, deleting, renaming, disabling, or enabling user accounts.","group_id_src":"V-253309"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-253310r991551","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:51\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   false (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :     false ('Audit User Account Management' is set to 'Success')\nResult Analysis :          user_account_management = 'AUDIT_NONE' failed test of 'equals' compared to 'AUDIT_SUCCESS' \nTest            :     false ('Audit User Account Management' is set to 'Success' and 'Failure')\nResult Analysis :          user_account_management = 'AUDIT_NONE' failed test of 'equals' compared to 'AUDIT_SUCCESS_FAILURE' \n","rule_version":"WN11-AU-000040","rule_title":"The system must be configured to audit Account Management - User Account Management successes.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows11:def:253310"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-001403"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Security Option \"Audit: Force audit policy subcategory settings to override audit policy category settings\" must be set to \"Enabled\" (WN11-SO-000030) for the detailed auditing subcategories to be effective.\n\nUse the AuditPol tool to review the current Audit Policy configuration:\nOpen a Command Prompt with elevated privileges (\"Run as Administrator\").\nEnter \"AuditPol /get /category:*\".\n\nCompare the AuditPol settings with the following. If the system does not audit the following, this is a finding:\n\nAccount Management &gt;&gt; User Account Management - Success","rule_id_src":"SV-253310r991551_rule","group_title":"SRG-OS-000239-GPOS-00089","false_positives":"","uuid":"70037448-6D7C-1014-9267-B51FD91C93C0","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5471","stig_uuid":"6FDFF1B9-6D7C-1014-8C20-99EC6B15618D","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_id":"V-253310","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000239-GPOS-00089","id":"V-253310"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Advanced Audit Policy Configuration &gt;&gt; System Audit Policies &gt;&gt; Account Management &gt;&gt; \"Audit User Account Management\" with \"Success\" selected.","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nUser Account Management records events such as creating, changing, deleting, renaming, disabling, or enabling user accounts.","group_id_src":"V-253310"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-253311r1051047","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:51\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Audit: Force audit policy subcategory settings to override audit policy category settings must be set to Enabled)\nTest            :   false (Detailed Tracking - Plug and Play Events successes.)\nResult Analysis :        pnp_activity = 'AUDIT_NONE' failed test of 'pattern match' compared to 'AUDIT_(SUCCESS|SUCCESS_FAILURE)' \n","rule_version":"WN11-AU-000045","rule_title":"The system must be configured to audit Detailed Tracking - PNP Activity successes.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows:def:253311"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000172","CCI-003938","CCI-001814"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Security Option \"Audit: Force audit policy subcategory settings to override audit policy category settings\" must be set to \"Enabled\" (WN11-SO-000030) for the detailed auditing subcategories to be effective. \n\nUse the AuditPol tool to review the current Audit Policy configuration:\nOpen a Command Prompt with elevated privileges (\"Run as Administrator\").\nEnter \"AuditPol /get /category:*\"\n\nCompare the AuditPol settings with the following. If the system does not audit the following, this is a finding:\n\nDetailed Tracking &gt;&gt; Plug and Play Events - Success","rule_id_src":"SV-253311r1051047_rule","group_title":"SRG-OS-000365-GPOS-00152","false_positives":"","uuid":"700378E1-6D7C-1014-BEE7-ABE35D0F6D6A","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5471","stig_uuid":"6FDFF1B9-6D7C-1014-8C20-99EC6B15618D","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_id":"V-253311","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000365-GPOS-00152","id":"V-253311"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Advanced Audit Policy Configuration &gt;&gt; System Audit Policies &gt;&gt; Detailed Tracking &gt;&gt; \"Audit PNP Activity\" with \"Success\" selected.","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nPlug and Play activity records events related to the successful connection of external devices.","group_id_src":"V-253311"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-253312r1051048","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:51\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   false (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :     false (Audit - Process Creation - Success only)\nResult Analysis :          process_creation = 'AUDIT_NONE' failed test of 'equals' compared to 'AUDIT_SUCCESS' \nTest            :     false (Audit - Process Creation - Success and Failure)\nResult Analysis :          process_creation = 'AUDIT_NONE' failed test of 'equals' compared to 'AUDIT_SUCCESS_FAILURE' \n","rule_version":"WN11-AU-000050","rule_title":"The system must be configured to audit Detailed Tracking - Process Creation successes.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows11:def:253312"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000172","CCI-003938","CCI-001814"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Security Option \"Audit: Force audit policy subcategory settings to override audit policy category settings\" must be set to \"Enabled\" (WN11-SO-000030) for the detailed auditing subcategories to be effective.\n\nUse the AuditPol tool to review the current Audit Policy configuration:\nOpen a Command Prompt with elevated privileges (\"Run as Administrator\").\nEnter \"AuditPol /get /category:*\".\n\nCompare the AuditPol settings with the following. If the system does not audit the following, this is a finding:\n\nDetailed Tracking &gt;&gt; Process Creation - Success","rule_id_src":"SV-253312r1051048_rule","group_title":"SRG-OS-000064-GPOS-00033","false_positives":"","uuid":"70037D8A-6D7C-1014-B4EA-AFACBE680377","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5471","stig_uuid":"6FDFF1B9-6D7C-1014-8C20-99EC6B15618D","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_id":"V-253312","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000064-GPOS-00033","id":"V-253312"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Advanced Audit Policy Configuration &gt;&gt; System Audit Policies &gt;&gt; Detailed Tracking &gt;&gt; \"Audit Process Creation\" with \"Success\" selected.","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nProcess creation records events related to the creation of a process and the source.","group_id_src":"V-253312"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-253313r991578","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:51\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   false (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :     false ('Audit Account Lockout' is set to 'Failure')\nResult Analysis :          account_lockout = 'AUDIT_NONE' failed test of 'equals' compared to 'AUDIT_FAILURE' \nTest            :     false ('Audit Account Lockout' is set to 'Success' and 'Failure')\nResult Analysis :          account_lockout = 'AUDIT_NONE' failed test of 'equals' compared to 'AUDIT_SUCCESS_FAILURE' \n","rule_version":"WN11-AU-000054","rule_title":"The system must be configured to audit Logon/Logoff - Account Lockout failures.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows11:def:253313"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000172"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Security Option \"Audit: Force audit policy subcategory settings to override audit policy category settings\" must be set to \"Enabled\" (WN11-SO-000030) for the detailed auditing subcategories to be effective.\n\nUse the AuditPol tool to review the current Audit Policy configuration:\n\nOpen a Command Prompt with elevated privileges (\"Run as Administrator\").\n\nEnter \"AuditPol /get /category:*\"\n\nCompare the AuditPol settings with the following. If the system does not audit the following, this is a finding:\n\nLogon/Logoff &gt;&gt; Account Lockout - Failure","rule_id_src":"SV-253313r991578_rule","group_title":"SRG-OS-000470-GPOS-00214","false_positives":"","uuid":"7003821B-6D7C-1014-B6C8-9067B48D0ECE","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5471","stig_uuid":"6FDFF1B9-6D7C-1014-8C20-99EC6B15618D","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_id":"V-253313","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000470-GPOS-00214","id":"V-253313"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Advanced Audit Policy Configuration &gt;&gt; System Audit Policies &gt;&gt; Logon/Logoff &gt;&gt; \"Audit Account Lockout\" with \"Failure\" selected.","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nAccount Lockout events can be used to identify potentially malicious logon attempts.","group_id_src":"V-253313"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-253314r991570","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:51\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Audit: Force audit policy subcategory settings to override audit policy category settings must be set to Enabled)\nTest            