ctivity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nAudit Group Membership records information related to the group membership of a user's logon token.","group_id_src":"V-253314"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-253315r958406","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:51\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   false (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :     false (Audit - Logoff - Success only)\nResult Analysis :          logoff = 'AUDIT_NONE' failed test of 'equals' compared to 'AUDIT_SUCCESS' \nTest            :     false (Audit - Logoff - Success and Failure)\nResult Analysis :          logoff = 'AUDIT_NONE' failed test of 'equals' compared to 'AUDIT_SUCCESS_FAILURE' \n","rule_version":"WN11-AU-000065","rule_title":"The system must be configured to audit Logon/Logoff - Logoff successes.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows11:def:253315"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000067"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Security Option \"Audit: Force audit policy subcategory settings to override audit policy category settings\" must be set to \"Enabled\" (WN11-SO-000030) for the detailed auditing subcategories to be effective.\n\nUse the AuditPol tool to review the current Audit Policy configuration:\nOpen a Command Prompt with elevated privileges (\"Run as Administrator\").\nEnter \"Aud