      :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     false ('Audit File Share' is set to 'Success')\nResult Analysis :          file_share = 'AUDIT_NONE' failed test of 'equals' compared to 'AUDIT_SUCCESS_FAILURE' \n                : file_share = 'AUDIT_NONE' failed test of 'equals' compared to 'AUDIT_SUCCESS' \n","rule_version":"WN11-AU-000082","rule_title":"Windows 11 must be configured to audit Object Access - File Share successes.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows11:def:253320"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000172"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Security Option \"Audit: Force audit policy subcategory settings (Windows Vista or later) to override audit policy category settings\" must be set to \"Enabled\" (WN11-SO-000030) for the detailed auditing subcategories to be effective.\n\nUse the AuditPol tool to review the current Audit Policy configuration:\n\nOpen PowerShell or a Command Prompt with elevated privileges (\"Run as Administrator\").\nEnter \"AuditPol /get /category:*\"\n\nCompare the AuditPol settings with the following:\n\nObject Access &gt;&gt; File Share - Success\n\nIf the system does not audit the above, this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-253320r991572_rule","group_title":"SRG-OS-000462-GPOS-00206","false_positives":"","uuid":"7003A52F-6D7C-1014-BA07-B8F10052DBDE","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5471","stig_uuid":"6FDFF1B9-6D7C-1014-8C20-99EC6B15618D","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_id":"V-253320","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000462-GPOS-00206","id":"V-253320"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Advanced Audit Policy Configuration &gt;&g