re the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Advanced Audit Policy Configuration &gt;&gt; System Audit Policies &gt;&gt; Policy Change &gt;&gt; \"Audit Authorization Policy Change\" with \"Success\" selected.","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nAuthorization Policy Change records events related to changes in user rights, such as create a token object.","group_id_src":"V-253327"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-253328r958732","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:51:51\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     false ('Sensitive Privilege Use' is set to 'Failure' or 'Success and Failure')\nResult Analysis :          sensitive_privilege_use = 'AUDIT_NONE' failed test of 'equals' compared to 'AUDIT_SUCCESS_FAILURE' \n                : sensitive_privilege_use = 'AUDIT_NONE' failed test of 'equals' compared to 'AUDIT_FAILURE' \n","rule_version":"WN11-AU-000110","rule_title":"The system must be configured to audit Privilege Use - Sensitive Privilege Use failures.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows11:def:253328"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-002234"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Security Option \"Audit: Force audit policy subcategory settings to override audit policy category settings\" must be set to \"Enabled\" (WN11-SO-000030) for the detailed auditing subcategories to be effective.\n\nUse the AuditPol tool to review the current Audit Policy configuration:\nOpen a Command Prompt with elevated privileges (\"Run as Administrator\").\nEnter \"AuditPol /get /category:*\".\n\nCompare the AuditPol settings with the following. If the system does not audit the following, this is a finding:\n\nPrivilege Use &gt;&gt; Sensitive Privilege Use - Failure","rule_id_src":"SV-253328r958732_rule","group_title":"SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127","false_positives":"","uuid":"7003D1B0-6D7C-1014-A725-BE0C372830D0","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5471","stig_uuid":"6FDFF1B9-6D7C-1014-8C20-99EC6B15618D","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_id":"V-253328","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127","id":"V-253328"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Advanced Audit Policy Configuration &gt;&gt; System Audit Policies &gt;&gt; Privilege Use &gt;&gt; \"Audit Sensitive Privilege Use\" with \"Failure\" selected.","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nSensitive Privilege Use records events related to use of sensitive privileges, such as \"Act as part of the operating system\" or \"Debug programs\".","group_id_src":"V-253328"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-253329r991575","finding_details":