result is false.\n","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000024","rule_title":"AutoplayAllowed must be set to disabled.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:119"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow media autoplay for websites\" must be set to \"disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"AutoplayAllowed\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-235741r1007485_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"A6921BEF-6D7C-1014-B094-F966B63ED44C","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5280","stig_uuid":"A68F29AE-6D7C-1014-9376-DC80EB852963","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_id":"V-235741","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-235741"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow media autoplay for websites\" to \"disabled\".","discussion":"This policy sets the media autoplay policy for websites.\n\nThe default setting \"Not configured\" respects the current media autoplay settings and lets users configure their autoplay settings.\n\nSetting to \"Enabled\" sets media autoplay to \"Allow\". All websites are allowed to autoplay media. Users cannot override this policy.\n\nSetting to \"Disabled\" sets media autoplay to \"Limit\". This limits websites that are allowed to autoplay media to webpages with high media engagement and active WebRTC streams. Prior to Microsoft Edge version 92, this would set media autoplay to \"Block\". Users cannot override this policy.","group_id_src":"V-235741"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-235742r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:54:55\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (WebUSB must be disabled)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\DefaultWebUsbGuardSetting'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000025","rule_title":"WebUSB must be disabled.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:120"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Content settings/Control use of the WebUSB API\" must be set to \"enabled\" with the option value set to \"Do not allow any site to request access to USB devices via the WebUSB API\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"DefaultWebUsbGuardSetting\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 2\", this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-235742r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"A69220DE-6D7C-1014-9EAB-EE18E801D38C","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5280","stig_uuid":"A68F29AE-6D7C-1014-9376-DC80EB852963","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_id":"V-235742","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-235742"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Content settings/Control use of the WebUSB API\" to enabled\" and select \"Do not allow any site to request access to USB devices via the WebUSB API\".","discussion":"Set whether websites can access connected USB devices. Access can be blocked completely or the user asked each time a website wants to get access to connected USB devices.\n\nOverride this policy for specific URL patterns by using the WebUsbAskForUrls and WebUsbBlockedForUrls policies.\n\nIf this policy is not configured, sites can ask users whether they can access the connected USB devices ('AskWebUsb') by default, and users can change this setting.","group_id_src":"V-235742"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-235743r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:54:55\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Google Cast is disabled)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\EnableMediaRouter'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000026","rule_title":"Google Cast must be disabled.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:121"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Cast/Enable Google Cast\" must be set to \"disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"EnableMediaRouter\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-235743r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"A692263B-6D7C-1014-9401-FA48355E8249","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5280","stig_uuid":"A68F29AE-6D7C-1014-9376-DC80EB852963","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_id":"V-235743","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-235743"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Cast/Enable Google Cast\" to \"disabled\".","discussion":"Enable this policy to enable Google Cast. Users will be able to launch it from the app menu, page context menus, media controls on Cast-enabled websites, and (if shown) the Cast toolbar icon.\n\nDisable this policy to disable Google Cast.\n\nBy default, Google Cast is enabled.","group_id_src":"V-235743"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-235744r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:54:55\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Web Bluetooth API is disabled)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\DefaultWebBluetoothGuardSetting'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000027","rule_title":"Web Bluetooth API must be disabled.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:122"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Content settings/Control use of the Web Bluetooth API\" must be set to \"enabled\" with the option value set to \"Do not allow any site to request access to Bluetooth devices via the Web Bluetooth API\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"DefaultWebBluetoothGuardSetting\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 2\", this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-235744r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"A6922B42-6D7C-1014-96A2-C54CE16575B9","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5280","stig_uuid":"A68F29AE-6D7C-1014-9376-DC80EB852963","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_id":"V-235744","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-235744"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Content settings/Control use of the Web Bluetooth API\" to \"enabled\" with the option value set to \"Do not allow any site to request access to Bluetooth devices via the Web Bluetooth API.","discussion":"Control whether websites can access nearby Bluetooth devices. Access can be blocked completely or the site required to ask the user each time it wants to access a Bluetooth device.\n\nIf this policy is not configured, the default value ('AskWebBluetooth', meaning users are asked each time) is used and users can change it.\n\nPolicy options mapping:\n- BlockWebBluetooth (2) = Do not allow any site to request access to Bluetooth devices via the Web Bluetooth API.\n- AskWebBluetooth (3) = Allow sites to ask the user to grant access to a nearby Bluetooth device.","group_id_src":"V-235744"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-235745r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:54:55\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Disable autofill for credit cards)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\AutofillCreditCardEnabled'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000028","rule_title":"Autofill for Credit Cards must be disabled.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:123"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Enable AutoFill for credit cards\" must be set to \"disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"AutofillCreditCardEnabled\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-235745r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"A692303D-6D7C-1014-8285-B0CAB27D5A7F","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5280","stig_uuid":"A68F29AE-6D7C-1014-9376-DC80EB852963","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_id":"V-235745","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-235745"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Enable AutoFill for credit cards\" to \"disabled\".","discussion":"Enables the Microsoft Edge AutoFill feature and lets users auto complete credit card information in web forms using previously stored information.\n\nIf this policy is disabled, AutoFill never suggests or fills credit card information, nor will it save additional credit card information that users might submit while browsing the web.\n\nIf this policy is enabled or not configured, users can control AutoFill for credit cards.","group_id_src":"V-235745"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-235746r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:54:55\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Disable autofill for addresses)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\AutofillAddressEnabled'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000029","rule_title":"Autofill for addresses must be disabled.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:124"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Enable AutoFill for addresses\" must be set to \"disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"AutofillAddressEnabled\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-235746r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"A692359E-6D7C-1014-9077-CEA7AD502974","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5280","stig_uuid":"A68F29AE-6D7C-1014-9376-DC80EB852963","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_id":"V-235746","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-235746"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Enable AutoFill for addresses\" to \"disabled\".","discussion":"Enables the AutoFill feature and allows users to auto-complete address information in web forms using previously stored information.\n\nIf this policy is disabled, AutoFill never suggests or fills credit card information, nor will it save additional credit card information that users might submit while browsing the web.\n\nIf this policy is enabled or not configured, users can control AutoFill for addresses in the user interface.","group_id_src":"V-235746"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-235747r961038","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:54:55\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Enable Enable online OCSP/CRL checks)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\EnableOnlineRevocationChecks'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000030","rule_title":"Online revocation checks must be performed.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:125"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000185"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Enable online OCSP/CRL checks\" must be set to \"Enabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"EnableOnlineRevocationChecks\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 1\", this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-235747r961038_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000175","false_positives":"","uuid":"A6923A6E-6D7C-1014-AAFD-ADB8A9522268","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5280","stig_uuid":"A68F29AE-6D7C-1014-9376-DC80EB852963","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_id":"V-235747","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000175","id":"V-235747"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Enable online OCSP/CRL checks\" to \"Enabled\".","discussion":"If you enable this policy, Microsoft Edge will perform soft-fail, online OCSP/CRL checks. \"Soft fail\" means that if the revocation server can't be reached, the certificate will be considered valid.\n\nIf you disable the policy or don't configure it, Microsoft Edge won't perform online revocation checks.","group_id_src":"V-235747"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-235748r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:54:55\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Disable personalization reporting)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\PersonalizationReportingEnabled'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000031","rule_title":"Personalization of ads, search, and news by sending browsing history to Microsoft must be disabled.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:126"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow personalization of ads, search and news by sending browsing history to Microsoft\" must be set to \"disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"PersonalizationReportingEnabled\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-235748r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"A6923F4D-6D7C-1014-A2CA-FD55D78111E7","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5280","stig_uuid":"A68F29AE-6D7C-1014-9376-DC80EB852963","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_id":"V-235748","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-235748"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow personalization of ads, search and news by sending browsing history to Microsoft\" to \"disabled\".","discussion":"This policy prevents Microsoft from collecting a user's Microsoft Edge browsing history to be used for personalizing advertising, search, news and other Microsoft services.\n\nThis setting is only available for users with a Microsoft account. This setting is not available for child accounts or enterprise accounts.\n\nIf this policy is disabled, users cannot change or override the setting. If this policy is enabled or not configured, Microsoft Edge will default to the user's preference.","group_id_src":"V-235748"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-235749r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:54:55\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Disable tracking user's location)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\DefaultGeolocationSetting'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000032","rule_title":"Site tracking of a userâs location must be disabled.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:127"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Content settings/Default geolocation setting\" must be set to \"enabled\" with the option value set to \"Don't allow any site to track users' physical location\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"DefaultGeolocationSetting\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 2\", this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-235749r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"A69244BE-6D7C-1014-A7F1-D8F305988E25","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5280","stig_uuid":"A68F29AE-6D7C-1014-9376-DC80EB852963","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_id":"V-235749","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-235749"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Content settings/Default geolocation setting\" to \"enabled\" and select \"Don't allow any site to track users' physical location\".","discussion":"Set whether websites can track users' physical locations. Tracking can be allowed by default (\"AllowGeolocation\") or denied by default (\"BlockGeolocation\"), or the user can be asked each time a website requests their location (\"AskGeolocation\").\n\nIf this policy is not configured, \"AskGeolocation\" is used and the user can change it.\n\nPolicy options mapping:\n- AllowGeolocation (1) = Allow sites to track users' physical location.\n- BlockGeolocation (2) = Do not allow any site to track users' physical location.\n- AskGeolocation (3) = Ask whenever a site wants to track users' physical location.","group_id_src":"V-235749"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-235750r960864","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:54:55\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Check to make sure that Microsoft Edge is set to not allow deletion of browser history.)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\AllowDeletingBrowserHistory'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000033","rule_title":"Browser history must be saved.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:128"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000166"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Enable deleting browser and download history\" must be set to \"disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"AllowDeletingBrowserHistory\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-235750r960864_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000080","false_positives":"","uuid":"A6924B0A-6D7C-1014-8AC6-BB655E6EFE6A","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5280","stig_uuid":"A68F29AE-6D7C-1014-9376-DC80EB852963","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_id":"V-235750","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000080","id":"V-235750"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Enable deleting browser and download history\" to \"disabled\".","discussion":"This setting disables deleting browser history and download history and prevents users from changing this setting.","group_id_src":"V-235750"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-235751r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:54:55\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Edge Developer Tools Availability must be disallowed.)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\DeveloperToolsAvailability'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000034","rule_title":"Edge development tools must be disabled.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:129"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Control where developer tools can be used\" with the option value set to \"Don't allow using the developer tools\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"DeveloperToolsAvailability\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 2\", this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-235751r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"A6924FF7-6D7C-1014-A39E-FF68CB54C92A","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5280","stig_uuid":"A68F29AE-6D7C-1014-9376-DC80EB852963","severity":"low","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_id":"V-235751","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-235751"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Control where developer tools can be used\" to \"enabled\" and select \"Don't allow using the developer tools\".","discussion":"While the risk associated with browser development tools is more related to the proper design of a web application, a risk vector remains within the browser. The developer tools allow end users and application developers to view and edit all types of web application-related data via the browser. Page elements, source code, javascript, API calls, application data, etc., may all be viewed and potentially manipulated. Manipulation could be useful for troubleshooting legitimate issues, and this may be performed in a development environment. Manipulation could also be malicious and must be addressed.","group_id_src":"V-235751"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-235752r1156563","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:54:55\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Download restrictions are configured)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\DownloadRestrictions'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000036","rule_title":"Download restrictions must be configured.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:130"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"If this machine is on SIPRNet, this is Not Applicable.\n\nThe policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow download restrictions\" must be set to \"Enabled\" with the option value set to \"BlockDangerousDownloads\", \"Block potentially dangerous or unwanted downloads\", or \"BlockMaliciousDownloads\". The more restrictive option, \"Block all downloads\", is also acceptable.\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"DownloadRestrictions\" is set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-235752r1156563_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"A6925580-6D7C-1014-8C7F-EDE762521A76","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5280","stig_uuid":"A68F29AE-6D7C-1014-9376-DC80EB852963","severity":"low","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_id":"V-235752","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-235752"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow download restrictions\" to \"Enabled\" and select one of the following: \"BlockDangerousDownloads\", \"Block potentially dangerous or unwanted downloads\", \"BlockAllDownloads\", or \"BlockMaliciousDownloads\".","discussion":"This configures the type of downloads that Microsoft Edge completely blocks without allowing users to override the security decision.\n\nSet \"BlockDangerousDownloads\" to allow all downloads except those that carry Microsoft Defender SmartScreen warnings of known dangerous downloads or that have dangerous file type extensions.\n\nSet \"BlockPotentiallyDangerousDownloads\" to allow all downloads except those that carry Microsoft Defender SmartScreen warnings of potentially dangerous or unwanted downloads or that have dangerous file type extensions.\n\nSet \"BlockAllDownloads\" to block all downloads.\n\nSet \"BlockMaliciousDownloads\" to allow all downloads except those that carry Microsoft Defender SmartScreen warnings of known malicious downloads.\n\nIf this policy is not configured or the \"DefaultDownloadSecurity\" option is not set, the downloads go through the usual security restrictions based on Microsoft Defender SmartScreen analysis results.\n\nPolicy options mapping:\n\nDefaultDownloadSecurity (0) = No special restrictions\n\nBlockDangerousDownloads (1) = Block malicious downloads and dangerous file types\n\nBlockPotentiallyDangerousDownloads (2) = Block potentially dangerous or unwanted downloads and dangerous file types\n\nBlockAllDownloads (3) = Block all downloads\n\nBlockMaliciousDownloads (4) = Block malicious downloads","group_id_src":"V-235752"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-235753r1015297","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:54:55\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT III, V-235753, SV-235753r1015297, SRG-APP-000378)\n","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000039","rule_title":"URLs must be allowlisted for plugin use if used.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-ocil.xml","name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.edge:questionnaire:6901"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-003980","CCI-001812"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"This requirement for \"Allow pop-up windows on specific sites\" is not required; this is optional.\n\nThe policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Content settings/Allow pop-up windows on specific sites\" must be set to \"Enabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\n\"PopupsAllowedForUrls\" must be set as follows:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\PopupsAllowedForUrls\\1 = mydomain.com\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\PopupsAllowedForUrls\\2 = myagency.mil\n\nIf configured, the list of domains for which Microsoft Edge allows pop-ups may be allowlisted.","rule_id_src":"SV-235753r1015297_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000378","false_positives":"","uuid":"A6925BB2-6D7C-1014-914D-BDE8105491DA","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5280","stig_uuid":"A68F29AE-6D7C-1014-9376-DC80EB852963","severity":"low","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_reviewed","group_id":"V-235753","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000378","id":"V-235753"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Content settings/Allow pop-up windows on specific sites\" to \"Enabled\". A list of allowlisted URLs may be specified here.","discussion":"Define a list of sites, based on URL patterns that can open pop-up windows.","group_id_src":"V-235753"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-235754r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:54:55\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Enable the setting 'Control which extensions cannot be installed')\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\ExtensionInstallBlocklist\\1'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000041","rule_title":"Extensions installation must be blocklisted by default.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:131"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Extensions/Control which extensions cannot be installed\" must be set to \"Enabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\ExtensionInstallBlocklist\\1\n\nIf the value for \"1\" is not set to \"REG_SZ = *\", this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-235754r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"A6926166-6D7C-1014-B784-DC985786B197","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5280","stig_uuid":"A68F29AE-6D7C-1014-9376-DC80EB852963","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_id":"V-235754","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-235754"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Extensions/Control which extensions cannot be installed\" to \"Enabled\". A list of blocklisted extensions may then be specified.","discussion":"List specific extensions that users cannot install in Microsoft Edge. When this policy is deployed, any extensions on this list that were previously installed will be disabled, and the user will not be able to enable them. If an item is removed from the list of blocked extensions, the extension is automatically reenabled anywhere it was previously installed.\n\nUse \"*\" to block all extensions that are not explicitly listed in the allow list.\n\nIf this policy is not configured, users can install any extension in Microsoft Edge.","group_id_src":"V-235754"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-235755r961479","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:54:55\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT III, V-235755, SV-235755r961479, SRG-APP-000386)\n","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000042","rule_title":"Extensions that are approved for use must be allowlisted if used.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-ocil.xml","name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.edge:questionnaire:7301"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-001774"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"This requirement for \"Allow specific extensions to be installed\" is not required; this is optional.\n\nThe policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Extensions/Allow specific extensions to be installed\" must be set to \"Enabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\n\"ExtensionInstallAllowlist\" must be set as follows:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\ExtensionInstallAllowlist\\1 = \"extension_id1\"\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\ExtensionInstallAllowlist\\2 = \"extension_id2\"\n\nIf configured, the list of extensions for which Microsoft Edge allows to be installed may be allowlisted.","rule_id_src":"SV-235755r961479_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000386","false_positives":"","uuid":"A692690B-6D7C-1014-8E2F-E459D13E0C6E","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5280","stig_uuid":"A68F29AE-6D7C-1014-9376-DC80EB852963","severity":"low","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_reviewed","group_id":"V-235755","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000386","id":"V-235755"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Extensions/Allow specific extensions to be installed\" to \"Enabled\".  A list of allowlisted extensions may then be specified.","discussion":"By default, all extensions are allowed. However, if all extensions are blocked by setting the \"ExtensionInstallBlockList\" policy to \"*,\" users can only install extensions defined in this policy.","group_id_src":"V-235755"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-235756r961521","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:54:55\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Disable Microsoft Edge Password Manager)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\PasswordManagerEnabled'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000043","rule_title":"The Password Manager must be disabled.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:132"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-002007"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Password manager and protection/Enable saving passwords to the password manager\" must be set to \"disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"PasswordManagerEnabled\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-235756r961521_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000400","false_positives":"","uuid":"A6926F84-6D7C-1014-B8AE-F30B09526B74","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5280","stig_uuid":"A68F29AE-6D7C-1014-9376-DC80EB852963","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_id":"V-235756","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000400","id":"V-235756"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Password manager and protection/Enable saving passwords to the password manager\" to \"disabled\".","discussion":"Enable Microsoft Edge to save user passwords.\n\nIf this policy is enabled, users can save their passwords in Microsoft Edge. The next time the user visits the site, Microsoft Edge will enter the password automatically.","group_id_src":"V-235756"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-235758r1117151","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:54:55\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT I, V-235758, SV-235758r1117151, SRG-APP-000456)\n","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000045","rule_title":"The version of Microsoft Edge running on the system must be a supported version.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-ocil.xml","name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.edge:questionnaire:7701"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-002605"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Cross-reference the build information displayed with the Microsoft Edge site to identify, at minimum, the oldest supported build available. \n\nIf the installed version of Edge is not supported by Microsoft, this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-235758r1117151_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000456","false_positives":"","uuid":"A6927819-6D7C-1014-8E5E-C486AC68A14F","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5280","stig_uuid":"A68F29AE-6D7C-1014-9376-DC80EB852963","severity":"high","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_reviewed","group_id":"V-235758","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000456","id":"V-235758"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Install a supported version of Edge.","discussion":"Security flaws with software applications are discovered daily. Vendors are constantly updating and patching their products to address newly discovered security vulnerabilities. Organizations (including any contractor to the organization) are required to promptly install security-relevant software updates (e.g., patches, service packs, and hot fixes). Flaws discovered during security assessments, continuous monitoring, incident response activities, or information system error handling must also be addressed expeditiously. \n\nOrganization-defined time periods for updating security-relevant software may vary based on a variety of factors including, for example, the security category of the information system or the criticality of the update (i.e., severity of the vulnerability related to the discovered flaw). \n\nThis requirement will apply to software patch management solutions that are used to install patches across the enclave and also to applications themselves that are not part of that patch management solution. For example, many browsers today provide the capability to install their own patch software. Patch criticality, as well as system criticality will vary. Therefore, the tactical situations regarding the patch management process will also vary. This means that the time period used must be a configurable parameter. Time frames for application of security-relevant software updates may be dependent upon the Information Assurance Vulnerability Management (IAVM) process.\n\nThe application will be configured to check for and install security-relevant software updates within an identified time period from the availability of the update. The specific time period will be defined by an authoritative source (e.g., IAVM, CTOs, DTMs, and STIGs).","group_id_src":"V-235758"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-235760r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:54:55\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Enable the setting 'Enable site isolation for every site')\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\SitePerProcess'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000047","rule_title":"Site isolation for every site must be enabled.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:135"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Enable site isolation for every site\" must be set to \"enabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"SitePerProcess\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 1\", this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-235760r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"A6927DAE-6D7C-1014-ABB2-8E2E63E4BBE8","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5280","stig_uuid":"A68F29AE-6D7C-1014-9376-DC80EB852963","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_id":"V-235760","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-235760"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Enable site isolation for every site\" to \"enabled\".","discussion":"The \"SitePerProcess\" policy can be used to prevent users from opting out of the default behavior of isolating all sites. The \"IsolateOrigins\" policy can be used to isolate additional, finer-grained origins.\n\nEnabling this policy prevents users from opting out of the default behavior where each site runs in its own process.\n\nIf this policy is not disabled or configured, a user can opt out of site isolation (e.g., by using \"Disable site isolation\" entry in edge://flags.) Disabling the policy or not configuring the policy does not turn off Site Isolation.","group_id_src":"V-235760"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-235761r1043177","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:54:55\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Enable the setting 'Supported authentication schemes')\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\AuthSchemes'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000048","rule_title":"Supported authentication schemes must be configured.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:136"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000382"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/HTTP authentication/Supported authentication schemes\" must be set to  \"ntlm,negotiate\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"AuthSchemes\" is not set to \"REG_SZ = ntlm,negotiate\", this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-235761r1043177_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000142","false_positives":"","uuid":"A69283D7-6D7C-1014-9EBA-C9EE653027D8","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5280","stig_uuid":"A68F29AE-6D7C-1014-9376-DC80EB852963","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_id":"V-235761","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000142","id":"V-235761"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/HTTP authentication/Supported authentication schemes\" to \"ntlm,negotiate\".","discussion":"This setting specifies which HTTP authentication schemes are supported.\n\nThe policy can be configured by using these values: \"basic\", \"digest\", \"ntlm\", and \"negotiate\". Separate multiple values with commas.\n\nIf this policy is not configured, all four schemes are used.","group_id_src":"V-235761"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-235763r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:54:55\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Microsoft Defender SmartScreen must be enabled.)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\SmartScreenEnabled'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000050","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender SmartScreen must be enabled.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:138"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/SmartScreen settings/Configure Microsoft Defender SmartScreen\" must be set to \"Enabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"SmartScreenEnabled\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 1\", this is a finding.\n\nIf this machine is on SIPRNet, this is Not Applicable.","rule_id_src":"SV-235763r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"A6928A09-6D7C-1014-B206-A6136DCF3DEE","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5280","stig_uuid":"A68F29AE-6D7C-1014-9376-DC80EB852963","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_id":"V-235763","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-235763"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/SmartScreen settings/Configure Microsoft Defender SmartScreen\" to \"Enabled\".","discussion":"This policy setting configures Microsoft Defender SmartScreen, which provides warning messages to help protect  users from potential phishing scams and malicious software. By default, Microsoft Defender SmartScreen is turned on.\n\nIf this setting is enabled, Microsoft Defender SmartScreen is turned on.\n\nIf this setting is disabled, Microsoft Defender SmartScreen is turned off.\n\nIf this setting is not configured, users can choose whether to use Microsoft Defender SmartScreen.\n\nThis policy is available only on Windows instances that are joined to a Microsoft Active Directory domain, Windows 10 Pro or Enterprise instances that enrolled for device management, or macOS instances that are that are managed via MDM or joined to a domain via MCX.","group_id_src":"V-235763"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-235764r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:54:55\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Microsoft Defender SmartScreen must be configured to block potentially unwanted apps.)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\SmartScreenPuaEnabled'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000051","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender SmartScreen must be configured to block potentially unwanted apps.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:139"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/SmartScreen settings/Configure Microsoft Defender SmartScreen to block potentially unwanted apps\" must be set to \"Enabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for SmartScreenPuaEnabled is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 1\", this is a finding.\n\nIf this machine is on SIPRNet, this is Not Applicable.","rule_id_src":"SV-235764r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"A6928FD0-6D7C-1014-8AAC-957CA9972A43","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5280","stig_uuid":"A68F29AE-6D7C-1014-9376-DC80EB852963","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_id":"V-235764","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-235764"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/SmartScreen settings/Configure Microsoft Defender SmartScreen to block potentially unwanted apps\" to \"Enabled\".","discussion":"This policy setting configures blocking for potentially unwanted apps with Microsoft Defender SmartScreen. Potentially unwanted app blocking with Microsoft Defender SmartScreen provides warning messages to help protect users from adware, coin miners, bundleware, and other low-reputation apps that are hosted by websites. Potentially unwanted app blocking with Microsoft Defender SmartScreen is turned off by default.\n\nIf this setting is enabled, potentially unwanted app blocking with Microsoft Defender SmartScreen is turned on.\n\nIf this setting is disabled, potentially unwanted app blocking with Microsoft Defender SmartScreen is turned off.\n\nIf this setting is not configured, users can choose whether to use potentially unwanted app blocking with Microsoft Defender SmartScreen.\n\nThis policy is available only on Windows instances that are joined to a Microsoft Active Directory domain, Windows 10 Pro or Enterprise instances that enrolled for device management, or macOS instances that are managed via MDM or joined to a domain via MCX.","group_id_src":"V-235764"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-235765r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:54:55\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Prompt for download location)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\PromptForDownloadLocation'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000052","rule_title":"The download location prompt must be configured.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:140"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Ask where to save downloaded files\" must be set to \"enabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"PromptForDownloadLocation\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 1\", this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-235765r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"A692957D-6D7C-1014-820D-B7D043D9E61F","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5280","stig_uuid":"A68F29AE-6D7C-1014-9376-DC80EB852963","severity":"low","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_id":"V-235765","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-235765"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Ask where to save downloaded files\" to \"enabled\".","discussion":"This setting provides positive feedback before a download starts, limiting the possibility of inadvertent downloads without notifying the user.","group_id_src":"V-235765"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-235766r1051115","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:54:55\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Tracking of browsing activity must be disabled.)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\TrackingPrevention'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000054","rule_title":"Tracking of browsing activity must be disabled.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:141"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000388"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Block tracking of users' web-browsing activity\" must be set to \"Enabled\" with the option value set to \"Balanced\" or \"Strict\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"TrackingPrevention\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 2\" or \"REG_DWORD = 3\", this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-235766r1051115_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000148","false_positives":"","uuid":"A6929AB0-6D7C-1014-AD20-FEF178768B39","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5280","stig_uuid":"A68F29AE-6D7C-1014-9376-DC80EB852963","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_id":"V-235766","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000148","id":"V-235766"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Block tracking of users' web-browsing activity\" to \"Balanced\" or \"Strict\".","discussion":"The setting allows websites to be blocked from tracking users' web-browsing activity.\n\nIf this policy is disabled or is not configured, users can set their own level of tracking prevention.\n\nPolicy options mapping:\n- TrackingPreventionOff (0) = Off (no tracking prevention)\n- TrackingPreventionBasic (1) = Basic (blocks harmful trackers; content and ads will be personalized)\n- TrackingPreventionBalanced (2) = Balanced (blocks harmful trackers and trackers from sites user has not visited; content and ads will be less personalized)\n- TrackingPreventionStrict (3) = Strict (blocks harmful trackers and majority of trackers from all sites; content and ads will have minimal personalization; some parts of sites might not work)","group_id_src":"V-235766"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-235767r960972","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:54:55\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Disable the setting 'Allow websites to query for available payment methods')\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\PaymentMethodQueryEnabled'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000055","rule_title":"A website's ability to query for payment methods must be disabled.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:142"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow websites to query for available payment methods\" must be set to \"disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for PaymentMethodQueryEnabled is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-235767r960972_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000149","false_positives":"","uuid":"A692A04F-6D7C-1014-B8B6-D1D6DC4EB6E7","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5280","stig_uuid":"A68F29AE-6D7C-1014-9376-DC80EB852963","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_id":"V-235767","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000149","id":"V-235767"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow websites to query for available payment methods\" to \"disabled\".","discussion":"This setting determines whether websites can check if the user has payment methods saved.\n\nIf this policy is disabled, websites that use \"PaymentRequest.canMakePayment\" or \"PaymentRequest.hasEnrolledInstrument\" API will be informed that no payment methods are available.\n\nIf this policy is enabled or is not set, websites can check to determine if the user has payment methods saved.","group_id_src":"V-235767"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-235768r1015298","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:54:55\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Suggestions of similar web pages in the event of a navigation error must be disabled.)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\AlternateErrorPagesEnabled'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000056","rule_title":"Suggestions of similar web pages in the event of a navigation error must be disabled.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:143"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381","CCI-000767"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Suggest similar pages when a webpage can't be found\" must be set to \"Disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for AlternateErrorPagesEnabled is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-235768r1015298_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000151","false_positives":"","uuid":"A692A5C1-6D7C-1014-AE34-F4E570A79D2F","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5280","stig_uuid":"A68F29AE-6D7C-1014-9376-DC80EB852963","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_id":"V-235768","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000151","id":"V-235768"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Suggest similar pages when a webpage can't be found\" to \"Disabled\".","discussion":"This setting allows Microsoft Edge to issue a connection to a web service to generate URL and search suggestions for connectivity issues such as DNS errors.\n\nIf this policy is enabled, a web service is used to generate URL and search suggestions for network errors.\n\nIf this policy is disabled, no calls to the web service are made and a standard error page is shown.\n\nIf this policy is not configured, Microsoft Edge respects the user preference that is set under Services at edge://settings/privacy. Specifically, there is a \"Suggest similar pages when a webpage can't be found\" toggle, which the user can switch on or off. \n\nNote that if this policy has been enabled (AlternateErrorPagesEnabled), the \"Suggest similar pages when a webpage can't be found setting\" is turned on, but the user cannot change the setting by using the toggle. \n\nIf this policy is disabled, the \"Suggest similar pages when a webpage can't be found\" setting is turned off, and the user cannot change the setting by using the toggle.","group_id_src":"V-235768"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-235769r960981","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:54:55\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Disable the setting 'Allow user feedback')\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\UserFeedbackAllowed'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000057","rule_title":"User feedback must be disabled.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:144"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow user feedback\" must be set to \"disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for UserFeedbackAllowed is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-235769r960981_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000152","false_positives":"","uuid":"A692AAFA-6D7C-1014-88EA-88C7FD35344A","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5280","stig_uuid":"A68F29AE-6D7C-1014-9376-DC80EB852963","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_id":"V-235769","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000152","id":"V-235769"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow user feedback\" to \"disabled\".","discussion":"Microsoft Edge uses the Edge Feedback feature (enabled by default) to allow users to send feedback, suggestions, or customer surveys and to report any issues with the browser. By default, users cannot disable (turn off) the Edge Feedback feature.\n\nIf this policy is enabled or not configured, users can invoke Edge Feedback.\n\nIf this policy is disabled, users cannot invoke Edge Feedback.","group_id_src":"V-235769"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-235770r960984","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:54:55\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (The collections feature must be disabled.)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\EdgeCollectionsEnabled'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000058","rule_title":"The collections feature must be disabled.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:145"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Enable the Collections feature\" must be set to \"Disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"EdgeCollectionsEnabled\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-235770r960984_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000153","false_positives":"","uuid":"A692B009-6D7C-1014-BB68-82E2E24EEA43","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5280","stig_uuid":"A68F29AE-6D7C-1014-9376-DC80EB852963","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_id":"V-235770","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000153","id":"V-235770"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Enable the Collections feature\" to \"Disabled\".","discussion":"This setting allows users to access the Collections feature, where they can collect, organize, share, and export content more efficiently and with Office integration.\n\nIf this policy is enabled or not configured, users can access and use the Collections feature in Microsoft Edge.\n\nIf this policy is disabled, users cannot access and use Collections in Microsoft Edge.","group_id_src":"V-235770"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-235771r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:54:55\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Enable the setting 'Enable site isolation for every site')\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\ConfigureShare'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000059","rule_title":"The Share Experience feature must be disabled.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:146"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Configure the Share experience\" must be set to \"enabled\" with the option value set to \"Don't allow using the Share experience\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"ConfigureShare\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 1\", this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-235771r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"A692B501-6D7C-1014-BF78-F994450DC208","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5280","stig_uuid":"A68F29AE-6D7C-1014-9376-DC80EB852963","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_id":"V-235771","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-235771"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Configure the Share experience\" to \"Don't allow using the Share experience\".","discussion":"If this policy is set to \"ShareAllowed\" (the default), users will be able to access the Windows 10 Share experience from the Settings and More menu in Microsoft Edge to share with other apps on the system.\n\nIf this policy is set to \"ShareDisallowed\", users will not be able to access the Windows 10 Share experience. If the Share button is on the toolbar, it will also be hidden.\n\nPolicy options mapping:\n- ShareAllowed (0) = Allow using the Share experience.\n- ShareDisallowed (1) = Do not allow using the Share experience.","group_id_src":"V-235771"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-235772r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:54:55\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Disable Browser Guest Mode)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\BrowserGuestModeEnabled'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000060","rule_title":"Guest mode must be disabled.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:147"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Enable guest mode\" must be set to \"disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"BrowserGuestModeEnabled\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-235772r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"A692B9F7-6D7C-1014-B65D-9EAB501A2543","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5280","stig_uuid":"A68F29AE-6D7C-1014-9376-DC80EB852963","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_id":"V-235772","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-235772"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Enable guest mode\" to \"disabled\".","discussion":"Enabling Guest mode allows the use of guest profiles in Microsoft Edge. In a guest profile, the browser does not import browsing data from existing profiles, and it deletes browsing data when all guest profiles are closed.\n\nIf this policy is enabled or not configured, Microsoft Edge lets users browse in guest profiles.\n\nIf this policy is disabled, Microsoft Edge does not let users browse in guest profiles.","group_id_src":"V-235772"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-235773r960993","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:54:55\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Relaunch notification must be required.)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\RelaunchNotification'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000061","rule_title":"Relaunch notification must be required.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:148"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Notify a user that a browser restart is recommended or required for pending updates\" must be set to \"Enabled\" with the option value set to \"Required\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"RelaunchNotification\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 2\", this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-235773r960993_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000156","false_positives":"","uuid":"A692BFD7-6D7C-1014-8765-890B6620C953","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5280","stig_uuid":"A68F29AE-6D7C-1014-9376-DC80EB852963","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_id":"V-235773","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000156","id":"V-235773"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Notify a user that a browser restart is recommended or required for pending updates\" web-browsing activity to \"Required\".","discussion":"Users must be required to restart the browser to finish installation of pending updates and prevent users from continually using an old/vulnerable browser version.","group_id_src":"V-235773"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-235774r1015299","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:54:55\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Built in DNS client is disabled)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\BuiltInDnsClientEnabled'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000062","rule_title":"The built-in DNS client must be disabled.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:149"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-001941","CCI-001942"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Use built-in DNS client\" must be set to \"disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"BuiltInDnsClientEnabled\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-235774r1015299_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000157","false_positives":"","uuid":"A692C5CE-6D7C-1014-B658-8853223C68EC","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5280","stig_uuid":"A68F29AE-6D7C-1014-9376-DC80EB852963","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_id":"V-235774","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000157","id":"V-235774"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Use built-in DNS client\" to \"disabled\".","discussion":"This setting controls whether to use the built-in DNS client.\n\nThis does not affect which DNS servers are used; it only controls the software stack that is used to communicate with them. For example, if the operating system is configured to use an enterprise DNS server, that same server would be used by the built-in DNS client. However, it is however possible that the built-in DNS client will address servers in different ways by using more modern DNS-related protocols such as DNS-over-TLS.\n\nIf this policy is enabled, the built-in DNS client is used if it is available.\n\nIf this policy is disabled, the client is never used.","group_id_src":"V-235774"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-246736r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:54:55\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (QUIC protocol is disabled)\n","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000063","rule_title":"Use of the QUIC protocol must be disabled.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:150"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow QUIC protocol\" must be set to \"Disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"QuicAllowed\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-246736r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"A692CB18-6D7C-1014-B9CE-CE10D3939AA2","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5280","stig_uuid":"A68F29AE-6D7C-1014-9376-DC80EB852963","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_id":"V-246736","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-246736"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow QUIC protocol\" to \"Disabled\".","discussion":"QUIC is used by more than half of all connections from the Edge web browser to Google's servers, and this activity is undesirable in the DoD.\n\nIf you enable this policy or don't configure it, the QUIC protocol is allowed.\n\nIf you disable this policy, the QUIC protocol is blocked.","group_id_src":"V-246736"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-251694r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:54:55\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT III, V-251694, SV-251694r960963, SRG-APP-000141)\n","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000064","rule_title":"The list of domains media autoplay allows must be allowlisted if used.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-ocil.xml","name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.edge:questionnaire:10901"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"If this machine is on SIPRNet, this is Not Applicable.\n\nThis requirement for \"AutoplayAllowlist\" is not required; this is optional.\n\nThe policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow media autoplay on specific sites\" may be set to \"allow\" for allowlisted domains.\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nAutoplayAllowlist may be set as follows:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\AutoplayAllowlist\\1 = mydomain.com\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\AutoplayAllowlist\\2 = myagency.mil\n\nIf configured, the list of domains for which autoplay is allowed may be allowlisted.","rule_id_src":"SV-251694r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"A692D024-6D7C-1014-9B2D-E46C9E2EFE3F","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5280","stig_uuid":"A68F29AE-6D7C-1014-9376-DC80EB852963","severity":"low","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_reviewed","group_id":"V-251694","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-251694"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow media autoplay on specific sites\" may be set to \"allow\" for allowlisted domains.","discussion":"Define a list of sites, based on URL patterns, that are allowed to autoplay media.\n\nIf this policy is not configured, the global default value from the AutoplayAllowed policy (if set) or the user's personal configuration is used for all sites.\n\nEDGE-00-000024 disables the AutoplayAllowed policy. ","group_id_src":"V-251694"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-260465r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:54:55\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Visual Search is disabled)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\VisualSearchEnabled'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000065","rule_title":"Visual Search must be disabled.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:260465"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Verify the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Visual search enabled\" is set to \"Disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"VisualSearchEnabled\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-260465r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"A692D566-6D7C-1014-9DBA-FCAFF0607C6C","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5280","stig_uuid":"A68F29AE-6D7C-1014-9376-DC80EB852963","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_id":"V-260465","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-260465"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Visual search enabled\" to \"Disabled\".","discussion":"Visual Search allows for quick exploration of more related content about entities in an image.\n\nIf this policy is enabled or not configured, Visual Search will be enabled via image hover, context menu, and search in Sidebar.\n\nIf this policy is disabled, Visual Search will be disabled and more information about images will not be available via hover, context menu, and search in Sidebar.","group_id_src":"V-260465"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-260466r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:54:55\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Copilot is disabled)\n","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000066","rule_title":"Copilot must be disabled.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:260466"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Verify the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Show Hubs Sidebar\" is set to \"Disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"HubsSidebarEnabled\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-260466r960963_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"A692DBBF-6D7C-1014-A442-8FCDD62A2F39","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5280","stig_uuid":"A68F29AE-6D7C-1014-9376-DC80EB852963","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_id":"V-260466","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-260466"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Show Hubs Sidebar\" to \"Disabled\".","discussion":"The Sidebar is a launcher bar on the right side of Microsoft Edge's screen.\n\nIf this policy is enabled or not configured, the Sidebar will be shown. If this policy is disabled, the Sidebar will never be shown.\n\nDisabling Sidebar will disable Copilot.","group_id_src":"V-260466"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-260467r960864","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:54:55\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Session only-based cookies is enabled)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\DefaultCookiesSetting'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000067","rule_title":"Session only-based cookies must be enabled.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:260467"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000166"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Verify the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Content settings/Configure cookies\" is set to \"Enabled\" with the option value set to \"Keep cookies for the duration of the session, except ones listed in 'SaveCookiesOnExit'\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for âDefaultCookiesSettingâ is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 4\", this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-260467r960864_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000080","false_positives":"","uuid":"A692E1C5-6D7C-1014-9F8B-C9AD36E1377B","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5280","stig_uuid":"A68F29AE-6D7C-1014-9376-DC80EB852963","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_id":"V-260467","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000080","id":"V-260467"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Content settings/Configure cookies\" to \"Enabled\" with the option value set to \"Keep cookies for the duration of the session, except ones listed in 'SaveCookiesOnExit'\".","discussion":"Cookies must only be allowed per session and only for approved URLs as permanently stored cookies can be used for malicious intent. \n\nApproved URLs may be allowlisted via the \"CookiesAllowedForUrls\" or \"SaveCookiesOnExit\" policy settings, but these are not requirements.","group_id_src":"V-260467"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-266981r1169858","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:54:55\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (FriendlyURLs is enabled)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\ConfigureFriendlyURLFormat'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000068","rule_title":"FriendlyURLs must be disabled.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:266981"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Configure the default paste format of URLs copied from Microsoft Edge and determine if additional formats will be available to users\" must be set to \"enabled\" with the option value set to \"The plain URL without any extra information, such as the pageÂ´s title. This is the recommended option when this policy is configured. For more information, see the description.\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"ConfigureFriendlyURLFormat\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 1\", this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-266981r1169858_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"A692E7B8-6D7C-1014-94BD-E6827BAAC0A1","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5280","stig_uuid":"A68F29AE-6D7C-1014-9376-DC80EB852963","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_id":"V-266981","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-266981"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft EdgeConfigure the default paste format of URLs copied from Microsoft Edge, and determine if additional formats will be available to users\" to \"enabled\" and select \"The plain URL without any extra information, such as the pageÂ´s title. This is the recommended option when this policy is configured. For more information, see the description.\"","discussion":"If FriendlyURLs are enabled, Microsoft Edge will compute additional representations of the URL and place them on the clipboard.\n\nThis policy configures what format will be pasted when the user pastes in external applications, or inside Microsoft Edge without the \"Paste As\" context menu item.\n\nIf configured, this policy makes a choice on behalf of the user. The options in edge://settings/shareCopyPaste will be grayed out, and the options in the \"Paste As\" context menu will not be available.\n\nNot configured = The user will be able to choose their preferred paste format. By default, this is set to the friendly URL format. The \"Paste As\" menu will be available in Microsoft Edge.\n\n1 = No additional formats will be stored on the clipboard. There will be no \"Paste as\" context menu item in Microsoft Edge and the only format available to paste will be the plain text URL format. Effectively, the friendly URL feature will be disabled.\n\n3 = The user will get a friendly URL whenever they paste into surfaces that accept rich text. The plain URL will still be available for non-rich surfaces. There will be no \"Paste As\" menu in Microsoft Edge.\n\n4 = (Not currently used)\n\nThe richer formats may not be well-supported in some paste destinations and/or websites. In these scenarios, the plain URL option is recommended when configuring this policy.\n\nThe recommended policy is available in Microsoft Edge 105 or later.\n\nPolicy options mapping:\n\nPlainText (1) = The plain URL without any extra information, such as the page's title. This is the recommended option when this policy is configured. For more information, see the description.\n\nTitledHyperlink (3) = Titled Hyperlink: A hyperlink that points to the copied URL, but whose visible text is the title of the destination page. This is the Friendly URL format.","group_id_src":"V-266981"},{"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-279940r1156561","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-05T07:54:55\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Access to Microsoft 365 Copilot writing assistance is disabled)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\ComposeInlineEnabled'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000069","rule_title":"Access to Microsoft 365 Copilot writing assistance must be disabled.","documentable":"false","weight":"10.0","mitigation_control":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:279940"},"security_override_guidance":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Control access to Microsoft 365 Copilot writing assistance in Microsoft Edge for Business\" must be set to \"disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"ComposeInlineEnabled\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","rule_id_src":"SV-279940r1156561_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","false_positives":"","uuid":"A692ED8A-6D7C-1014-84F3-B92817AB9900","responsibility":"","reference_identifier":"5280","stig_uuid":"A68F29AE-6D7C-1014-9376-DC80EB852963","severity":"medium","mitigations":"","potential_impacts":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_id":"V-279940","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-279940"},"third_party_tools":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Control access to Microsoft 365 Copilot writing assistance in Microsoft Edge for Business\" to \"disabled\".","discussion":"This policy controls whether users can use writing support features in Microsoft Edge for Business, such as Rewrite, which utilizes Microsoft 365 Copilot Chat.","group_id_src":"V-279940"}],"display_name":"Microsoft Edge","release_info":"Release: 4 Benchmark Date: 05 Jan 2026"}]}